apter.ipaddress;\n        }\n    }\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E',3,0,'2008-08-27 15:24:50'),(6080,'mlowried','x3Cpx3EWell, those features are specific to a tool that you are using for development in those languages.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EYou wouldnx27t have those tools if (for example) you were using notepad to write code. So, maybe you should ask the question for the tool you are using.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EFor PHP: x3Ca href=x22http://webservices.xml.com/pub/a/ws/2004/03/24/phpws.htmlx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Ehttp://webservices.xml.com/pub/a/ws/2004/03/24/phpws.htmlx3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E',2,0,'2008-08-07 11:17:55'),(6130,'srm9547','x3Cpx3E@Goyuix -- thatx27s excellent for something written from memory.\ntested it here -- found the connection wasnx27t opened. Otherwise very nice.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eusing System.Data.OleDb;\n...\n\nusing (OleDbConnection conn = new OleDbConnection())\n{\n    conn.ConnectionString = x22Provider=sqloledb;Data Source=yourServername\\\\yourInstance;Initial Catalog=databaseName;Integrated Security=SSPI;x22;\n\n    using (OleDbCommand cmd = new OleDbCommand())\n    {\n        conn.Open();\n        cmd.Connection = conn;\n        cmd.CommandText = x22Select * from yourTablex22;\n\n        using (OleDbDataReader dr = cmd.ExecuteReader())\n        {\n            while (dr.Read())\n            {\n                Console.WriteLine(dr[x22columnNamex22]);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E',26,0,'2008-08-04 05:31:31'),(6210,'achancelier6','x3Cpx3Etherex27s an x3Ca href=x22http://blog.sapien.com/index.php/2008/06/23/out-twitter/x22x3Eout-twitter scriptx3C/ax3E i use for posting to twitter. itx27s nice, as it means you can send something to twitter without the risk of being distracted by a browser.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3Ei added an alias for it, x22twitx22.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3Eso now you can type, for example:x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EPS C:\\x26gt;x22trying out stack overflowx22 | twitx3Cbrx3Ex3C/codex3Ex3C/prex