INSERT INTO `Question` VALUES (80,'SQLStatement.execute() - multiple queries in one statement','x3Cpx3EIx27ve written a database generation script in x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SQLx22x3ESQLx3C/ax3E and want to execute it in my x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Integrated_Runtimex22x3EAdobe AIRx3C/ax3E application:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3ECreate Table tRole (\n      roleID integer Primary Key\n      ,roleName varchar(40)\n);\nCreate Table tFile (\n    fileID integer Primary Key\n    ,fileName varchar(50)\n    ,fileDescription varchar(500)\n    ,thumbnailID integer\n    ,fileFormatID integer\n    ,categoryID integer\n    ,isFavorite boolean\n    ,dateAdded date\n    ,globalAccessCount integer\n    ,lastAccessTime date\n    ,downloadComplete boolean\n    ,isNew boolean\n    ,isSpotlight boolean\n    ,duration varchar(30)\n);\nCreate Table tCategory (\n    categoryID integer Primary Key\n    ,categoryName varchar(50)\n    ,parent_categoryID integer\n);\n...\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI execute this in Adobe AIR using the following methods:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Epublic static function RunSqlFromFile(fileName:String):void {\n    var file:File = File.applicationDirectory.resolvePath(fileName);\n    var stream:FileStream = new FileStream();\n    stream.open(file, FileMode.READ)\n    var strSql:String = stream.readUTFBytes(stream.bytesAvailable);\n    NonQuery(strSql);\n}\n\npublic static function NonQuery(strSQL:String):void\n{\n    var sqlConnection:SQLConnection = new SQLConnection();\n    sqlConnection.open(File.applicationStorageDirectory.resolvePath(DBPATH);\n    var sqlStatement:SQLStatement = new SQLStatement();\n    sqlStatement.text = strSQL;\n    sqlStatement.sqlConnection = sqlConnection;\n    try\n    {\n        sqlStatement.execute();\n    }\n    catch (error:SQLError)\n    {\n        Alert.show(error.toString());\n    }\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENo errors are generated, however only x3Ccodex3EtRolex3C/codex3E exists. It seems that it only looks at the first query (up to the semicolon- if I remove it, the query fails). Is there a way to call multiple queries in one statement?x3C/px3E',1,9,'hschade12','2008-08-01 17:57:07'),(90,'Good branching and merging tutorials for TortoiseSVN?','x3Cpx3EAre there any really good tutorials explaining x3Ca href=x22http://svnbook.red-bean.com/en/1.8/svn.branchmerge.htmlx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Ebranching and mergingx3C/ax3E with Apache Subversion? x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAll the better if itx27s specific to TortoiseSVN client.x3C/px3E',1,11,'cscarbarrowm','2008-08-01 18:41:24'),(120,'ASP.NET Site Maps','x3Cpx3EHas anyone got experience creating x3Cstrongx3ESQL-based ASP.NETx3C/strongx3E site-map providers?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve got the default XML file x3Ccodex3Eweb.sitemapx3C/codex3E working properly with my Menu and x3Cstrongx3ESiteMapPathx3C/strongx3E controls, but Ix27ll need a way for the users of my site to create and modify pages dynamically.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI need to tie page viewing permissions into the standard x3Ccodex3EASP.NETx3C/codex3E membership system as well.x3C/px3E',1,8,'msmallpeacex','2008-08-01 19:50:08'),(180,'Function for creating color wheels','x3Cpx3EThis is something Ix27ve pseudo-solved many times and never quite found a solution. Thatx27s stuck with me. The problem is to come up with a way to generate x3Ccodex3ENx3C/codex3E colors, that are as distinguishable as possible where x3Ccodex3ENx3C/codex3E is a parameter.x3C/px3E',1,8,'nivakhnov17','2008-08-01 22:42:19'),(260,'Adding scripting functionality to .NET applications','x3Cpx3EI have a little game written in C#. It uses a database as back-end. Itx27s \na x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collectible_card_gamex22x3Etrading card gamex3C/ax3E, and I wanted to implement the function of the cards as a script.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat I mean is that I essentially have an interface, x3Ccodex3EICardx3C/codex3E, which a card class implements (x3Ccodex3Epublic class Card056 : ICardx3C/codex3E) and which contains function that are called by the game.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENow, to make the thing maintainable/moddable, I would like to have the class for each card as source code in the database and essentially compile it on first use. So when I have to add/change a card, Ix27ll just add it to the database and tell my application to refresh, without needing any assembly deployment (especially since we would be talking about 1 assembly per card which means hundreds of assemblies).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs that possible? Register a class from a source file and then instantiate it, etc.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EICard Cards[current] = new MyGame.CardLibrary.Card056();\nCards[current].OnEnterPlay(ref currentGameState);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe language is C#, but extra bonus if itx27s possible to write the script in any .NET language.x3C/px3E',1,5,'clawrence3','2008-08-02 03:22:08'),(330,'Should I use nested classes in this case?','x3Cpx3EI am working on a collection of classes used for video playback and recording. I have one main class which acts like the public interface, with methods like x3Ccodex3Eplay()x3C/codex3E, x3Ccodex3Estop()x3C/codex3E, x3Ccodex3Epause()x3C/codex3E, x3Ccodex3Erecord()x3C/codex3E etc... Then I have workhorse classes which do the video decoding and video encoding. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI just learned about the existence of nested classes in C++, and Ix27m curious to know what programmers think about using them. I am a little wary and not really sure what the benefits/drawbacks are, but they seem (according to the book Ix27m reading) to be used in cases such as mine.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe book suggests that in a scenario like mine, a good solution would be to nest the workhorse classes inside the interface class, so there are no separate files for classes the client is not meant to use, and to avoid any possible naming conflicts? I donx27t know about these justifications. Nested classes are a new concept to me. Just want to see what programmers think about the issue.x3C/px3E',1,10,'rmaccurlyer','2008-08-02 06:51:36'),(470,'Homegrown consumption of web services','x3Cpx3EIx27ve been writing a few web services for a .net app, now Ix27m ready to consume them. Ix27ve seen numerous examples where there is homegrown code for consuming the service as opposed to using the auto generated methods Visual Studio creates when adding the web reference. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there some advantage to this?x3C/px3E',1,5,'scurraghy','2008-08-02 19:11:47'),(580,'Deploying SQL Server Databases from Test to Live','x3Cpx3EI wonder how you guys manage deployment of a database between 2 SQL Servers, specifically SQL Server 2005.\nNow, there is a development and a live one. As this should be part of a buildscript (standard windows batch, even do with current complexity of those scripts, i might switch to PowerShell or so later), Enterprise Manager/Management Studio Express do not count.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWould you just copy the .mdf File and attach it? I am always a bit careful when working with binary data, as this seems to be a compatiblity issue (even though development and live should run the same version of the server at all time).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EOr - given the lack of x22EXPLAIN CREATE TABLEx22 in T-SQL - do you do something that exports an existing database into SQL-Scripts which you can run on the target server? If yes, is there a tool that can automatically dump a given Database into SQL Queries and that runs off the command line? (Again, Enterprise Manager/Management Studio Express do not count).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnd lastly - given the fact that the live database already contains data, the deployment may not involve creating all tables but rather checking the difference in structure and ALTER TABLE the live ones instead, which may also need data verification/conversion when existing fields change.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENow, i hear a lot of great stuff about the x3Ca href=x22http://www.red-gate.com/products/index.htmx22x3ERed Gatex3C/ax3E products, but for hobby projects, the price is a bit steep.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo, what are you using to automatically deploy SQL Server Databases from Test to Live?x3C/px3E',1,8,'nivakhnov17','2008-08-03 03:30:59'),(650,'Automatically update version number','x3Cpx3EI would like the version property of my application to be incremented for each build but Ix27m not sure on how to enable this functionality in Visual Studio (2005/2008). I have tried to specify the AssemblyVersion as 1.0.* but it doesnx27t get me exactly what I want. x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m also using a settings file and in earlier attempts when the assembly version changed my settings got reset to the default since the application looked for the settings file in another directory. x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EI would like to be able to display a version number in the form of 1.1.38 so when a user finds a problem I can log the version they are using as well as tell them to upgrade if they have an old release.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EA short explanation of how the versioning works would also be appreciated. When does the build and revision number get incremented?x3C/px3E',1,8,'srm4902','2008-08-03 15:12:52'),(810,'Visual Studio Setup Project - Per User Registry Settings','x3Cpx3EIx27m trying to maintain a Setup Project in x3Ccodex3EVisual Studio 2003x3C/codex3E (yes, itx27s a legacy application). The problem we have at the moment is that we need to write registry entries to x3Ccodex3EHKCUx3C/codex3E for every user on the computer. They need to be in the x3Ccodex3EHKCUx3C/codex3E rather than x3Ccodex3EHKLMx3C/codex3E because they are the default user settings, and they do change per user. My feeling is thatx3C/px3E\n\nx3Colx3E\nx3Clix3EThis isnx27t possiblex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EThis isnx27t something the installer should be doing, but something the application should be doing (after all what happens when a user profile is created after the install?).x3C/lix3E\nx3C/olx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWith that in mind, I still want to change as little as possible in the application, so my question is, x3Cstrongx3Eis it possible to add registry entries for every user in a x3Ccodex3EVisual Studio 2003x3C/codex3E setup project?x3C/strongx3E x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnd, at the moment the project lists five registry root keys (x3Ccodex3EHKEY_CLASSES_ROOT, HKEY_CURRENT_USERx3C/codex3E, x3Ccodex3EHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINEx3C/codex3E, x3Ccodex3EHKEY_USERSx3C/codex3E, and User/Machine Hive). I donx27t really know anything about the Users root key, and havenx27t seen User/Machine Hive. Can anyone enlighten me on what they are? Perhaps they could solve my problem above.x3C/px3E',1,4,'osilley7','2008-08-04 00:35:01'),(930,'How do I connect to a database and loop over a recordset in C#?','x3Cpx3EWhatx27s the simplest way to connect and query a database for a set of records in C#?x3C/px3E',1,7,'itrowla','2008-08-04 04:47:25'),(1010,'How to get the value of built, encoded ViewState?','x3Cpx3EI need to grab the base64-encoded representation of the ViewState. Obviously this would not be available until fairly late in the request lifecycle, which is OK.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EFor example, if the output of the page includes:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ex26lt;input type=x22hiddenx22 name=x22__VIEWSTATEx22 \n  id=x22__VIEWSTATEx22 value=x22/wEPDwUJODU0Njc5MD...==x22 /x26gt;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI need a way on the server side to get the value x3Ccodex3Ex22/wEPDwUJODU0Njc5MD...==x22x3C/codex3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ETo clarify, I need this value when the page is being rendered, not on PostBack. e.g. I need to know the ViewState value that is being x3Cemx3Esentx3C/emx3E to the client, not the ViewState Ix27m getting back from them.x3C/px3E',1,4,'prihak','2008-08-04 07:59:42'),(1040,'How do I delete a file which is locked by another process in C#?','x3Cpx3EIx27m looking for a way to delete a file which is locked by another process using C#. I suspect the method must be able to find which process is locking the file (perhaps by tracking the handles, although Ix27m not sure how to do this in C#) then close that process before being able to complete the file delete using x3Ccodex3EFile.Delete()x3C/codex3E.x3C/px3E',1,4,'msmallpeacex','2008-08-04 09:45:22'),(1070,'Process size on UNIX','x3Cpx3EWhat is the correct way to get the process size on x3Ccodex3ESolaris, HP-UXx3C/codex3E and x3Ccodex3EAIXx3C/codex3E? Should we use x3Ccodex3Etopx3C/codex3E or x3Ccodex3Eps -o vszx3C/codex3E or something else?x3C/px3E',1,6,'clawrence3','2008-08-04 11:34:44'),(1160,'Use SVN Revision to label build in CCNET','x3Cpx3EI am using CCNET on a sample project with SVN as my source control. CCNET is configured to create a build on every check in. CCNET uses MSBuild to build the source code.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EI would like to use the latest revision number to generate AssemblyInfo.cs while compiling.\n\nHow can I retrieve the latest revision from subversion and use the value in CCNET?x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EEdit: Ix27m not using NAnt - only MSBuild.x3C/px3E',1,6,'wscreen1b','2008-08-04 15:37:24'),(1180,'How to make subdomain user accounts in a webapp','x3Cpx3EI am looking to allow users to control of subdomain of an app I am toying with, much like Basecamp where it is x3Ccodex3Ecustomusername.seework.comx3C/codex3E.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat is required on the x3Ccodex3EDNSx3C/codex3E end to allow these to be created dynamically and be available instantly. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnd how do you recommend dealing with this in the logic of the site? x3Ccodex3EHtaccessx3C/codex3E rule to  lookup the subdomain in the x3Ccodex3EDBx3C/codex3E?x3C/px3E',1,7,'hschade12','2008-08-04 16:22:07'),(1300,'Is nAnt still supported and suitable for .net 3.5/VS2008?','x3Cpx3EI am using MSBuild to build my stuff. I want to use CruiseControl.net as by Build Server.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3ENow, CCNET refers nAnt a lot, but it looks as if ccnet can do most of the stuff nant 