Visual Studio 2008 for C++ presumably with the built-in unit testing suite.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny links or tutorials would be appreciated.x3C/px3E',1,2,'rdowdellz','2008-08-06 11:57:50'),(3180,'Anyone soloing using fogbugz?','x3Cpx3EIs there anyone working solo and using fogbugz out there? Ix27m interested in personal experience/overhead versus paper.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EI am involved in several projects and get pretty hammered with lots of details to keep track of... Any experience welcome.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3E(Yes I know Mr. Joel is on the stackoverflow team... I still want good answers :)x3C/px3E',1,2,'sdally1','2008-08-06 12:47:45'),(3230,'How do you pack a visual studio c++ project for release?','x3Cpx3EIx27m wondering how to make a release build that includes all necessary dll files into the .exe so the program can be run on a non-development machine without it having to install the microsoft redistributable on the target machine.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EWithout doing this you get the error message that the application configuration is not correct and to reinstall.  x3C/px3E',1,7,'jsorel9','2008-08-06 13:49:27'),(3260,'Peak detection of measured signal','x3Cpx3EWe use a data acquisition card to take readings from a device that increases its signal to a peak and then falls back to near the original value. To find the peak value we currently search the array for the highest reading and use the index to determine the timing of the peak value which is used in our calculations.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis works well if the highest value is the peak we are looking for but if the device is not working correctly we can see a second peak which can be higher than the initial peak. We take 10 readings a second from 16 devices over a 90 second period.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy initial thoughts are to cycle through the readings checking to see if the previous and next points are less than the current to find a peak and construct an array of peaks. Maybe we should be looking at a average of a number of points either side of the current position to allow for noise in the system. Is this the best way to proceed or are there better techniques?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWe do use LabVIEW and I have checked the x3Ca href=x22http://forums.lavag.org/Peak-Detection-t8499.htmlx22x3ELAVA forumsx3C/ax3E and there are a number of interesting examples. This is part of our test software and we are trying to avoid using too many non-standard VI libraries so I was hoping for feedback on the process/algorithms involved rather than specific code. x3C/px3E',1,6,'eburnyaten','2008-08-06 14:23:18'),(3400,'How do you get leading wildcard full-text searches to work in SQL Server?','x3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3ENote:x3C/strongx3E I x3Cemx3Eamx3C/emx3E using SQLx27s Full-text search capabilities, CONTAINS clauses and all - the * is the wildcard in full-text, % is for LIKE clauses only.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve read in several places now that x22leading wildcardx22 searches (e.g. using x22*overflowx22 to match x22stackoverflowx22) is not supported in MS SQL.  Ix27m considering using a x3Ca href=x22http://blogs.msdn.com/sqlclr/archive/2005/06/29/regex.aspxx22x3ECLR function to add regex matchingx3C/ax3E, but Ix27m curious to see what other solutions people might have.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EMore Infox3C/strongx3E: x3Ca href=x22http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms552152.aspxx22x3EYou can add the asterisk only at the end of the word or phrase.x3C/ax3E - along with my empirical experience:  When matching x22myvaluex22, x22my*x22 works, but x22(asterisk)valuex22 returns no match, when doing a query as simple as:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3ESELECT * FROM TABLENAME WHERE CONTAINS(TextColumn, x27x22*searchtermx22x27);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThus, my need for a workaround.  Ix27m only using search in my site on an actual search page - so it needs to work basically the same way that Google works (in the eyes on a Joe Sixpack-type user). Not nearly as complicated, but this sort of match really shouldnx27t fail.x3C/px3E',1,11,'fbrizellc','2008-08-06 17:52:29'),(3470,'How do I Transform Sql Columns into Rows?','x3Cpx3EI have a very simple problem which requires a very quick and simple solution in SQL Server 2005.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have a table with x Columns. I want to be able to select one row from the table and then transform the columns into rows.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3ETableA\nColumn1, Column2, Column3\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESQL Statement to ruturnx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EResultA\nValue of Column1\nValue of Column2\nValue of Column3\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3E@Kevin:x3C/strongx3E Ix27ve had a google search on the topic but alot of the example where overly complex for my example, x3Cstrongx3Eare you able to help further?x3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3E@Mario: The solution I am creating has 10 columns which stores the values 0 to 6 and I must work out how many columns have the value 3 or more. So I thought about creating a query to turn that into rows and then using the generated table in a subquery to say count the number of rows with Column x3E= 3x3C/px3E',1,9,'dmatuszinski15','2008-08-06 18:36:56'),(3510,'What does the term x22BODMASx22 mean?','x3Cpx3EWhat is BODMAS and why is it useful in programming?x3C/px3E',1,3,'srm4902','2008-08-06 18:54:52'),(3530,'How do I run Rake tasks within a Ruby script?','x3Cpx3EI have a x3Ccodex3ERakefilex3C/codex3E with a Rake task that I would normally call from the command line:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Erake blog:post Title\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27d like to write a Ruby script that calls that Rake task multiple times, but the only solution I see is shelling out using `` (backticks) or x3Ccodex3Esystemx3C/codex3E.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhatx27s the right way to do this?x3C/px3E',1,6,'nivakhnov17','2008-08-06 19:15:54'),(3790,'Is there a WMI Redistributable Package?','x3Cpx3EIx27ve been working on a project that accesses the WMI to get information about the software installed on a userx27s machine. Wex27ve been querying Win32_Product only to find that it doesnx27t exist in 64-bit versions of Windows because itx27s an x3Ca href=x22http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa392726%28VS.85%29.aspxx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Ex22optional componentx22x3C/ax3E.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI know there are a lot of really good alternatives to querying the WMI for this information, but Ix27ve got a bit of a x3Ca href=x22http://www.codeplex.com/linq2wmix22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Evested interestx3C/ax3E in finding out how well this is going to work out.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat I want to know is if therex27s some kind of redistributable that can be packaged with our software to allow 64-bit users to get the WMI Installer Provider put onto their machines? Right now, they have to install it manually and the installation requires they have their Windows disc handy.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEdit:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3EYou didnx27t mention for what OS, but the WMI Redistributable Components version 1.0 definitely exists.x3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EFor Operation System, wex27ve been using .NET 3.5 so we need packages that will work on XP64 and 64bit versions of Windows Vista.x3C/px3E',1,8,'jsorel9','2008-08-06 22:15:43'),(4080,'What code analysis tools do you use for your Java projects?','x3Cpx3EWhat code analysis tools do you use on your Java projects?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI am interested in all kindsx3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3Estatic code analysis tools (FindBugs, PMD, and any others)x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ecode coverage tools (Cobertura, Emma, and any others)x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Eany other instrumentation-based tools x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Eanything else, if Ix27m missing somethingx3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIf applicable, also state what build tools you use and how well these tools integrate with both your IDEs and build tools. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIf a tool is only available a specific way (as an IDE plugin, or, say, a build tool plugin) that information is also worth noting.x3C/px3E',1,4,'fbrizellc','2008-08-07 02:45:27'),(4110,'What program can I use to generate diagrams of SQL view/table structure?','x3Cpx3EIx27ve been tasked with redesigning part of a ms-sql database structure which currently involves a lot of views, some of which contain joins to other views. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnyway, I wonder if anyone here could recommend a utility to automatically generate diagrams to help me visualise the whole structure.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhatx27s the best program youx27ve used for such problems?x3C/px3E',1,4,'gdodding5','2008-08-07 03:19:50'),(4170,'How to learn ADO.NET','x3Cpx3EI need to learn ADO.NET to build applications based on MS Office. I have read a good deal about ADO.NET in the MSDN Library, but everything seems rather messy to me.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat are the basics one must figure out when using ADO.NET? I think a few key words will suffice to let me organize my learning.x3C/px3E',1,5,'ofaircloughi','2008-08-07 04:25:03'),(4230,'The Difference Between a DataGrid and a GridView in ASP.NET?','x3Cpx3EIx27ve been doing ASP.NET development for a little while now, and Ix27ve used both the GridView and the DataGrid controls before for various things, but I never could find a really good reason to use one or the other. Ix27d like to know:x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat is the difference between these 2 ASP.NET controls? What are the advantages or disadvantages of both? Is one any faster? Newer? Easier to maintain?x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EThe intellisense summary for the controls doesnx27t seem to describe any difference between the two. They both can view, edit, and sort data and automatically generate columns at runtime.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EEdit:x3C/strongx3E Visual Studio 2008 no longer lists DataGrid as an available control in the toolbox. It is still available (for legacy support I assume) if you type it in by hand though.x3C/px3E',1,2,'idevey11','2008-08-07 04:54:31'),(4320,'ASP.Net 2.0 Application without Business Logic Layer?','x3Cpx3EIs it x22acceptablex22 to have an x3Cstrongx3EASP.Net 2.0x3C/strongx3E application without the BLL (Business Logic Layer) as the following?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Colx3E\nx3Clix3ESQL Server Data Storage x26amp; Stored Proceduresx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EData Link Layer (Strongly Typed Table Adapters) connecting to Stored Procsx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EPresentation Layer ASPX Pages with Code behind and ObjectDataSource for connection straight to the DLLx3C/lix3E\nx3C/olx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs a BLL always preferable, even if business logic is entirely validatable in the presentationx27s code behind?  What are the potential drawbacks for not using a BLL?x3C/px3E',1,7,'tplumsteadj','2008-08-07 06:41:24'),(4430,'How to easily consume a web service from PHP','x3Cpx3EIs there available any tool for PHP which can be used to generate code for consuming a x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_servicex22x3Eweb servicex3C/ax3E based on its x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_Services_Description_Languagex22x3EWSDLx3C/ax3E? Something comparable to clicking x22Add Web Referencex22 in Visual Studio or the Eclipse plugin which does the same thing for Java.x3C/px3E',1,5,'cribbens4','2008-08-07 09:48:33'),(4610,'How can I create Prototype Methods (like JavaScript) in C#.Net?','x3Cpx3EHow is it possible to make prototype methods in C#.Net?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn JavaScript, I can do the following to create a trim method for the string object:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EString.prototype.trim = function() {\n    return this.replace(/^\\s+|\\s+$/g,x22x22);\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow can I go about doing this in C#.Net?x3C/px3E',1,7,'jsorel9','2008-08-07 16:00:50'),(4630,'How can I Java webstart multiple, dependent, native libraries?','x3Cpx3EExample: I have two shared objects (same should apply to .dlls). The first shared object is from a third-party library, wex27ll call it libA.so. I have wrapped some of this with JNI and created my own library, libB.so. Now libB depends on libA.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EWhen webstarting, both libraries are places in some webstart working area. My java code attempts to load libB. At this point the system loader will attempt to load libA which is not in the system library path (java.library.path wonx27t help this). The end result is that libB has an unsatisfied link and cannot be used. x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EI have tried loading libA before libB, but that still does not work. Seems the OS wants to do that loading for me. Is there any way I can make this work other than statically  compiling?x3C/px3E',1,1,'itrowla','2008-08-07 16:26:50'),(4670,'DVCS Choices - Whatx27s good for Windows?','x3Cpx3ESo I want to get a project on a distributed version control system, such as mercurial, git, or bazaar.  The catch is that I need the Windows support to be good, i.e. no instructions that start off with x22install cygwin...x22.  Now Ix27ve x3Cemx3Eheardx3C/emx3E that gitx27s Windows support is decent these days, but donx27t have any first hand experience.  Also, it sounds like the bazaar team has an explicit goal of making it as multiplatform as possible.\n\nCan I get any recommendations?x3C/px3E',1,11,'aalandg','2008-08-07 16:57:32'),(4850,'C# and Arrow Keys','x3Cpx3EI am new to C# and am doing some work in an existing application. I have a DirectX viewport that has components in it that I want to be able to position using arrow keys.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECurrently I am overriding ProcessCmdKey and catching arrow input and send an OnKeyPress event. This works, but I want to be able to use modifiers(x3Cstrongx3Ex3Ckbdx3EALTx3C/kbdx3E+x3Ckbdx3ECTRLx3C/kbdx3E+x3Ckbdx3ESHIFTx3C/kbdx3Ex3C/strongx3E). As soon as I am holding a modifier and press an arrow no events are triggered that I am listening to.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDoes anyone have any ideas or suggestions on where I should go with this?x3C/px3E',1,5,'aauger2','2008-08-07 19:23:28'),(4860,'Authoritative source on XML-sig','x3Cpx3EWe have a question with regards to XML-sig and need detail about the optional elements as well as some of the canonicalization and transform stuff.  Wex27re writing a spec for a very small XML-syntax payload that will go into the metadata of media files and it needs to by cryptographically signed.  Rather than re-invent the wheel, We thought we should use the XML-sig spec but I think most of it is overkill for what we need, and so we like to have more information/dialogue with people who know the details.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESpecifically, do we need to care about either transforms or canonicalization if the XML is very basic with no tabs for formatting and is specific to our needs?x3C/px3E',1,8,'nivakhnov17','2008-08-07 19:33:59'),(4870,'Why is this regular expression faster?','x3Cpx3EIx27m writing a Telnet client of sorts in C# and part of what I have to parse are ANSI/VT100 escape sequences, specifically, just those used for colour and formatting (detailed x3Ca href=x22http://www.termsys.demon.co.uk/vtansi.htm#colorsx22x3Eherex3C/ax3E).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EOne method I have is one to find all the codes and remove them, so I can render the text without any formatting if needed:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E    \npublic static string StripStringFormating(string formattedString)\n{\n    if (rTest.IsMatch(formattedString))\n        return rTest.Replace(formattedString, string.Empty);\n    else\n        return formattedString;\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m new to regular expressions and I was suggested to use this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Estatic Regex rText = new Regex(@x22\\e\\[[\\d;]+mx22, RegexOptions.Compiled);x3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHowever, this failed if the escape code was incomplete due to an error on the server. So then this was suggested, but my friend warned it might be slower (this one also matches another condition (z) that I might come across later):x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Estatic Regex rTest = \n              new Regex(@x22(\\e(\\[([\\d;]*[mz]?))?)?x22, RegexOptions.Compiled);x3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis not only worked, but was in fact faster to and reduced the impact on my text rendering. Can someone explain to a regexp newbie, why? :)x3C/px3E',1,4,'rdowdellz','2008-08-07 19:43:11'),(4880,'Is a x22Confirm Emailx22 input good practice when user changes email address?','x3Cpx3EMy organization has a form to allow users to update their email address with us.\n\nItx27s suggested that we have two input boxes for email: the second as an email confirmation.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EI always copy/paste my email address when faced with the confirmation.\n\nIx27m assuming most of our users are not so savvy.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3ERegardless, is this considered a good practice?\n\nI canx27t stand it personally, but I also realize it probably isnx27t meant for me.\n\nIf someone screws up their email, they canx27t login, and they must call to sort things out.x3C/px3E',1,6,'achancelier6','2008-08-07 19:54:22'),(4930,'How to reference to multiple version assembly','x3Cpx3EIx27m developing a Sharepoint application and use .NET AjaxControlToolkit library, we are adding a custom aspx page to the Sharepoint. Sharepoint 2007 run in quirks mode so Ix27ve made some modification to the AJAX library to make it behave like it normally should. The problem is, the other team already use AJAX library and it is a different version with mine. This cause conflict because there could be only one dll in the bin folder with the same name.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EFrom what I know, .NET should be able to handle this situation easily. Ix27ve tried using strong name and GAC to solve it, but it still refer to the dll in the bin folder. If there is no AjaxControlToolkit.dll in the bin folder, the application will simply fail to load the assembly. x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EIf I use complete assembly information on my like this x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ex26lt;%@ x3Cbrx3E    Register x3Cbrx3E    tagprefix=x22AjaxControlToolkitx22x3Cbrx3E    namespace=x22AjaxControlToolkitx22x3Cbrx3E    assembly=x22AjaxControlToolkit, Version=1.0.299.18064, x3Cbrx3E    PublicKeyToken=12345678abcdefgh, x3Cbrx3E    Culture=neutralx22x3Cbrx3E%x26gt;x3Cbrx3Ex3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EIt gives me Compiler Error CS0433x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3ECan someone help me on how to use multiple version of assembly in an application?x3C/px3E',1,1,'rmaccurlyer','2008-08-07 20:35:33'),(5170,'SQL Server Management Studio alternatives to browse/edit tables and run queries','x3Cpx3EI was wondering if there are any alternatives to Microsoftx27s SQL Server Management Studio?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENot therex27s anything wrong with SSMS, but sometimes it just seem too big an application where all I want todo is browse/edit tables and run queries.x3C/px3E',1,11,'cribbens4','2008-08-07 23:06:03'),(5260,'What is the best way to wrap time around the work day?','x3Cpx3EI have a situation where I want to add hours to a date and have the new date wrap around the work-day. I cobbled up a function to determine this new date, but want to make sure that Ix27m not forgetting anything.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe hours to be added is called x22delayx22. It could easily be a parameter to the function instead.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EPlease post any suggestions. [VB.NET Warning]x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EPrivate Function GetDateRequired() As Date\n    x27x27// A decimal representation of the current hour\n    Dim hours As Decimal = Decimal.Parse(Date.Now.Hour) + (Decimal.Parse(Date.Now.Minute) / 60.0) \n\n    Dim delay As Decimal = 3.0           x27x27// delay in hours\n    Dim endOfDay As Decimal = 12.0 + 5.0 x27x27// end of day, in hours\n    Dim startOfDay As Decimal = 8.0      x27x27// start of day, in hours\n\n    Dim newHour As Integer\n    Dim newMinute As Integer\n\n    Dim dateRequired As Date = Now\n    Dim delta As Decimal = hours + delay\n\n    x27x27// Wrap around to the next day, if necessary\n    If delta x26gt; endOfDay Then\n        delta = delta - endOfDay\n        dateRequired = dateRequired.AddDays(1)\n\n        newHour = Integer.Parse(Decimal.Truncate(delta))\n        newMinute = Integer.Parse(Decimal.Truncate((delta - newHour) * 60))\n        newHour = startOfDay + newHour\n    Else\n        newHour = Integer.Parse(Decimal.Truncate(delta))\n        newMinute = Integer.Parse(Decimal.Truncate((delta - newHour) * 60))\n    End If\n\n    dateRequired = New Date(dateRequired.Year, dateRequired.Month, dateRequired.Day, newHour, newMinute, 0)\n\n    Return dateRequired\nEnd Sub\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3ENotex3C/strongx3E: This will probably not work if delay is more than 9 hours long. It should never change from 3, through.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEDIT:\nThe goal is find the date and time that you get as a result of adding several hours to the current time. This is used to determine a default value for a due date of a submission. I want to add 3 hours to the current time to get the due date time. However, I donx27t want due dates that go beyond 5pm on the current day. So, I tried to have the hours split between (today, up to 5pm) and (tomorrow, from 8am on), such that adding 3 hours to 4pm would give you 19am, because 1 hour is added to the end of today and 2 hours are added to the beginning of tomorrow.x3C/px3E',1,10,'hbuxcy1c','2008-08-08 00:21:52'),(5460,'Telligentx27s Community Server','x3Cpx3EThe company I work for is wanting to add blog functionality to our website and they were looking to spend an awful amount of money to have some crap being built on top of a CMS they purchased (sitecore).  I pointed them to Telligentx27s Community Server and  we had a sales like meeting today to get the Marketing folks on board. \n\nMy question is if anyone has had issues working with Community Server, skinning it and extending it?x3Cbrx3E\n\nI wanted to explain a bit why I am thinking Community Server, the company is wanting multiple blogs with multiple authors.  I want to be out of the admin part of this as much as possible and didnx27t think there were too many engines that having multiple blogs didnx27t mean db work.  I also like the other functionality that Community Server provides and think the company will find it useful, particularly the media section as right now we have some really shotty way of dealing with whitepapers and stuff.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3Eedit: We are actually using the Sitecore blog module for a single blog on our intranet (which is actually what the CMS is serving).  Some reasoning for why I donx27t like it for our public site are they are on different servers, it doesnx27t support multiple authors, there is no built in syndication, it is a little flimsy feeling to me from looking at the source and I personally think the other features of Community Server make its price tag worth it.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3Eanother edit: Need to stick to .net software that run on sql server in my companyx27s case, but I donx27t mind seeing recommendations for others.  ExpressionEngine looks promising, will try it out on my personal box.x3C/px3E',1,6,'tplumsteadj','2008-08-08 03:00:30'),(5600,'Tables with no Primary Key','x3Cpx3EI have several tables whose only unique data is a uniqueidentifier (a Guid) column. Because guids are non-sequential (and theyx27re client-side generated so I canx27t use newsequentialid()), I have made a non-primary, non-clustered index on this ID field rather than giving the tables a clustered primary key.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m wondering what the performance implications are for this approach. Ix27ve seen some people suggest that tables should have an auto-incrementing (x22identityx22) int as a clustered primary key even if it doesnx27t have any meaning, as it means that the database engine itself can use that value to quickly look up a row instead of having to use a bookmark.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy database is merge-replicated across a bunch of servers, so Ix27ve shied away from identity int columns as theyx27re a bit hairy to get right in replication.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat are your thoughts? Should tables have primary keys? Or is it ok to not have any clustered indexes if there are no sensible columns to index that way?x3C/px3E',1,10,'enewberryf','2008-08-08 06:47:15'),(5690,'MVC Preview 4 - No route in the route table matches the supplied values','x3Cpx3EI have a route that I am calling through a RedirectToRoute like this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ereturn this.RedirectToRoute(x22Super-SuperRoutex22, new { year = selectedYear });\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have also tried:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E return this.RedirectToRoute(x22Super-SuperRoutex22, new { controller = x22Superx22, action = x22SuperRoutex22, id = x22RouteTopicx22, year = selectedYear });\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe route in the global.asax is like this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eroutes.MapRoute(\n    x22Super-SuperRoutex22, // Route name\n    x22Super.mvc/SuperRoute/{year}x22,  // URL with parameters\n     new { controller = x22Superx22, action = x22SuperRoutex22, id = x22RouteTopicx22 }  // Parameter defaults\n);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo why do I get the error: x22No route in the route table matches the supplied values.x22?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI saw that the type of selectedYear was var.  When I tried to convert to int with int.Parse I realised that selectedYear was actually null, which would explain the problems.  I guess next time Ix27ll pay more attention to the values of the variables at a breakpoint :)x3C/px3E',1,4,'civakhnop','2008-08-08 09:03:42'),(5880,'Are there any negative reasons to use an N-Tier solution?','x3Cpx3EIx27m pretty new to my company (2 weeks) and wex27re starting a new platform for our system using .NET 3.5 Team Foundation from DotNetNuke. Our x22architectx22 is suggesting we use one class project. Of course, I chime back with a x223-tierx22 architecture (Business, Data, Web class projects). x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there any disadvantages to using this architecture? Prox27s would be separation of code from data, keeping class objects away from your code, etc.x3C/px3E',1,11,'prihak','2008-08-08 17:04:02'),(6080,'What to use for login ID?','x3Cpx3EWe are in the early design stages of a major rewrite of our product. Right now our customers are mostly businesses. We manage accounts. User names for an account are each on their own namespace but it means that we canx27t move assets between servers.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EWe want to move to a single namespace. But that brings the problem of unique user names.x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3ESo whatx27s the best idea?x3C/px3E\n\n\n\nx3Culx3E\n\nx3Clix3EEmail address (w/verification) ?x3C/lix3E\n\nx3Clix3EUnique alpha-numeric string (x22johnsmith9234x22)?x3C/lix3E\n\nx3Clix3EShould we look at OpenID?x3C/lix3E\n\nx3C/ulx3E',1,5,'aa9279','2008-08-08 19:40:58'),(6110,'Normalizing a Table with Low Integrity','x3Cpx3EIx27ve been handed a table with about 18000 rows. Each record describes the location of one customer. The issue is, that when the person created the table, they did not add a field for x22Company Namex22, only x22Location Name,x22 and one company can have many locations.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EFor example, here are some records that describe the same customer:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3ELocation Tablex3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E ID  Location_Name     \n 1   TownShop#1        \n 2   Town Shop - Loc 2 \n 3   The Town Shop     \n 4   TTS - Someplace   \n 5   Town Shop,the 3   \n 6   Toen Shop4        \nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy goal is to make it look like:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3ELocation Tablex3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E ID  Company_ID   Location_Name     \n 1   1            Town Shop#1       \n 2   1            Town Shop - Loc 2 \n 3   1            The Town Shop     \n 4   1            TTS - Someplace   \n 5   1            Town Shop,the 3   \n 6   1            Toen Shop4        