e been doing, lately. The application that Ix27m building is intended for distribution among consumers who will probably not have the latest version (or perhaps x3CEMx3Eany versionx3C/EMx3E) of the .NET framework on their machines.x3C/Px3E\n\nx3CPx3EI went to go x3CA href=x22http://www.microsoft.com/downloads/details.aspx?FamilyId=333325FD-AE52-4E35-B531-508D977D32A6x26amp;displaylang=enx22x3Edownload the .NET 3.5 redistributable packagex3C/Ax3E only to find out that itx27s almost x3CSTRONGx3Ex3CEMx3E200 MB!x3C/EMx3Ex3C/STRONGx3E This is unacceptable for my application, because itx27s supposed to be a quick and painless consumer application that installs quickly and keeps a low profile on the userx27s machine. For users that have .NET 3.5 already installed, our binary downloads have been instantaneous, so far. This 200 MB gorilla will more than quadruple the size of the download. Is there any other option than this redistributable package that I can use to make sure the framework is on the machine that wonx27t take the user out of our x22quick and painlessx22 workflow? Our target time from beginning of download to finalizing the install is less than two minutes. Is it just not possible for someone who doesnx27t already have .NET installed?x3C/Px3E',1,1,'rdowdellz','2008-08-09 02:32:01'),(6530,'Where should I put my log file for an asp.net application?','x3Cpx3EI have a ASP.NET application that wex27ve written our own logging module for.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy question is, where is the standard place to write a log file to? I.e. the website will be running as the anonymous user identity (e.g. IUSR on IIS7) and I need a place where I know itx27ll have permission to write to.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECheers,x3C/px3E',1,9,'erowcliffe1d','2008-08-09 06:03:52'),(6890,'How to wait for thread complete before continuing?','x3Cpx3EI have some code for starting a thread on the .NET CF 2.0:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EThreadStart tStart = new ThreadStart(MyMethod);\nThread t = new Thread(tStart);\nt.Start();\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIf I call this inside a loop the items complete out of order. How do introduce a wait after x3Ccodex3Et.Start()x3C/codex3E, so that the work on the thread completes before the code continues? Will BeginInvoke/EndInvoke be a better option for this than manually creating threads?x3C/px3E',1,4,'dsizland14','2008-08-10 00:00:37'),(7180,'Animation in .NET','x3Cpx3EWhat is a good way to perform animation using .NET?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI would prefer not to use Flash if possible, so am looking for suggestions of ways which will work to implement different types of animation on a new site I am producing.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe new site is for a magician, so I want to provide animated buttons (Cards turning over, etc.) and also embed video.  Is it possible to do this without using Flash or is this the only real solution?  I would like to keep it as cross-platform and standard as possible.x3C/px3E',1,4,'wscreen1b','2008-08-10 16:39:20'),(7190,'Setting up Continuous Integration with SVN','x3Cpx3EWhat tools would you recommend for setting up CI for build and deployment of multiple websites built on DotNetNuke using SVN for source control? x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWe are currently looking at configuring Cruise Control to work with NAnt, NUnit, NCover and Trac as a test case. What other combinations would worth investigating?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWe have full control of our development environment so using some form of CI is certain here but I would also like to convince our production services team that they can reliably deploy to the system test, uat and even production environments using these tools.x3C/px3E',1,11,'aa9279','2008-08-10 17:09:13'),(7260,'How do I setup Public-Key Authentication?','x3Cpx3EHow do I setup Public-Key Authentication for SSH?x3C/px3E',1,3,'aalandg','2008-08-10 21:50:11'),(7440,'What do you use to Unit-Test your Web UI?','x3Cpx3EThe company Ix27m currently working for is using x3Ca href=x22http://selenium.