lic TokenTree()\n    {\n        /* I must admit to not fully understanding this,\n         * I got it from msdn. As far as I can tell, IDictionary is an\n         * interface, and Dictionary is the default implementation of\n         * that interface, right?\n         */\n        SubPairs = new Dictionaryx26lt;string, stringx26gt;();\n    }\n\n    public string Key;\n    public string Value;\n    public IDictionaryx26lt;string, stringx26gt; SubPairs;\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EItx27s only really a simple shunt for passing around data.x3C/px3E',1,8,'msmallpeacex','2008-08-12 17:12:50'),(8830,'Not showing Dialog when opening file in Acrobat Pro using Applescript','x3Cpx3EWhen opening Adobe Acrobat Pro, whether it be through x3Cstrongx3EApplescriptx3C/strongx3E or finder, the introductory dialog is shown.  Is there a way to not show this dialog without already having checked the x22Donx27t Show Againx22 option when opening a document using x3Cstrongx3EApplescriptx3C/strongx3E?  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EPhotoshop and Illustrator x3Cstrongx3EApplescriptx3C/strongx3E libraries have ways of setting interaction levels and not showing dialogs, but I canx27t seem to find the option in Acrobat.x3C/px3E',1,5,'kgrenkovu','2008-08-12 17:43:30'),(8880,'Get list of domains on the network','x3Cpx3EUsing the Windows API, how can I get a list of domains on my network?x3C/px3E',1,2,'clawrence3','2008-08-12 18:20:31'),(8940,'VMWare Server Under Linux Secondary NIC connection','x3Cpx3EWith VMWare Server running under Linux (Debain), I would like to have the following setup:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3E1st: NIC being used by many of the\nimages running under VMWare, as well\nas being used by the Linux OS x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3E2nd: NIC being used by only 1 image and to be unused by the Linux OS (as its part of a DMZ)x3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAlthough the second NIC wonx27t be used by Linux, it is certainly recognised as a NIC (e.g. eth1).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs this possible under VMWare Server, and if so, is it as simple as not binding eth1 under Linux and then bridging it to the image under VMWare Server?x3C/px3E',1,5,'nivakhnov17','2008-08-12 19:04:29'),(8950,'SharePoint WSS 3.0 Integration with Mac OSX (either Safari or Firefox)','x3Cpx3EWe have a SharePoint WSS site and some of our users on on the Mac OSX platform.  Are there any tips or tricks to get a similar experience to Windows with document shares and calendars on the Mac?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEdit: Browsing a SharePoint WSS site on a Mac, whether using Firefox or Safari, has a very similar look and feel as it does on Windows IE.  The similar experience I am looking for has to do with integrating the calendars, document shares, etc. into the desktop.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EFor example, with IE you can go to a calendar and select x22Actions -x3E Connect to Outlookx22 and it will make the calendar visible and manageable from within Outlook.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there any way to get the Mac to work similarly?x3C/px3E',1,8,'dsizland14','2008-08-12 19:17:47'),(8970,'Accessing iSight programatically?','x3Cpx3EIs it possible to access the iSight camera on a macbook programatically? By this I mean I would like to be able to just grab still frames from the iSight camera on command and then do something with them. If so, is it only accessible using objective c, or could other languages be used as well? x3C/px3E',1,3,'clawrence3','2008-08-12 19:31:40'),(9240,'Interfaces on different logic layers','x3Cpx3ESay you have an application divided into 3-tiers: GUI, business logic, and data access. In your business logic layer you have described your business objects: getters, setters, accessors, and so on... you get the idea. The interface to the business logic layer guarantees safe usage of the business logic, so all the methods and accessors you call will validate input. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis great when you first write the UI code, because you have a neatly defined interface that you can trust.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBut here comes the tricky part, when you start writing the data access layer, the interface to the business logic does not accommodate your needs. You need to have more accessors and getters to set fields which are/used to be hidden. Now you are forced to erode the interface of your business logic; now it is possible set fields from the UI layer, which the UI layer has no business setting. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBecause of the changes needed for the data access layer, the interface to the business logic has eroded to the point where it is possible to even set the business logic with invalid data. Thus, the interface does not guarantee safe usage anymore.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI hope I explained the problem clearly enough. How do you prevent interface eroding, maintain information hiding and encapsulation, and yet still accommodate different interface needs among different layers? x3C/px3E',1,9,'awrefford16','2008-08-13 01:06:38'),(9410,'How do you pass a function as a parameter in C?','x3Cpx3EI want to create a function that performs a function passed by parameter on a set of data. How do you pass a function as a parameter in C?x3C/px3E',1,3,'mschafflere','2008-08-13 06:16:32'),(9570,'What libraries do I need to link my mixed-mode application to?','x3Cpx3EIx27m integrating .NET support into our C++ application.x3Cbr /x3E\nItx27s an old-school MFC application, with 1 extra file compiled with the x22/clrx22 option that references a CWinFormsControl.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m not allowed to remove the linker flag x22/NODEFAULTLIBx22.x3Cbr /x3E\n(We have our own build management system, not Visual Studiox27s.)x3Cbr /x3E\nThis means I have to specify all necessary libraries: VC runtime and MFC.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EOther compiler options include x22/MDx22x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENext to that: I canx27t use the linker flag x22/FORCE:MULTIPLEx22 and just add x3Cemx3Eeverythingx3C/emx3E:x3Cbr /x3E\nIx27m looking for a non-overlapping set of libraries.x3C/px3E',1,3,'erowcliffe1d','2008-08-13 12:05:00'),(9650,'Lisp/Scheme interpreter without Emacs?','x3Cpx3Ex3Cbr /x3E\nIx27ve been wanting to teach myself Lisp for a while.  However, all the interpreters of which Ix27ve heard involve some flavor of emacs.\nAre there any command line interpreters, such that I could type this into the command line:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3Elispinterpret sourcefile.lispx3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ejust like I can run perl or python.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhile Ix27d also like to become more familiar with Emacs (if only not to be frustrated when I work with somebody who uses Emacs), Ix27d rather decouple learning Emacs from learning Lisp.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEdit: I actually want to follow SICP which uses Scheme, so an answer about Scheme would be more useful.  Ix27m just not that familiar with the differences.x3C/px3E',1,3,'ajan8','2008-08-13 15:06:12'),(9750,'How can I reverse the ON bits in a byte?','x3Cpx3EI was reading Joelx27s book where he was suggesting as interview question:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3EWrite a program to reverse the x22ONx22 bits in a given byte.x3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI only can think of a solution using C. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAsking here so you can show me how to do in a Non C way (if possible)x3C/px3E',1,11,'enewberryf','2008-08-13 17:00:48'),(10190,'How to return a page of results from SQL?','x3Cpx3EMany applications have grids that display data from a database table one page at a time. Many of them also let the user pick the number of records per page, sort by any column, and navigate back and forth through the results.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhatx27s a good algorithm to implement this pattern without bringing the entire table to the client and then filtering the data on the client. How do you bring just the records you want to display to the user?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDoes LINQ simplify the solution?x3C/px3E',1,3,'itrowla','2008-08-13 22:38:02'),(10230,'Checking for string contents? string Length Vs Empty String','x3Cpx3EWhich is more efficient for the compiler and the best practice for checking whether a string is blank? x3C/px3E\n\nx3Colx3E\nx3Clix3EChecking whether the length of the string == 0x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EChecking whether the string is empty (strVar == x22x22)x3C/lix3E\nx3C/olx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAlso, does the answer depend on language?x3C/px3E',1,6,'enewberryf','2008-08-13 23:03:27'),(10260,'What are the useful new ASP.NET features in the .NET Framework 3.5?','x3Cpx3EIx27ve kept up to date with new features in the C# language as itx27s moved from version 1 through version 3.  I havenx27t done such a good job keeping up to date with ASP.NET.  I feel like some of the post version 1 features are not so good (e.g. the AJAX framework) or are just not that useful to me (e.g. the membership framework).  Can anyone recommend any new killer ASP.NET features that might have gone unnoticed?x3C/px3E',1,1,'rtomeo0','2008-08-13 23:18:07'),(10300,'Validating posted form data in the ASP.NET MVC framework','x3Cpx3EIx27ve been playing around with the ASP.NET MVC Framework and the one thing thatx27s really confusing me is how Ix27m meant to do server side validation of posted form data.  I presume I donx27t post back to the same URL, but if I donx27t, how do I redisplay the form with the entered data and error messages?  Also, where should the validation logic go?  In the model or the controller?  This seems to be one of the few areas where web forms are much stronger (I miss the validation controls).x3C/px3E',1,9,'msmallpeacex','2008-08-13 23:45:33'),(10580,'What is the difference between Early and Late Binding?','x3Cpx3EWhat is the difference between early and late binding?x3C/px3E',1,9,'cscarbarrowm','2008-08-14 06:10:53'),(10600,'Whatx27s the best database storage device?','x3Cpx3ESo, the answer should probably be presented in tiers for the size of the application, but Ix27m wondering about peoplex27s experience with choosing where the disk drives used by the database should reside.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHere are some of the options:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3EJBOD - (just a bunch of disks) Old fashioned internal disks - fast but not very expandablex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3ENAS - Slow but cheap and expandable, probably best for backupsx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EDAS - A decent compromise, but generally accessible from only one or two machinesx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3ESAN - Expensive but very goodx3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow much should you worry about choosing a 15k drive over a 10k or 7200RPM?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhatx27s your favorite RAID level?x3C/px3E',1,6,'rmaccurlyer','2008-08-14 06:52:28'),(10610,'Pre-built regular expression patterns or Regex Libraries?','x3Cpx3EDoes anyone use have a good regex library that they like to use? Most of the regexes that you find online either contain bugs or are so focused on the edge cases that it turns into a competition to validate whatever spec 100%. Of course you can write your own, but when you are billing by the hour its handy to have a library around. x3C/px3E',1,11,'sfitzhenryv','2008-08-14 07:04:16'),(10670,'Asynchronous Remoting calls','x3Cpx3EWe have a remoting singleton server running in a separate windows service (letx27s call her RemotingService). The clients of the RemotingService are ASP.NET instances (many many).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECurrently, the clients remoting call RemotingService and blocks while the RemotingService call is serviced. However, the remoting service is getting complicated enough (with more RPC calls and complex algorithms) that the asp.net worker threads are blocked for a significantly long time (4-5 seconds).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAccording to x3Ca href=x22http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/magazine/cc164128.aspxx22x3Ethis msdn articlex3C/ax3E, doing this will not scale well because an asp.net worker thread is blocked for each remoting RPC. It advises switching to async handlers to free up asp.net worker threads.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3EThe purpose of an asynchronous handler\n  is to free up an ASP.NET thread pool\n  thread to service additional requests\n  while the handler is processing the\n  original request.x3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis seems fine, except the remoting call still takes up a thread from the thread pool.\nIs this the same thread pool as the asp.net worker threads? x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EHow should I go about turning my remoting singleton server into an async system such that I free up my asp.net worker threads?x3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve probably missed out some important information, please let me know if there is anything else you need to know to answer the question.x3C/px3E',1,3,'cscarbarrowm','2008-08-14 08:35:16'),(10680,'Is there a difference between the on_exit() and atexit() functions?','x3Cpx3EIs there any difference betweenx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E   int on_exit(void (*function)(int , void *), void *arg);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Eandx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E   int atexit(void (*function)(void));\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Eother than the fact that the function used by on_exit gets the exit status?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThat is, if I donx27t care about the exit status, is there any reason to use one or the other?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EEdit:x3C/strongx3E Many of the answers warned against x3Ccodex3Eon_exitx3C/codex3E because itx27s non-standard. If Ix27m developing an app that is for internal corporate use and guaranteed to run on specific configurations, should I worry about this? x3C/px3E',1,11,'rmaccurlyer','2008-08-14 08:53:45'),(10810,'Why do I get the error x22Unable to update the passwordx22 when calling AzMan?','x3Cpx3EIx27m doing a authorization check from a WinForms application with the help of the AzMan authorization provider from Enterprise Library and am receiving the the following error:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3EUnable to update the password. The value provided as the current password is incorrect. (Exception from HRESULT: 0x8007052B) (Microsoft.Practices.EnterpriseLibrary.Security.AzMan) x3C/px3E\n  \n  x3Chrx3E\n  \n  x3Cpx3EUnable to update the password. The value provided as the current password is incorrect. (Exception from HRESULT: 0x8007052B) (Microsoft.Interop.Security.AzRoles) x3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe AzMan store is hosted in ADAM on another computer in the same domain. Other computers and users do not have this problem. The user making the call has read access to both ADAM and the AzMan store. The computer running the WinForms app and the computer running ADAM are both on Windows XP SP2.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve had access problems with AzMan before that Ix27ve resolved, but this is a new one... What am I missing?x3C/px3E',1,2,'rmaccurlyer','2008-08-14 12:38:24'),(10860,'Data Layer Best Practices','x3Cpx3EI am in the middle of a x22discussionx22 with a colleague about the best way to implement the data layer in a new application.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EOne viewpoint is that the data layer should be aware of business objects (our own classes that represent an entity), and be able to work with that object natively.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe opposing viewpoint is that the data layer should be object-agnostic, and purely handle simple data types (strings, bools, dates, etc.)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI can see that both approaches may be valid, but my own viewpoint is that I prefer the former.  That way, if the data storage medium changes, the business layer doesnx27t (necessarily) have to change to accommodate the new data layer.  It would therefore be a trivial thing to change from a SQL data store to a serialized xml filesystem store.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy colleaguex27s point of view is that the data layer shouldnx27t have to know about object definitions, and that as long as the data is passed about appropriately, that is enough.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENow, I know that this is one of those questions that has the potential to start a religious war, but Ix27d appreciate any feedback from the community on how you approach such things.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ETIAx3C/px3E',1,3,'sdally1','2008-08-14 14:23:05'),(10870,'How can I x22unacceptx22 a drag in Flex?','x3Cpx3EOnce Ix27ve called x3Ccodex3EDragManager.acceptDragx3C/codex3E is there any way to x22unacceptx22 the drag? Say that I have a view which can accept drag and drop, but only in certain areas. Once the user drags over one of these areas I call x3Ccodex3EDragManager.acceptDrag(this)x3C/codex3E (from a x3Ccodex3EDragEvent.DRAG_OVERx3C/codex3E handler), but if the user then moves out of this area Ix27d like to change the status of the drag to not accepted and show the x3Ccodex3EDragManager.NONEx3C/codex3E feedback. However, neither calling x3Ccodex3EDragManager.acceptDrag(null)x3C/codex3E nor x3Ccodex3EDragManager.showFeedback(DragManager.NONE)x3C/codex3E seems to have any effect. Once Ix27ve accepted the drag an set the feedback type I canx27t seem to change it.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EJust to make it clear: the areas where the user should be able to drop are not components or even display objects, in fact they are just ranges in the text of a text field (like the selection). Had they been components of their own I could have solved it by making each of them accept drag events individually. I guess I could create proxy components that float over the text to emulate it, but Ix27d rather not if it isnx27t necessary.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve managed to get it working in both AIR and the browser now, but only by putting proxy components on top of the ranges of text where you should be able to drop things. That way I get the right feedback and drops are automatically unaccepted on drag exit.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis is the oddest thing about Dx26amp;D in AIR:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EDragManager.doDrag(initiator, source, event, dragImage, offsetX, offsetY);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn browser-based Flex, x3Ccodex3EoffsetXx3C/codex3E and x3Ccodex3EoffsetYx3C/codex3E should be negative (so says the documentation, and it works fine). However, when running x3Cemx3Eexactly the same codex3C/emx3E in AIR you have to make the offsets positive. The same numbers, but positive. That is very, very weird.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve tested some more and what x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/10870/how-can-i-unaccept-a-drag-in-flex#11209x22x3E@maclemax3C/ax3E works, but not if you run in AIR. It seems like drag and drop in AIR is different. Itx27s really, really weird because not only is the feedback not showing correctly, and itx27s not possible to unaccept, but the coordinates are also completely off. I just tried my application in a browser instead of AIR and dragging and dropping is completely broken.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAlso, skipping the x3Ccodex3EdragEnterx3C/codex3E handler works fine in AIR, but breaks everything when running in a browser.x3C/px3E',1,6,'kgrenkovu','2008-08-14 14:32:52'),(10880,'Any good advice on using emacs for C++ project?','x3Cpx3EIx27m looking for a good article on using emacs as C/C++ IDE.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESomething like Steve Yeggex27s x3Ca href=x22http://steve.yegge.googlepages.com/effective-emacsx22x3Ex22Effective emacsx22x3C/ax3E.x3C/px3E',1,9,'awrefford16','2008-08-14 14:42:59'),(10980,'IKVM and Licensing','x3Cpx3EI have been looking into IKVMing Apachex27s FOP project to use with our .NET app.  Itx27s a commercial product, and looking into licensing, IKVM runs into some sticky areas because of its use of GNU Classpath.  From what Ix27ve seen, no one can say for sure if this stuff can be used in a commercial product.  Has anyone used IKVM, or an IKVMx27d product, in a commercial product?  Herex27s what Ix27ve found so far:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://weblog.ikvm.net/story.aspx/licensex22 rel=x22nofollowx22 title=x22Config Section Generatorx22x3EIKVM license pagex3C/ax3E, which notes that one dll contains code from other projects, their license x3Ca href=x22http://openjdk.java.net/legal/gplv2+ce.htmlx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EGPLv2 + Classpath Exceptionx3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://saxon.sourceforge.net/x22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3ESaxon for .NETx3C/ax3E is generated with IKVM, but released under the Apache license...x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnyone have experience with this?x3C/px3E',1,7,'eburnyaten','2008-08-14 17:16:37'),(10990,'What are the proper permissions for an upload folder with PHP/Apache?','x3Cpx3ESorry for the basic question - Ix27m a .NET developer and donx27t have much experience with LAMP setups.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have a PHP site that will allow uploads to a specific folder. I have been told that this folder needs to be owned by the webserver user for the upload process to work, so I created the folder and then set permissions as such:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Echown apache:apache -R uploads/\nchmod 755 -R uploads/\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe only problem now is that the FTP user can not modify the uploaded files at all.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there a permission setting that will allow me to still upload files and then modify them later as a user other than the webserver user?x3C/px3E',1,10,'hbuxcy1c','2008-08-14 17:22:25'),(11060,'How should I unit test a code-generator?','x3Cpx3EThis is a difficult and open-ended question I know, but I thought Ix27d throw it to the floor and see if anyone had any interesting suggestions.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have developed a code-generator that takes our python interface to our C++ code (generated via SWIG) and generates code needed to expose this as WebServices.  When I developed this code I did it using TDD, but Ix27ve found my tests to be brittle as hell.  Because each test essentially wanted to verify that for a given bit of input code (which happens to be a C++ header) Ix27d get a given bit of outputted code I wrote a small engine that reads test definitions from XML input files and generates test cases from these expectations.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe problem is I dread going in to modify the code at all.  That and the fact that the unit tests themselves are a: complex, and b: brittle.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo Ix27m trying to think of alternative approaches to this problem, and it strikes me Ix27m perhaps tackling it the wrong way.  Maybe I need to focus more on the outcome, IE: does the code I generate actually run and do what I want it to, rather than, does the code look the way I want it to.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHas anyone got any experiences of something similar to this they would care to share?x3C/px3E',1,6,'civakhnop','2008-08-14 17:59:21'),(11200,'T-Sql date format for seconds since last epoch / formatting for sqlite input','x3Cpx3EIx27m guessing it needs to be something like:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3ECONVERT(CHAR(24), lastModified, 101)\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHowever Ix27m not sure of the right value for the third parameter.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThanks!x3C/px3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWell Ix27m trying to write a script to copy my sql server db to a sqlite file, which gets downloaded to an air app, which then syncs the data to another sqlite file. Ix27m having a ton of trouble with dates. If I select a date in air and try to insert it, it fails because itx27s not in the right format... even if it was a valid date to begin with. I figured Ix27d try to experiment with the unix time since thatx27s the only thing thats worked so far. I am considering just leaving them as varchar because I donx27t sort by them anyway.x3C/px3E',1,9,'sdally1','2008-08-14 19:26:11'),(11330,'Passing more parameters in C function pointers','x3Cpx3ELetx27s say Ix27m creating a chess program. I have a functionx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Evoid foreachMove( void (*action)(chess_move*), chess_game* game);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ewhich will call the function pointer action on each valid move. This is all well and good, but what if I need to pass more parameters to the action function? For example:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Echess_move getNextMove(chess_game* game, int depth){\n  //for each valid move, determine how good the move is\n  foreachMove(moveHandler, game);\n}\n\nvoid moveHandler(chess_move* move){\n  //uh oh, now I need the variables x22gamex22 and x22depthx22 from the above function\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ERedefining the function pointer is not the optimal solution. The foreachMove function is versatile and many different places in the code reference it. It doesnx27t make sense for each one of those references to have to update their function to include parameters that they donx27t need.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow can I pass extra parameters to a function that Ix27m calling through a pointer?x3C/px3E',1,10,'mbeckinsale1a','2008-08-14 20:51:07'),(11430,'What version of .Net framework ships with SQL Server 2008?','x3Cpx3EDoes SQL Server 2008 ship with the .NET 3.5 CLR, so that stored procedures written in CLR can use 3.5 features?x3C/px3E',1,3,'osilley7','2008-08-14 22:08:00'),(11460,'ASP.NET Proxy Application','x3Cpx3ELet me try to explain what I need. I have a server that is visible from the internet. What I need is to create a ASP.NET application that get the request of a web Site and send to a internal server, then it gets the response and publish the the info. For the client this should be totally transparent.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EFor different reasons I cannot redirect the port to the internal server. What I can do but no know how - maybe the answer is there - is to create a new Web Site that its host in the other server.x3C/px3E',1,2,'awrefford16','2008-08-14 22:28:42'),(11500,'Speeding up an ASP.Net Web Site or Application','x3Cpx3EI have an Ajax.Net enabled ASP.Net 2.0 web site. Hosting for both the site and the database are out of my control as is the databasex27s schema. In testing on hardware I do control the site performs well however on the clientx27s hardware, there are noticeable delays when reloading or changing pages. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat I would like to do is make my application as compact and speedy as possible when I deliver it. One idea is to set expiration dates for all of the sitex27s static resources so they arenx27t recalled on page loads. By resources I mean images, linked style sheets and JavaScript source files. Is there an easy way to do this?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat other ways are there to optimize a .Net web site?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EUPDATE: \nIx27ve run YSlow on the site and the areas where I am getting hit the hardest are in the number of JavaScript and Style Sheets being loaded (23 JS files and 5 style sheets). All but one (the main style sheet) has been inserted by Ajax.net and Asp. Why so many? x3C/px3E',1,9,'mheyward10','2008-08-14 22:52:54'),(11520,'What are the list of Resharper like plugins for VS I should consider?','x3Cpx3EMy license for Whole Tomatoes Visual AssistX is about to expire and Ix27m not really planning on renewing it.  I use it for spell checking but thatx27s about it.  The refactoring abilities have been a little disappointing.  Before I just jump into Resharper though what are your thoughts on other possible plugins?x3C/px3E',1,3,'sspindlerw','2008-08-14 23:03:53'),(11620,'How do you kill all current connections to a SQL Server 2005 database?','x3Cpx3EI want to rename a database, but keep getting the error that x27couldnx27t get exclusive lockx27 on the database, which implies there is some connection(s) still active.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow can I kill all the connections to the database so that I can rename it?x3C/px3E',1,7,'hginglell13','2008-08-14 23:54:25'),(11680,'Design pattern for parsing binary file data and storing in a database','x3Cpx3EDoes anybody recommend a design pattern for taking a binary data file, parsing parts of it into objects and storing the resultant data into a database?  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI think a similar pattern could be used for taking an XML or tab-delimited file and parse it into their representative objects.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EA common data structure would include:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3E(Header) (DataElement1) (DataElement1SubData1) (DataElement1SubData2)(DataElement2) (DataElement2SubData1) (DataElement2SubData2) (EOF)x3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI think a good design would include a way to change out the parsing definition based on the file type or some defined metadata included in the header.  So a x3Ca href=x22http://www.oodesign.com/factory-method-pattern.htmlx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EFactory Patternx3C/ax3E would be part of the overall design for the Parser part.x3C/px3E',1,3,'mschafflere','2008-08-15 00:36:07'),(11690,'How can I get Unicode characters to display properly for the tooltip for the IMG ALT in IE7?','x3Cpx3EIx27ve got some Japanese in the ALT attribute, but the tooltip is showing me the ugly block characters in the tooltip.  The rest of the content on the page renders correctly.  So far, it seems to be limited to the tooltips.x3C/px3E',1,9,'cleatham18','2008-08-15 00:50:31'),(11720,'How can I create virtual machines as part of a build process using MSBuild and MS Virtual Server and/or Hyper-V Server Virtualization?','x3Cpx3EWhat I would like to do is create a clean virtual machine image as the output of a build of an application.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo a new virtual machine would be created (from a template is fine, with the OS installed, and some base software installed) --- a new web site would be created in IIS, and the web app build output copied to a location on the virtual machine hard disk, and IIS configured correctly, the VM would start up and run.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI know there are MSBuild tasks to script all the administrative actions in IIS, but how do you script all the actions with Virtual machines?  Specifically, creating a new virtual machine from a template, naming it uniquely, starting it, configuring it, etc...x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESpecifically I was wondering if anyone has successfully implemented any VM scripting as part of a build process.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EUpdate: I assume with Hyper-V, there is a different set of libraries/APIs to script virtual machines, anyone played around with this?  And anyone with real practical experience of doing something like this?x3C/px3E',1,11,'tvallentint','2008-08-15 01:32:34'),(11740,'Configurable Table Prefixes with a .Net OR/M?','x3Cpx3EIn a web application like wiki or forums or blogging software, it is often useful to store your data in a relational database. Since many hosting companies offer a single database with their hosting plans (with additional databases costing extra) it is very useful for your users when your database objects (tables, views, constraints, and stored procedures) have a common prefix. It is typical for applications aware of database scarcity to have a hard-coded table prefix. I want more, however. Specifically, Ix27d like to have a table prefix that users can designatex26mdash;say in the web.config file (with an appropriate default, of course).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESince I hate coding x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Create%2C_read%2C_update_and_deletex22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3ECRUDx3C/ax3E operations by hand, I prefer to work through a competent OR/M and have used (and enjoyed) LINQ to SQL, Subsonic, and ADO.Net. Ix27m having some thrash in a new project, however, when it comes to putting a table prefix in a userx27s web.config file. Are there any .Net-based OR/M products that can handle this scenario elegantly?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe best I have been able to come up with so far is using LINQ to SQL with an external mapping file that Ix27d have to update somehow based on an as-yet hypothetical web.config setting.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnyone have a better solution? I tried to make it happen in Entity Framework, but that turned into a mess quickly. (Due to my unfamiliarity with EF? Possibly.) How about SubSonic? Does it have an option to apply a table prefix besides at code generation time?x3C/px3E',1,4,'fbrizellc','2008-08-15 02:32:58'),(11820,'How much extra overhead is generated when sending a file over a web service as a byte array?','x3Cpx3EThis x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/11782/file-uploads-via-web-servicesx22 rel=x22nofollowx22 title=x22excanvasx22x3Equestion and answerx3C/ax3E shows how to send a file as a byte array through an XML web service. How much overhead is generated by using this method for file transfer?  I assume the data looks something like this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ex26lt;?xml version=x221.0x22 encoding=x22UTF-8x22 ?x26gt;\nx26lt;bytesx26gt;\n    x26lt;bytex26gt;16x26lt;/bytex26gt;\n    x26lt;bytex26gt;28x26lt;/bytex26gt;\n    x26lt;bytex26gt;127x26lt;/bytex26gt;\n    ...\nx26lt;/bytesx26gt;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIf this format is correct, the bytes must first be converted to UTF-8 characters. Each of these characters allocates 8 bytes. Are the bytes stored in base 10, hex, or binary characters? How much larger does the file appear as it is being sent due to the XML data and character encoding? Is compression built into web services?x3C/px3E',1,11,'srm4902','2008-08-15 04:29:57'),(11930,'How can I determine the IP of my router/gateway in Java?','x3Cpx3EHow can I determine the IP of my router/gateway in Java? I can get my IP easily enough. I can get my internet IP using a service on a website. But how can I determine my gatewayx27s IP?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis is somewhat easy in .NET if you know your way around. But how do you do it in Java?x3C/px3E',1,8,'prihak','2008-08-15 07:32:28'),(11950,'How do you log errors (Exceptions) in your ASP.NET apps?','x3Cpx3EIx27m looking for the best way to log errors in an ASP.NET application.\nI want to be able to receive emails when errors occurs in my application, with detailed information about the Exception and the current Request.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn my company we used to have our own ErrorMailer, catching everything in the Global.asax Application_Error. It was x22Okx22 but not very flexible nor configurable.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWe swithed recently to NLog. Itx27s much more configurable, we can define different targets for the errors, filter them, buffer them (not tried yet). Itx27s a very good improvement.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBut I discovered lately that therex27s a whole Namespace in the .Net framework for this purpose : x3Ca href=x22http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/system.web.management.aspxx22x3ESystem.Web.Managementx3C/ax3E and it can be configured in the x3Ca href=x22http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/2fwh2ss9(VS.80).aspxx22x3EhealthMonitoringx3C/ax3E section of web.config.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHave you ever worked with .Net health monitoring? What is your solution for error logging?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThanks,x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EVincentx3C/px3E',1,6,'prihak','2008-08-15 08:05:10'),(12140,'Access to global application settings','x3Cpx3EA database application that Ix27m currently working on, stores all sorts of settings in the database. Most of those settings are there to customize certain business rules, but therex27s also some other stuff in there.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe app contains objects that specifically do a certain task, e.g., a certain complicated calculation. Those non-UI objects are unit-tested, but also need access to lots of those global settings. The way wex27ve implemented this right now, is by giving the objects properties that are filled by the Application Controller at runtime. When testing, we create the objects in the test and fill in values for testing (not from the database).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis works better, in any case much better than having all those objects need some global x3Cemx3ESettingsx3C/emx3E object --- that of course effectively makes unit testing impossible :) Disadvantage can be that you sometimes need to set a dozen of properties, or that you need to let those properties x27percolatex27 into sub-objects.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3ESo the general question isx3C/strongx3E: how do you provide access to global application settings in your projects, without the need for global variables, while still being able to unit test your code? This must be a problem thatx27s been solved 100x27s of times...x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3E(Note: Ix27m not too much of an experienced programmer, as youx27ll have noticed; but I love to learn! And of course, Ix27ve already done research into this topic, but Ix27m really looking for some first-hand experiences)x3C/px3E',1,9,'nivakhnov17','2008-08-15 15:12:35'),(12290,'Considering N2 CMS but worried about performance. Is this justified?','x3Cpx3EHy, does anyone worked with N2 Content Management System(x3Ca href=x22http://www.codeplex.com/n2x22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Ehttp://www.codeplex.com/n2x3C/ax3E).\nIf yes, how does it perform, performance wise(under heavy load)?\nIt seems pretty simple and easy to use.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAdrianx3C/px3E',1,3,'kgrenkovu','2008-08-15 18:29:20'),(12330,'Programmatically list WMI classes and their properties','x3Cpx3EHey everyone, \nIs there any known way of listing the WMI classes and their properties available for a particular system? Im interested in a vbscript approach, but please suggest anything really :)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EP.S. Great site.x3C/px3E',1,7,'sfitzhenryv','2008-08-15 19:06:31'),(12720,'Add .NET 2.0 SP1 as a prerequisite for deployment project','x3Cpx3EI have a .NET 2.0 application that has recently had contributions that are Service Pack 1 dependent.  The deployment project has detected .NET 2.0 as a prerequisite, but NOT SP1.  How do I include SP1 as a dependency/prerequisite in my deployment project?x3C/px3E',1,2,'dsizland14','2008-08-16 00:42:51'),(12870,'Arrays of Arrays in Java','x3Cpx3EThis is a nasty one for me...  Ix27m a PHP guy working in Java on a JSP project.  I know how to do what Ix27m attempting through too much code and a complete lack of finesse.   Ix27d prefer to do it RIGHT. :) Here is the situation:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m writing a small display to show customers what days they can water their lawns based on their watering group (ABCDE) and what time of year it is.  Our seasons look like this:\nSummer (5-1 to 8-31) \nSpring  (3-1 to 4-30) \nFall (9-1 to 10-31)\nWinter (11-1 to 2-28) x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAn example might be:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIf Ix27m in group A, here would be my allowed times:\nWinter: Mondays only\nSpring: Tues, Thurs, Sat\nSummer: Any Day\nFall: Tues, Thurs, Satx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIf I was writing this in PHP I would use arrays like this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E//M=Monday,t=Tuesday,T=Thursday.... etc\n$schedule[x22Ax22][x22Winterx22]=x27Mx27;\n$schedule[x22Ax22][x22Springx22]=x27tTSx27;\n$schedule[x22Ax22][x22Summerx22]=x27Anyx27;\n$schedule[x22Ax22][x22Fallx22]=x27tTSx27;\n$schedule[x22Bx22][x22Winterx22]=x27tx27;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI COULD make the days arrays (array(x22Tuesdayx22,x22Thursdayx22,x22Saturdayx22)) etc, but it is not necessary for what Ix27m really trying to accomplish.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI will also need to setup arrays to determine what season Ix27m in:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E$seasons[x22Summerx22][x22startx22]=0501;\n$seasons[x22Summerx22][x22endx22]=0801;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECan anyone suggest a really cool way to do this? I will have todayx27s date and the group letter.  I will need to get out of my function a day (M) or a series of days (tTS), (Any).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThanks, folks!x3C/px3E',1,7,'sdally1','2008-08-16 03:07:03'),(12880,'Large Data Sets','x3Cpx3EIx27m always looking for large data sets to test various types of programs on. Does anyone have any suggestions?x3C/px3E',1,1,'chenburyh','2008-08-16 03:22:54'),(12890,'What is a good way to denormalize a mysql database?','x3Cpx3EI have a large database of normalized order data that is becoming very slow to query for reporting.  Many of the queries that I use in reports join five or six tables and are having to examine tens or hundreds of thousands of lines.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThere are lots of queries and most have been optimized as much as possible to reduce server load and increase speed.  I think itx27s time to start keeping a copy of the data in a denormalized format.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny ideas on an approach?  Should I start with a couple of my worst queries and go from there?x3C/px3E',1,11,'sfitzhenryv','2008-08-16 03:36:30'),(13000,'How to setup site-wide variables in php?','x3Cpx3EI want to define something like this in x3Cemx3Ephpx3C/emx3E:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E$EL = x22\\nx26lt;br /x26gt;\\nx22;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Eand then use that variable as an x22endlinex22 marker all over my site, like this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eecho x22Blah blah blah{$EL}x22;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow do I define $EL once (in only 1 file), include it on every page on my site, and x3Cemx3Enotx3C/emx3E have to reference it using the (strangely backwards) x3Ccodex3Eglobal $EL;x3C/codex3E statement in every page function?x3C/px3E',1,10,'tvallentint','2008-08-16 09:05:09'),(13060,'What do ref, val and out mean on method parameters?','x3Cpx3EIx27m looking for a clear, concise and accurate answer.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIdeally as the actual answer, although links to good explanations welcome.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis also applies to VB.Net, but the keywords are different - x3Ccodex3EByRefx3C/codex3E and x3Ccodex3EByValx3C/codex3E.x3C/px3E',1,8,'srm4902','2008-08-16 12:46:16'),(13160,'Best practice for webservices','x3Cpx3EIx27ve created a webservice and when I want to use its methods I instantiate it in the a procedure, call the method, and I finally I dispose it, however I think also it could be okay to instantiate the webservice in the x22private void Main_Load(object sender, EventArgs e)x22 event.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe thing is that if I do it the first way I have to instantiate the webservice every time I need one of its methods but in the other way I have to keep a webservice connected all the time when I use it in a form for example. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI would like to know which of these practices are better or if therex27s a much better way to do itx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EStrategy 1x3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eprivate void btnRead_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)\n{\n    try\n    {\n        //Show clock\n        this.picResult.Image = new Bitmap(pathWait);\n\n        Application.DoEvents();\n\n        //Connect to webservice\n        svc = new ForPocketPC.ServiceForPocketPC();\n        svc.Credentials = new System.Net.NetworkCredential(Settings.UserName, Settings.Password);\n        svc.AllowAutoRedirect = false;\n        svc.UserAgent = Settings.UserAgent;\n        svc.PreAuthenticate = true;\n        svc.Url = Settings.Url;\n        svc.Timeout = System.Threading.Timeout.Infinite;\n\n        svc.CallMethod();\n         ...\n    }\n    catch (Exception ex)\n    {\n        ShowError(ex);\n    }\n    finally\n    {\n        if (svc != null)\n            svc.Dispose();\n    }\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EStrategy 2x3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eprivate myWebservice svc;\n\nprivate void Main_Load(object sender, EventArgs e)\n{\n    //Connect to webservice\n    svc = new ForPocketPC.ServiceForPocketPC();\n    svc.Credentials = new System.Net.NetworkCredential(Settings.UserName, Settings.Password);\n    svc.AllowAutoRedirect = false;\n    svc.UserAgent = Settings.UserAgent;\n    svc.PreAuthenticate = true;\n    svc.Url = Settings.Url;\n    svc.Timeout = System.Threading.Timeout.Infinite;\n}\n\nprivate void btnRead_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)\n{\n    try\n    {\n        //Show clock\n        this.picResult.Image = new Bitmap(pathWait);\n\n        Application.DoEvents();\n        svc.CallMethod();\n         ...\n    }\n    catch (Exception ex)\n    {\n        ShowError(ex);\n    }\n}\n\nprivate void Main_Closing(object sender, CancelEventArgs e)\n{\n    svc.Dispose();\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E',1,2,'clawrence3','2008-08-16 18:58:30'),(13170,'A ThreadStateException occures when trying to restart a thread','x3Cpx3EFrom time to time I get a System.Threading.ThreadStateException when attempting to restart a thread. The code in question is as follows:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E// Make sure the thread is done stopping\nwhile (this.mThread.ThreadState == ThreadState.Running)\n{ \n    Thread.Sleep(0);\n}\n// Respawn a thread if the current one is stopped or doesnx27t exist\nif (this.mThread == null || this.mThread.ThreadState == ThreadState.Stopped)\n{ \n    this.mThread = new Thread(new ParameterizedThreadStart(Monitor)); }\n// Start the thread\nif (check)\n{ \n    this.mThread.Start(60000); \n}\nelse\n{   \n    this.mThread.Start(0); \n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo two questions - is this the correct way of doing things, and  it is, is there a way to prevent the error from occurring?x3C/px3E',1,1,'scurraghy','2008-08-16 19:24:19'),(13200,'How do I integrate my continuous integration system with my bug tracking system?','x3Cpx3EI use cruisecontrol.rb for CI and FogBugz for bug tracking, but the more general the answers, the better.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EFirst is the technical problem: is there an API for FogBugz?  Are there good tutorials, or better yet, pre-written code?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESecond is the procedural problem: what, exactly, should the CI put in the bug tracker when the build breaks?  Perhaps:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ETitle: x22#{last committer} broke the build!x22x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBody: x22#{ error traces }x22x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI suppose this presupposes the answer to this question: should I even put CI breaks into my bug tracking?x3C/px3E',1,8,'achancelier6','2008-08-16 20:09:16'),(13430,'Does CruiseControl.NET run on IIS 7.0?','x3Cpx3EIx27m new to development (an admin by trade) and Ix27m setting up my development environment and I would like to set up a CruiseControl.Net server on Server 2008.  A quick Google did not turn up any instructions for getting it running on IIS 7.0, so I was wondering if anyone had experience getting this set up.x3C/px3E',1,11,'srm9547','2008-08-17 04:37:17'),(13460,'The theory (and terminology) behind Source Control','x3Cpx3EIx27ve tried using source control for a couple projects but still donx27t really understand it.  For these projects, wex27ve used TortoiseSVN and have only had one line of revisions.  (No trunk, branch, or any of that.)  If there is a recommended way to set up source control systems, what are they?  What are the reasons and benifits for setting it up that way?  What is the underlying differences between the workings of a centralized and distributed source control system?x3C/px3E',1,8,'mheyward10','2008-08-17 05:38:24'),(13470,'Purpose of {1} in this regular expression to match url protocols','x3Cpx3EI was reading x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/6173/regular-expression-for-parsing-links-from-a-webpagex22x3Ethis questionx3C/ax3E about how to parse URLs out of web pages and had a question about the x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/6173/regular-expression-for-parsing-links-from-a-webpage#6183x22x3Eaccepted answerx3C/ax3E which offered this solution:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpre class=x22lang-none prettyprint-overridex22x3Ex3Ccodex3E((mailto\\:|(news|(ht|f)tp(s?))\\://){1}\\S+)\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe solution was offered by x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/users/350/csmbax22x3Ecsmbax3C/ax3E and he credited it to x3Ca href=x22http://regexlib.com/Search.aspx?k=URLx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Eregexlib.comx3C/ax3E. Whew. Credits done.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI think this is a fairly naive regular expression but itx27s a fine starting point for building something better.  But, my question is this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat is the point of x3Ccodex3E{1}x3C/codex3E? It means x22exactly one of the previous groupingx22, right? Isnx27t that the default behavior of a grouping in a regular expression? Would the expression be changed in any way if the x3Ccodex3E{1}x3C/codex3E were removed?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIf I saw this from a coworker I would point out his or her error but as I write this the response is rated at a 6 and the expression on regexlib.com is rated a 4 of 5. So maybe Ix27m missing something?x3C/px3E',1,2,'srm9547','2008-08-17 06:01:56'),(13540,'Insert Update stored proc on SQL Server','x3Cpx3EIx27ve written a stored proc that will do an update if a record exists, otherwise it will do an insert. It looks something like this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eupdate myTable set Col1=@col1, Col2=@col2 where ID=@ID\nif @@rowcount = 0\ninsert into myTable (Col1, Col2) values (@col1, @col2)\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy logic behind writing it in this way is that the update will perform an implicit select using the where clause and if that returns 0 then the insert will take place.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe alternative to doing it this way would be to do a select and then based on the number of rows returned either do an update or insert. This I considered inefficient because if you are to do an update it will cause 2 selects (the first explicit select call and the second implicit in the where of the update). If the proc were to do an insert then therex27d be no difference in efficiency.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs my logic sound here?\nIs this how you would combine an insert and update into a stored proc?x3C/px3E',1,1,'ajan8','2008-08-17 10:48:50'),(13550,'CASE tools','x3Cpx3EI was using a CASE called x3Ca href=x22http://www.magicsoftware.com/x22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EMAGICx3C/ax3E for a system Ix27m developing, Ix27ve never used this kind of tool before and at first sight I liked, a month later I had a lot of the application generated, I felt very productive and ... I would say ... satisfied.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn some way a felt uncomfortable, cause, there is no code and everything I was used to, but in the other hand I could speed up my developing. The fact is that eventually I returned to use C# because I find it more flexible to develop, I can make unit testing, use CVS, I have access to more resources and basically I had x22all the controlx22. I felt that this tool didnx27t give me confidence and I thought that later in the project I could not manage it due to its forced established rules of development. And also a lot of things like sending emails, using my own controls, and other things had their complication, it seemed that at some point it was not going to be as easy as initially I thought and as initially the product claims. This reminds me a very nice article called x22x3Ca href=x22http://www.virtualschool.edu/mon/SoftwareEngineering/BrooksNoSilverBullet.htmlx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3ENo Silver Bulletx3C/ax3Ex22.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis CASE had its advantages but on the other hand it doesnx27t have resources you can consult and actually the license and certification are very expensive. For me another dissapointing thing is that because of its simplistic approach for development I felt scared on first hand cause of my unexperience on these kind of tools and second cause I thought that if I continued using it maybe it would have turned to be a complex monster that I could not manage later in the project.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI think its good to use these kind of solutions to speed up things but I wonder, why arenx27t these programs as popular as VS.Net, J2EE, Ruby, Python, etc. if they claim to enhace productivity better than the tools Ix27ve pointed?x3C/px3E',1,3,'cscarbarrowm','2008-08-17 11:08:41'),(13620,'Speed difference in using inline strings vs concatenation in php5?','x3Cpx3E(assume php5) considerx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ex26lt;?php\n\n    $foo = x27some wordsx27;\n\n    //case 1\n    print x22these are $foox22;\n\n    //case 2\n    print x22these are {$foo}x22;\n\n    //case 3\n    print x27these are x27 . $foo;\n?x26gt;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there much of a difference between 1 and 2?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIf not, what about between 1/2 and 3?x3C/px3E',1,9,'dperrenl','2008-08-17 17:19:32'),(14040,'Developer testing vs. QA team testing - What is the right division of work?','x3Cpx3EWhile trying to advocate more developer testing, I find the argument x22Isnx27t that QAx27s job?x22 is used a lot.  In my mind, it doesnx27t make sense to give the QA team all testing responsibilities, but at the same time Spolsky and others say you shouldnx27t be using the $100/hr developers to do something a $30/hr tester could be doing.  What are the experiences of others in a company with a dedicated QA team?  Where should the division of work be drawn?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EClarification: I meant QA as a validation and verification team. Devs should not be doing the validation (customer-focused testing), but where is the verification (functional testing) division point?x3C/px3E',1,9,'erowcliffe1d','2008-08-18 04:19:05'),(14300,'How do I make Powershell run a batch file and then stay open?','x3Cpx3EFor example; with the old command prompt it would be:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ecmd.exe /k mybatchfile.bat\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E',1,1,'awrefford16','2008-08-18 12:00:15'),(14310,'Using OpenGL textures larger than window/display size','x3Cpx3EIx27m having problems using textures that are larger than the OpenGL window or the display size as non-display render targets.x3Cbrx3E\nWhatx27s the solution for this problem?x3C/px3E',1,5,'eburnyaten','2008-08-18 12:09:10'),(14330,'RGB to monochrome conversion','x3Cpx3EHow do I convert the RGB values of a pixel to a single monochrome value?x3C/px3E',1,6,'aillidges','2008-08-18 12:27:32'),(14350,'How do I call a Flex SWF from a remote domain using Flash (AS3)?','x3Cpx3EI have a Flex swf hosted at x3Ca href=x22http://www.a.com/a.swfx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Ehttp://www.a.com/a.swfx3C/ax3E.\nI have a flash code on another doamin that tries loading the SWF:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E_loader = new Loader();\nvar req:URLRequest = new URLRequest(x22http://services.nuconomy.com/n.swfx22);\n_loader.contentLoaderInfo.addEventListener(Event.COMPLETE,onLoaderFinish);\n_loader.load(req);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/pre