etter, LINQ-to-SQL or stored procs? Any specific prox27s or conx27s?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThanks.x3C/px3E',1,5,'wscreen1b','2008-08-18 16:37:57'),(14570,'How to organize dataset queries to improve performance','x3Cpx3EI donx27t know when to add to a dataset a tableadapter or a query from toolbox. Does it make any difference?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI also dont know where to create instances of the adapters. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3EShould I do it in the x3Ccodex3EPage_Loadx3C/codex3E? x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EShould I just do it when Ix27m going to use it?  x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EAm I opening a new connection when I create a new instance?x3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis doesnx27t seem very important, but every time I create a query a little voice on my brain asks me these questions.x3C/px3E',1,6,'erowcliffe1d','2008-08-18 17:21:45'),(14760,'Is it possible to disable command input in the toolbar search box?','x3Cpx3EIn the Visual Studio toolbar, you can enter commands into the search box by prefixing them with a x3E symbol. Is there any way to disable this? Ix27ve never used the feature, and itx27s slightly annoying when trying to actually search for something that you know is prefixed by greater-than in the code. Itx27s particularly annoying when you accidentally search for x22x3E exitx22 and the IDE quits (I knew there was a line in the code that was something like x3Ccodex3Eif(counter x26gt; exitCount)x3C/codex3E so entered that search without thinking).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAt the very least, can you escape the x3E symbol so that you can search for it? Prefixing with ^ doesnx27t seem to work.x3C/px3E',1,11,'kgrenkovu','2008-08-18 19:04:25'),(14770,'How best to use File Version and Assembly Version?','x3Cpx3EIn .NET there are two version numbers available when building a project, File Version and Assembly Version. How are you using these numbers?  Keeping them the same?  Auto-incrementing one, but manually changing the other?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAlso what about the x3Ccodex3EAssemblyInformationalVersionx3C/codex3E attribute?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27d found this support Microsoft Knowledge Base (KB) article that provided some help:  x3Ca href=x22http://support.microsoft.com/kb/556041x22x3EHow to use Assembly Version and Assembly File Versionx3C/ax3E.x3C/px3E',1,10,'eburnyaten','2008-08-18 19:10:12'),(15040,'How do you set your LAMP testing server?','x3Cpx3EI am using xampp on Windows, but I would like to use something closer to my server setup.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://phpimpact.wordpress.com/2008/05/24/virtual-appliances-lamp-development-made-easy/x22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EFederico Cargnelutti tutorialx3C/ax3E explains how to setup LAMP VMWARE appliance; it is a great introduction to VMware appliances, but one of the commands was not working and it doesnx27t describe how to change the keyboard layout and the timezone.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Eps: the commands are easy to find but I donx27t want to look for them each time I reinstall the server. I am using this question as a reminder.x3C/px3E',1,4,'cleatham18','2008-08-18 22:26:53'),(15190,'Changing CURRENT save/default directory in Delphi 2007 without using Save-As','x3Cpx3EI have a project group that contains a project Ix27m working on as well as some related component and packages. I prefer to keep the database links active during design-time. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI know how to write the code which would change the database file location, but in this case, Ix27m just using x3Ccodex3Ex22.\\datax22x3C/codex3E instead, for various design-time reasons. Unfortunately, using a relative folder means that Delphi needs to be x22pointingx22 to the same folder that the project is in.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27d like to be able to force the folder location to a different root, without using the x22Save Asx22 feature. Does anyone happen to know where the Delphi IDE retrieves that info?x3C/px3E',1,6,'astarmoreq','2008-08-19 00:32:49'),(15240,'How do you create a debug only function that takes a variable argument list? Like printf()','x3Cpx3EIx27d like to make a debug logging function with the same parameters as x3Ccodex3Eprintfx3C/codex3E.  But one that can be removed by the pre-processor during optimized builds.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EFor example:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EDebug_Print(x22Warning: value %d x26gt; 3!\\nx22, value);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve looked at variadic macros but those arenx27t available on all platforms. x3Ccodex3Egccx3C/codex3E supports them, x3Ccodex3Emsvcx3C/codex3E does not.x3C/px3E',1,6,'enewberryf','2008-08-19 01:22:20'),(15310,'Optimizing the PDF Export of Huge Reports in Sql Reporting Services 2005','x3Cpx3EFirst off I understand that it is a horrible idea to run extremely large/long running reports. I am aware that Microsoft has a rule of thumb stating that a SSRS report should take no longer than 30 seconds to execute.  However sometimes gargantuan reports are a preferred evil due to external forces such complying with state laws.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAt my place of employment, we have an asp.net (2.0) app that we have migrated from Crystal Reports to SSRS. Due to the large user base and complex reporting UI requirements we have a set of screens that accepts user inputted parameters and creates schedules to be run over night. Since the application supports multiple reporting frameworks we do not use the scheduling/snapshot facilities of SSRS. All of the reports in the system are generated by a scheduled console app which takes user entered parameters and generates the reports with the corresponding reporting solutions the reports were created with. In the case of SSRS reports, the console app generates the SSRS reports and exports them as PDFs via the SSRS web service API. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo far SSRS has been much easier to deal with than Crystal with the exception of a certain 25,000 page report that we have recently converted from crystal reports to SSRS. The SSRS server is a 64bit 2003 server with 32 gigs of ram running SSRS 2005. All of our smaller reports work fantastically, but we are having trouble with our larger reports such as this one.  Unfortunately, we canx27t seem to generate the aforemention report through the web service API. The following error occurs roughly 30-35 minutes into the generation/export:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EException Message: The underlying connection was closed: An unexpected error occurred on a receive.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe web service call is something Ix27m sure you all have seen before:  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Edata = rs.Render(this.ReportPath, this.ExportFormat, null, deviceInfo,\n   selectedParameters, null, null, out encoding, out mimeType, out usedParameters, \n   out warnings, out streamIds);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe odd thing is that this report will run/render/export if the report is run directly on the reporting server using the report manager. The proc that produces the data for the report runs for about 5 minutes. The report renders in SSRS native format in the browser/viewer after about 12 minutes. Exporting to pdf through the browser/viewer in the report manager takes an additional 55 minutes. This works reliably and it produces a whopping 1.03gb pdf.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHere are some of the more obvious things Ix27ve tried to get the report working via the web service API:  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3Eset the HttpRuntime ExecutionTimeout\nvalue to 3 hours on the report\nserverx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Edisabled http keep alives on the report serverx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Eincreased the script timeout on the report serverx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Eset the report to never time out on the serverx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Eset the report timeout to several hours on the client call  x3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EFrom the tweaks I have tried, I am fairly comfortable saying that any timeout issues have been eliminated. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBased off of my research of the error message, I believe that the web service API does not send chunked responses by default. This means that it tries to send all 1.3gb over the wire in one response. At a certain point, IIS throws in the towel. Unfortunately the API abstracts away web service configuration so I canx27t seem to find a way to enable response chunking. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Colx3E\nx3Clix3EDoes anyone know of anyway to reduce/optimize the PDF export phase and or the size of the PDF without lowering the total page count?x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EIs there a way to turn on response chunking for SSRS?x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EDoes anyone else have any other theories as to why this runs on the server but not through the API?x3C/lix3E\nx3C/olx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEDIT: After reading kcrumleyx27s post I began to take a look at the average page size by taking file size / page count. Interestingly enough on smaller reports the math works out so that each page is roughly 5K. Interestingly, when the report gets larger this x22averagex22 increases. An 8000 page report for example is averaging over 40K/page. Very odd. I will also add that the number of records per page is set except for the last page in each grouping, so itx27s not a case where some pages have more records than another. x3C/px3E',1,2,'erowcliffe1d','2008-08-19 02:19:16'),(15390,'Best practices for managing and deploying large JavaScript apps','x3Cpx3EWhat are some standard practices for managing a medium-large JavaScript application? My concerns are both speed for browser download and ease and maintainability of development.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EOur JavaScript code is roughly x22namespacedx22 as:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Evar Client = {\n   var1: x27x27,\n   var2: x27x27,\n\n   accounts: {\n      /* 100x27s of functions and variables */\n   },\n\n   orders: {\n      /* 100x27s of functions and variables and subsections */\n   }\n\n   /* etc, etc  for a couple hundred kb */\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAt the moment, we have one (unpacked, unstripped, highly readable) JavaScript file to handle all the business logic on the web application. In addition, there is jQuery and several jQuery extensions. The problem we face is that it takes x3Cemx3Eforeverx3C/emx3E to find anything in the JavaScript code and the browser still has a dozen files to download.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs it common to have a handful of x22sourcex22 JavaScript files that gets x22compiledx22 into one final, compressed JavaScript file? Any other handy hints or best practices?x3C/px3E',1,9,'msmallpeacex','2008-08-19 03:45:14'),(15470,'How do I get rid of Home in ASP.Net MVC?','x3Cpx3EI know this site is written using ASP.Net MVC and I do not see x22/Homex22 in the url.  This proves to me that it can be done.  What special route and do I need?x3C/px3E',1,3,'chenburyh','2008-08-19 05:02:59'),(15690,'How do you begin designing a large system?','x3Cpx3EItx27s been mentioned to me that Ix27ll be the sole developer behind a large new system.  Among other things Ix27ll be designing a UI and database schema.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m sure Ix27ll receive some guidance, but Ix27d like to be able to knock their socks off.  What can I do in the meantime to prepare, and what will I need to keep in mind when I sit down at my computer with the spec?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EA few things to keep in mind: Ix27m a college student at my first real programming job.  Ix27ll be using Java.  We already have SCM set up with automated testing, etc...so tools are not an issue.x3C/px3E',1,11,'aillidges','2008-08-19 08:26:33'),(15700,'Runtime Configuration in .Net (specifically the EntLib)','x3Cpx3EIx27m looking for a way to configure a DB connection at runtime; specifically using the Enterprise Library.  I see that therex27s a *.Data.Configuration (or something close to this ... donx27t recall off the top of my head) assembly but am finding not much on the interwebs.  Complicating matters is the fact that the API help is broken on Vista.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENow, I found this work-around:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EConfiguration cfg = ConfigurationManager.OpenExeConfiguration(ConfigurationUserLevel.None);\nConnectionStringSettings connection = new ConnectionStringSettings();\nconnection.Name = x22Runtime Connectionx22;\nconnection.ProviderName = x22System.Data.OleDbx22;\nconnection.ConnectionString = x22myconstringx22;\ncfg.ConnectionStrings.ConnectionStrings.Add(connection);\ncfg.Save(ConfigurationSaveMode.Modified);\n\nConfigurationManager.RefreshSection(x22connectionStringsx22);\nvar runtimeCon = DatabaseFactory.CreateDatabase(x22Runtime Connectionx22);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnd although it gives me what I want, it permanently edits the App.config. Sure I can go back and delete the changes, but Ix27d rather not go through this hassle.x3C/px3E',1,5,'sspindlerw','2008-08-19 08:32:13'),(15880,'Read from .msg files','x3Cpx3EI need to read from Outlook .MSG file in .NET x3Cemx3Ewithoutx3C/emx3E using COM API for Outlook (cos it will not be installed on the machines that my app will run). Are there any free 3rd party libraries to do that? I want to extract From, To, CC and BCC fields. Sent/Receive date fields would be good if they are also stored in MSG files.x3C/px3E',1,9,'sdally1','2008-08-19 12:07:28'),(15900,'Entity diagrams in ASP.NET MVC','x3Cpx3EWhatx27s the best way/tool to display nice diagrams with entity relationships in ASP MVC views?  x3Cbr /x3E\ni.e. servers and and applications, or servers with other servers.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAre there any third party tools out there that can do this?  x3Cbr /x3E\nIx27ve been searching around things like Telerik, but itx27s really hard to google for this!x3C/px3E',1,11,'scurraghy','2008-08-19 12:46:08'),(16100,'How do I convert a string to an enum in C#?','x3Cpx3EWhatx27s the best way to convert a string to an enumeration value in C#?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have an HTML select tag containing the values of an enumeration. When the page is posted, I want to pick up the value (which will be in the form of a string) and convert it to the enumeration value.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn an ideal world, I could do something like this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EStatusEnum MyStatus = StatusEnum.Parse(x22Activex22);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ebut that isnx27t valid code.x3C/px3E',1,8,'sspindlerw','2008-08-19 16:51:55'),(16110,'C# Auto Clearing Winform Textbox','x3Cpx3EI have a user that want to be able to select a textbox and have the current text selected so that he doesnx27t have to highlight it all in order to change the contents.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe contents need to be handle when enter is pushed.  That part I think I have figured out but any suggestions would be welcome. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe part I need help with is that once enter has been pushed, any entry into the textbox should clear the contents again.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EEdit:x3C/strongx3E The textbox controls an piece of RF hardware.  What the user wants to be able to do is enter a setting and press enter.  The setting is sent to the hardware.  Without doing anything else the user wants to be able to type in a new setting and press enter again.x3C/px3E',1,4,'awrefford16','2008-08-19 16:55:46'),(16140,'Whatx27s the best way to get started with OSGI?','x3Cpx3EWhat makes a module/service/bit of application functionality a particularly good candidate for an OSGi module? x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m interested in using x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OSGix22x3EOSGix3C/ax3E in my applications. Wex27re a Java shop and we use Spring pretty extensively, so Ix27m leaning toward using x3Ca href=x22http://www.springframework.org/osgix22x3ESpring Dynamic Modules for OSGi(tm) Service Platformsx3C/ax3E. Ix27m looking for a good way to incorporate a little bit of OSGi into an application as a trial. Has anyone here used this or a similar OSGi technology? Are there any pitfalls? x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3E@Nicolas - Thanks, Ix27ve seen that one. Itx27s a good tutorial, but Ix27m looking more for ideas on how to do my first x22realx22 OSGi bundle, as opposed to a Hello World example.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3E@david - Thanks for the link! Ideally, with a greenfield app, Ix27d design the whole thing to be dynamic. What Ix27m looking for right now, though, is to introduce it in a small piece of an existing application. Assuming I can pick any piece of the app, what are some factors to consider that would make that piece better or worse as an OSGi guinea pig?x3C/px3E',1,4,'achancelier6','2008-08-19 17:20:49'),(16320,'Should DB layer members be static or instance?','x3Cpx3EIx27ve seen projects where the classes in the DB layer have just static functions in them and other projects where those classes need to be instantiated to get access to the member functions. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhich is x22betterx22 and why?x3C/px3E',1,7,'idevey11','2008-08-19 18:49:55'),(16330,'How do I handle page flow in MVC (particularly asp.net)','x3Cpx3EIf you had to provide a wizard like form entry experience in mvc how would you abstract the page flow?x3C/px3E',1,7,'clawrence3','2008-08-19 18:53:06'),(16340,'How do I generate a hashcode from a byte array in C#?','x3Cpx3ESay I have an object that stores a byte array and I want to be able to efficiently generate a hashcode for it. Ix27ve used the cryptographic hash functions for this in the past because they are easy to implement, but they are doing a lot more work than they should to be cryptographically oneway, and I donx27t care about that (Ix27m just using the hashcode as a key into a hashtable).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHerex27s what I have today:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Estruct SomeData : IEquatablex26lt;SomeDatax26gt;\n{\n    private readonly byte[] data;\n    public SomeData(byte[] data)\n    {\n        if (null == data || data.Length x26lt;= 0)\n        {\n            throw new ArgumentException(x22datax22);\n        }\n        this.data = new byte[data.Length];\n        Array.Copy(data, this.data, data.Length);\n    }\n\n    public override bool Equals(object obj)\n    {\n        return obj is SomeData x26amp;x26amp; Equals((SomeData)obj);\n    }\n\n    public bool Equals(SomeData other)\n    {\n        if (other.data.Length != data.Length)\n        {\n            return false;\n        }\n        for (int i = 0; i x26lt; data.Length; ++i)\n        {\n            if (data[i] != other.data[i])\n            {\n                return false;\n            }\n        }\n        return true;\n    }\n    public override int GetHashCode()\n    {\n        return BitConverter.ToInt32(new MD5CryptoServiceProvider().ComputeHash(data), 0);\n    }\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny thoughts?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3Edp: You are right that I missed a check in Equals, I have updated it.  Using the existing hashcode from the byte array will result in reference equality (or at least that same concept translated to hashcodes).\nfor example:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ebyte[] b1 = new byte[] { 1 };\nbyte[] b2 = new byte[] { 1 };\nint h1 = b1.GetHashCode();\nint h2 = b2.GetHashCode();\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWith that code, despite the two byte arrays having the same values within them, they are referring to different parts of memory and will result in (probably) different hash codes. I need the hash codes for two byte arrays with the same contents to be equal.x3C/px3E',1,7,'rtomeo0','2008-08-19 18:55:33'),(16460,'Removing N items from a list conditionally','x3Cpx3EI was writing some x3Cstrongx3EASP.NETx3C/strongx3E control when I came to the scenario where I needed to remove items from a list, only when they matched a certain condition.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe x3Ccodex3ERemoveAllx3C/codex3E method of the generic x3Ccodex3EListx3C/codex3E class does a good job, but removes x3Cemx3Eallx3C/emx3E items that match the condition, specified by the predicate.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat if I want to only remove a certain number of items specifying the condition? What do you think is the best way to do this?x3C/px3E',1,4,'sdally1','2008-08-19 19:57:51'),(16550,'Best .NET build tool','x3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EPossible Duplicate:x3C/strongx3Ex3Cbrx3E\n  x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/476163x22x3ENAnt or MSBuild, which one to choose and when?x3C/ax3E  x3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\n\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat is the best build tool for x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/.NET_Frameworkx22x3E.NETx3C/ax3E?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI currently use x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NAntx22x3ENAntx3C/ax3E but only because I have experience with x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apache_Antx22x3EAntx3C/ax3E. Is x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MSBuildx22x3EMSBuildx3C/ax3E preferred?x3C/px3E',1,4,'cgaweno','2008-08-19 21:02:48'),(16610,'How do you deal with transport-level errors in SqlConnection?','x3Cpx3EEvery now and then in a high volume .NET application, you might see this exception when you try to execute a query:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3ESystem.Data.SqlClient.SqlException:  A transport-level error has\n  occurred when sending the request to the server.x3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAccording to my research, this is something that x22just happensx22 and not much can be done to prevent it.  It does not happen as a result of a bad query, and generally cannot be duplicated.  It just crops up maybe once every few days in a busy OLTP system when the TCP connection to the database goes bad for some reason.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI am forced to detect this error by parsing the exception message, and then retrying the entire operation from scratch, to include using a new connection.  None of that is pretty.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnybody have any alternate solutions?x3C/px3E',1,10,'hbuxcy1c','2008-08-19 21:36:05'),(16660,'Internationalization in SSRS','x3Cpx3EWhatx27s the best way to handle translations for stock text in a x3Ccodex3ESSRSx3C/codex3E. For instance - if I have a report that shows a grid of contents whatx27s the best way to have the correct translation for the header of that grid show up, assuming the culture of the report is set correctly.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EPut another way - is it possible to do resources in a x3Ccodex3ESSRSx3C/codex3E report, or am I stuck with storing all that text in the database and querying for it?x3C/px3E',1,10,'astarmoreq','2008-08-19 22:15:29'),(16770,'Haskellx27s algebraic data types','x3Cpx3EIx27m trying to fully understand all of Haskellx27s concepts.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn what ways are algebraic data types similar to generic types, e.g., in C# and Java? And how are they different? Whatx27s so algebraic about them anyway? x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m familiar with universal algebra and its rings and fields, but I only have a vague idea of how Haskellx27s types work.x3C/px3E',1,3,'erowcliffe1d','2008-08-19 23:18:41'),(16860,'Getting Started with Unit Testing','x3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3EUnit testing is, roughly speaking, testing bits of your code in isolation with test code. The immediate advantages that come to mind are:x3C/px3E\n  \n  x3Culx3E\n  x3Clix3ERunning the tests becomes automate-able and repeatablex3C/lix3E\n  x3Clix3EYou can test at a much more granular level than point-and-click testing via a GUIx3C/lix3E\n  x3C/ulx3E\n  \n  x3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1383/what-is-unit-testingx22x3ERytmisx3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy question is, what are the current x22best practicesx22 in terms of tools as well as when and where to use unit testing as part of your daily coding?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ELets try to be somewhat language agnostic and cover all the bases.x3C/px3E',1,8,'dmatuszinski15','2008-08-20 00:18:09'),(16940,'VS 2008 - Detachable code tabs','x3Cpx3EAdmittedly this might not be a problem on larger screens, but my employer is abit tight and refuses to buy monitors larger than 19inch, this means that I dont have much screen real estate to view all the Visual Studio windows and my code at the same time, or two pieces of code at once. Is there anything that allows me to detach the code panels so that I can view two different classes at once on each of my screens? x3C/px3E',1,6,'hbuxcy1c','2008-08-20 00:57:28'),(16970,'Recommended notes/doc service that offers an API?','x3Cpx3EIx27m looking for a good online service for notes/documents (think Google Docs) that has a decent web UI and offers an API for clients to read/write the stored data.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EGoogle Docs is almost perfect - except therex27s no way to update the contents of existing documents.x3C/px3E',1,9,'aillidges','2008-08-20 01:13:55'),(17020,'What is the best way to partition terabyte drive in a linux development machine?','x3Cpx3EI have a new 1 TB drive coming in tomorrow. What is the best way to divide this space for a development workstation?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe biggest problem I think Ix27m going to have is that some partitions (probably /usr) will become to small after a bit of use. Other partitions are probably to huge. The swap drive for example is currently 2GB (2x 1GB RAM), but it is almost never used (only once that I know of).x3C/px3E',1,7,'clawrence3','2008-08-20 01:42:30'),(17140,'How do you spawn another process in C?','x3Cpx3EHow do you run an external program and pass it command line parameters using C? If you have to use operating system API, include a solution for Windows, Mac, and Linux.x3C/px3E',1,7,'scurraghy','2008-08-20 02:53:47'),(17170,'When to use IList and when to use List','x3Cpx3EI know that IList is the interface and List is the concrete type but I still donx27t know when to use each one. What Ix27m doing now is if I donx27t need the Sort or FindAll methods I use the interface. Am I right? Is there a better way to decide when to use the interface or the concrete type?x3C/px3E',1,4,'dperrenl','2008-08-20 03:09:54'),(17250,'Create an encrypted ZIP file in Python','x3Cpx3EIx27m creating an ZIP file with ZipFile in Python 2.5, it works ok so far:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eimport zipfile, os\n\nlocfile = x22test.txtx22\nloczip = os.path.splitext (locfile)[0] + x22.zipx22\nzip = zipfile.ZipFile (loczip, x22wx22)\nzip.write (locfile)\nzip.close()\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ebut I couldnx27t find how to encrypt the files in the ZIP file.\nI could use system and call PKZIP -s, but I suppose there must be a more x22Pythonicx22 way.  Ix27m looking for an open source solution.x3C/px3E',1,8,'mschafflere','2008-08-20 04:16:40'),(17320,'What areas of specialization within programming would you recommend to a beginner','x3Cpx3EI am a student studying software development, and I feel programming, in general, is too broad of a subject to try to know everything. To be proficient, you have to decide which areas to focus your learning and understanding. Certain skill sets synergize with each other, like data-driven web development and SQL experience. However, all the win32 API experience in the world may not directly apply to linux development. This leads me to believe, as a beginning programmer, I should start deciding where I want to specialize after I have general understanding of the basic principles of software development. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis is a multi-part question really: x3C/px3E\n\nx3Colx3E\nx3Clix3EWhat are the common specializations within computer programming and software development?  x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EWhich of these specializations have more long-term value, both as a foundation for other specializations and/or as marketable skills? x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EWhich skill sets complement each other? x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EAre there any areas of specialization that hinder your ability of developing other areas of specialization.x3C/lix3E\nx3C/olx3E',1,3,'cleatham18','2008-08-20 05:59:08'),(17370,'Using GLEW to use OpenGL extensions under Windows','x3Cpx3EIx27ve been using OpenGL extensions on Windows the x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/14413/using-opengl-extensions-on-windowsx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Epainful wayx3C/ax3E. Is GLEW the easier way to go? How do I get started with it?x3C/px3E',1,11,'gdodding5','2008-08-20 07:19:34'),(17430,'Language Conversion Testing','x3Cpx3EWe created a tool which converts a language called P2, a language similar to assembly which I think exists only in Japan, to C#. There are at least a hundred modules written in P2 and we want to verify if the conversion to C# is right? How can we test this?x3C/px3E',1,3,'ofaircloughi','2008-08-20 09:18:22'),(17500,'Why are DispatcherObject.CheckAccess() and VerifyAccess() hidden from Intellisense?','x3Cpx3EThe x3Ccodex3ESystem.Windows.Threading.DispatcherObjectx3C/codex3E class (which x3Ccodex3EDependencyObjectx3C/codex3E is based on) contains a useful function, called x3Ccodex3ECheckAccess()x3C/codex3E, that determines whether or not the code is running on the UI thread.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhen I wanted to use it yesterday, I was puzzled to find out that Intellisense didnx27t show the function (nor x3Ccodex3EVerifyAccess()x3C/codex3E, which throws an exception when not on the UI thread), even though the MSDN library lists it. I decided to investigate the class using Reflector. It seems that the function in question has an x3Ccodex3EEditorBrowsable(EditorBrowsableState.Never)x3C/codex3E attribute attached to it. The x3Ccodex3EDispatcherx3C/codex3E class, which is used by x3Ccodex3EDispatcherObjectx3C/codex3E, has the same attribute attached to x3Ccodex3ECheckAccess()x3C/codex3E and x3Ccodex3EVerifyAccess()x3C/codex3E:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Epublic abstract class DispatcherObject\n{\n    // ...\n\n    [EditorBrowsable(EditorBrowsableState.Never)]\n    public bool CheckAccess();\n    [EditorBrowsable(EditorBrowsableState.Never)]\n    public void VerifyAccess();\n\n    // ...\n\n    [EditorBrowsable(EditorBrowsableState.Advanced)]\n    public Dispatcher Dispatcher { get; }\n}\n\n\npublic sealed class Dispatcher\n{\n    // ...\n\n    [EditorBrowsable(EditorBrowsableState.Never)]\n    public bool CheckAccess();\n    [EditorBrowsable(EditorBrowsableState.Never)]\n    public void VerifyAccess();\n\n    // ...\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI donx27t believe that the application of that attribute is random (or a joke), so my question is: why is it there? Should those methods not be called directly? Then why arenx27t they x3Ccodex3Eprotectedx3C/codex3E (or x3Ccodex3Einternalx3C/codex3E, like some of the most useful methods in the WPF)?x3C/px3E',1,4,'aauger2','2008-08-20 11:07:30'),(17670,'Suitable alternative to CryptEncrypt','x3Cpx3EWe have a situation in our product where for a long time some data has been stored in the applicationx27s database as SQL string (choice of MS SQL server or sybase SQL anywhere) which was encrypted via the Windows API function x3Ca href=x22http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa379924.aspxx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3ECryptEncrypt.x3C/ax3E  (direct and decryptable)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe problem is that CryptEncrypt can produce NULLx27s in the output, meaning that when itx27s stored in the database, the string manipulations will at some point truncate the ciphertext.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIdeally wex27d like to use an algo that will produce cyphertext that doesnx27t contain NULLs as that will cause the least amount of change to the existing databases (changing a column from string to binary and code to deal with binary instead of strings) and just decrypt existing data and re-encrypt with the new algo at database upgrade time.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe algorithm doesnx27t need to be the most secure, as the database is already in a reasonably secure environment (not an open network / teh interwebs) but does need to bebetter than ROT13 (which I can almost decrypt in my head now!)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECheersx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Eedit: btw, any particular reason for changing ciphertext to cyphertext? ciphertext seems more widely used...x3C/px3E',1,11,'jsorel9','2008-08-20 13:37:02'),(17770,'Tracking Useful Information','x3Cpx3EWhat do the clever programmers here do to keep track of handy programming tricks and useful information they pick up over their many years of experience? Things like useful compiler arguments, IDE short-cuts, clever code snippets, etc.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI sometimes find myself frustrated when looking up something that I used to know a year or two ago. My IE favourites probably represent a good chunk of the Internet in the late 1990s, so clearly that isnx27t effective (at least for me). Or am I just getting old?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo.. what do you do?x3C/px3E',1,5,'tyurkiewicz19','2008-08-20 15:32:33'),(17840,'How can I learn about parser combinators?','x3Cpx3EIx27ve found a few resources on the subject, but they all require a deep understanding of x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smalltalkx22x3ESmallTalkx3C/ax3E or x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Haskell_%28programming_language%29x22x3EHaskellx3C/ax3E, neither of which I know.x3C/px3E',1,4,'tplumsteadj','2008-08-20 16:38:49'),(17870,'Select ..... where .... OR','x3Cpx3EIs there a way to select data where any one of multiple conditions occur on the same field?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EExample: I would typically write a statement such as:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eselect * from TABLE where field = 1 or field = 2 or field = 3\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there a way to instead say something like:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eselect * from TABLE where field = 1 || 2 || 3\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny help is appreciated.x3C/px3E',1,1,'ajan8','2008-08-20 16:58:51'),(17880,'Mac iWork/Pages Automation','x3Cpx3EThere is a rich scripting model for Microsoft Office, but not so with Apple iWork, and specifically the word processor Pages. While there are some AppleScript hooks, it looks like the best approach is to manipulate the underlying XML data.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis turns out to be pretty ugly because (for example) page breaks are stored in XML. So for example, you have something like:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E... we hold these truths to be self evident, that x26lt;/pagex26gt;\nx26lt;pagex26gt;all men are created equal, and are ...\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo if you want to add or remove text, you have to move the start/end tags around based on the size of the text on the page. This is pretty impossible without computing the number of words a page can hold, which seems wildly inelegant.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnybody have any thoughts on this?x3C/px3E',1,5,'eburnyaten','2008-08-20 17:02:38'),(17960,'PowerShell App.Config','x3Cpx3EHas anyone worked out how to get PowerShell to use x3Ccodex3Eapp.configx3C/codex3E files? I have a couple of .NET DLLx27s Ix27d like to use in one of my scripts but they expect their own config sections to be present in x3Ccodex3Eapp.configx3C/codex3E/x3Ccodex3Eweb.configx3C/codex3E.x3C/px3E',1,6,'achancelier6','2008-08-20 17:33:58'),(17980,'What Comes After The %?','x3Cpx3EIx27ve searched for this a little but I have not gotten a particularly straight answer. In C (and I guess C++), how do you determine what comes after the % when using x3Ccodex3Eprintfx3C/codex3E?. For example:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Edouble radius = 1.0;\ndouble area = 0.0;\narea = calculateArea( radius );\nprintf( x22%10.1f     %10.2\\nx22, radius, area );\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI took this example straight from a book that I have on the C language. This does not make sense to me at all. Where do you come up with x3Ccodex3E10.1fx3C/codex3E and x3Ccodex3E10.2fx3C/codex3E? Could someone please explain this?x3C/px3E',1,9,'osilley7','2008-08-20 17:44:34'),(18010,'Is AnkhSVN any good?','x3Cpx3EI asked a couple of coworkers about x3Ca href=x22http://ankhsvn.open.collab.netx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EAnkhSVNx3C/ax3E and neither one of them was happy with it. One of them went as far as saying that AnkhSVN has messed up his devenv several times.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhatx27s your experience with AnkhSVN? I really miss having an IDE integrated source control tool.x3C/px3E',1,1,'awrefford16','2008-08-20 17:54:31'),(18080,'Best traffic / performance / usage monitoring module?','x3Cpx3EAre there any open source (or I guess commercial) packages that you can plug into your site for monitoring purposes? Ix27d like something that we can hook up to our ASP.NET site and use to provide reporting on things like:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3Eperformance over timex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ecurrent loadx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Epage trafficx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3ESQL performancex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EPU time monitoring x3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIdeally in c# :)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWith some sexy graphs.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EEditx3C/strongx3E: Ix27d also be happy with a package that I can feed statistics and views of data to, and it would analyse trends, spot abnormal behaviour (e.g. x22no one has logged in for the last hour. is this Ok?x22, x22high traffic levels detectedx22, x22low number of API calls detectedx22)  and generally be very useful indeed. Does such a thing exist?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAt my last office we had a big screen which showed us loads and loads of performance counters over a couple of time ranges, and we could spot weird stuff happening, but the data was not stored and there was no way to report on it. Its a package for doing this that Ix27m after.x3C/px3E',1,7,'dmatuszinski15','2008-08-20 18:20:40'),(18250,'Creation Date of Compiled Executable (VC++ 2005)','x3Cpx3EThe creation date of an executable linked in VS2005 is not set to the real creation-date of the exe-file. Only a complete re-build will set the current date, a re-link will not do it. Obviously the file is set to some date, which is taken from one of the project-files. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo: is there a way to force the linker to set the creation-date to the real link-date?x3C/px3E',1,9,'awrefford16','2008-08-20 19:40:53'),(18290,'How Do You Secure database.yml?','x3Cpx3EWithin Ruby on Rails applications database.yml is a plain text file that stores database credentials.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhen I deploy my Rails applications I have an after deploy callback in my Capistrano \nrecipe that creates a symbolic link within the applicationx27s /config directory to the database.yml file. The file itself is stored in a separate directory thatx27s outside the standard Capistrano /releases directory structure. I chmod 400 the file so itx27s only readable by the user who created it.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3EIs this sufficient to lock it down? If not, what else do you do?x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EIs anyone encrypting their database.yml files?x3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E',1,5,'aa9279','2008-08-20 20:12:46'),(18450,'Is Mono ready for prime time?','x3Cpx3EHas anyone used Mono, the open source .NET implementation on a large or medium sized project? Ix27m wondering if itx27s ready for real world, production environments. Is it stable, fast, compatible, ... enough to use? Does it take a lot of effort to port projects to the Mono runtime, or is it really, x3Cemx3Ereallyx3C/emx3E compatible enough to just take of and run already written code for Microsoftx27s runtime?x3C/px3E',1,2,'dperrenl','2008-08-20 21:57:44'),(18460,'Best practise to authorize all users for just one page','x3Cpx3EWhat is the best way to authorize all users to one single page in a asp.net website.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EFor except the login page and one other page, I deny all users from viewing pages in the website. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow do you make this page accessible to all users?x3C/px3E',1,10,'fbrizellc','2008-08-20 22:04:58'),(18700,'Arguments for going open source','x3Cpx3EIx27ve spent my downtime at work this summer writing a framework of sorts for facilitating my day to day work. In short it loads a xml with markup that defines the blocks of the site, their content and the styling of these (very similar to html), handles the loading of assets and such.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENow Ix27m rather pleased with how this is turning out, and Ix27ve been itching to release some of my code for public use (and scrutiny). Ix27m also reasonably sure that it fills a void for quick and easy construction of sites (or parts of them).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3Ex3Cemx3EWhat would be the best arguments to convince my boss/coworkers that releasing this under an open source license is a good idea?x3C/emx3Ex3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E',1,7,'scurraghy','2008-08-21 00:05:22'),(18920,'Can you set, or where is, the local document root?','x3Cpx3EWhen opening a file from your hard drive into your browser, where is the document root?  To illustrate, given the following HTML code, if the page is opened from the local machine(file:///) then where should the css file be for the browser to find it?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ex26lt;link href=x22/temp/test.cssx22 rel=x22stylesheetx22 type=x22text/cssx22 /x26gt;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E',1,7,'srm4902','2008-08-21 01:43:23'),(19030,'How to check set of files conform to a naming scheme','x3Cpx3EI have a bunch of files (TV episodes, although that is fairly arbitrary) that I want to check match a specific naming/organisation scheme..x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECurrently: I have three arrays of regex, one for valid filenames, one for files missing an episode name, and one for valid paths.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThen, I loop though each valid-filename regex, if it matches, append it to a x22validx22 dict, if not, do the same with the missing-ep-name regexs, if it matches this I append it to an x22invalidx22 dict with an error code (2:x27missing epsiode namex27), if it matches neither, it gets added to invalid with the x27malformed namex27 error code.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe current code can be found x3Ca href=x22http://github.com/dbr/checktveps/tree/8a6dc68ad61e684c8d8f0ca1dc37a22d1c51aa82/2checkTvEps.pyx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Eherex3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI want to add a rule that checks for the presence of a folder.jpg file in each directory, but to add this would make the code substantially more messy in itx27s current state.. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow could I write this system in a more expandable way?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe rules it needs to check would be..x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3EFile is in the format x3Ccodex3EShow Name - [01x23] - Episode Name.avix3C/codex3E or x3Ccodex3EShow Name - [01xSpecial02] - Special Name.avix3C/codex3E or x3Ccodex3EShow Name - [01xExtra01] - Extra Name.avix3C/codex3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EIf filename is in the format x3Ccodex3EShow Name - [01x23].avix3C/codex3E display it a x27missing episode namex27 section of the outputx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EThe path should be in the format x3Ccodex3EShow Name/season 2/the_file.avix3C/codex3E (where season 2 should be the correct season number in the filename)x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Eeach x3Ccodex3EShow Name/season 1/x3C/codex3E folder should contain x22folder.jpgx22x3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3E.any ideas? While Ix27m trying to check TV episodes, this concept/code should be able to apply to many things..x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe only thought I had was a list of dicts in the format:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Echecker = [\n{\n    x27namex27:x27valid filesx27,\n    x27typex27:x27filex27,\n    x27functionx27:check_valid(), # runs check_valid() on all files\n    x27statusx27:0 # if it returns True, this is the status the file gets\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E',1,7,'cribbens4','2008-08-21 02:50:55'),(19280,'Code to ask yes/no question in javascript','x3Cpx3EI could only find the function x3Ccodex3Econfirm()x3C/codex3E that gives OK/Cancel buttons. Is there any way to give Yes/No buttons?x3C/px3E',1,10,'prihak','2008-08-21 07:20:05'),(19790,'Display rows in multiple columns in Asp.net Gridview','x3Cpx3EBy default each row of a Gridview maps to each row in a datatable or dataset attached to its datasource. But what if I want to display these rows in multiple columns. For example if it has 10 rows, 5 rows each should be displayed in 2 columns side by side. Also can I do this with the Infragistics grid. Is this possible?x3C/px3E',1,4,'cribbens4','2008-08-21 17:00:56'),(19970,'Best way to keep an ordered list of windows (from most-recently created to oldest)?','x3Cpx3EWhat is the best way to manage a list of windows (keeping them in order) to be able to promote the next window to the top-level when the current top-level window is closed.x3Cbrx3E\nThis is for a web application, so wex27re using jQuery Javascript.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWex27d talked through a few simplistic solutions, such as using an array and just treating [0] index as the top-most window.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m wondering if therex27s any potentially more efficient or useful alternative to what we had brainstormed.x3C/px3E',1,9,'hschade12','2008-08-21 17:58:25'),(20040,'What are the most important things to learn about .net as a Project Manager?','x3Cpx3EThinking about getting into .net technology project managementx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve had plenty of experience with PHP projects: Ix27m aware of most of the existing frameworks and libraries, and Ix27ve written specs and case studies based on this knowledge.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat should I know about .net?\nWhich top resources would you recommend me to know so I can rapidly learn and later stay up to date on the technology?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EEdit (8.24.08):x3C/strongx3E The answers I got so far essentially discuss being a good PM. Thanks, but this is not what I meant. Any .net essentials would be appreciated.x3C/px3E',1,4,'tplumsteadj','2008-08-21 18:14:53'),(20420,'Any ReSharper equivalent for Xcode?','x3Cpx3EIx27m a complete Xcode/Objective-C/Cocoa newbie but Ix27m learning fast and really starting to enjoy getting to grips with a new language, platform and paradigm.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EOne thing is though, having been using Visual Studio with R# for so long Ix27ve kind of been spoiled with the coding tools such as refactorings and completion etc and as far as I can tell Xcode has some fairly limited built in support for this stuff.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EOn that note, does anyone know if any add-ins or whatever are available for the Xcode environment which add coding helpers such as automatically generating implementation skeletons from a class interface definition etc? x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI suspect there arenx27t but I suppose it canx27t help to ask.x3C/px3E',1,2,'dsizland14','2008-08-21 20:18:41'),(20450,'Cleaning up RTF text','x3Cpx3EIx27d like to take some RTF input and clean it to remove all RTF formatting except \\ul \\b \\i to paste it into Word with minor format information.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe command used to paste into Word will be something like:\noWord.ActiveDocument.ActiveWindow.Selection.PasteAndFormat(0) (with some RTF text already in the Clipboard)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E{\\rtf1\\ansi\\deff0{\\fonttbl{\\f0\\fnil\\fcharset0 Courier New;}}\n{\\colortbl ;\\red255\\green255\\blue140;}\n\\viewkind4\\uc1\\pard\\highlight1\\lang3084\\f0\\fs18 The company is a global leader in responsible tourism and was \\ul the first major hotel chain in North America\\ulnone  to embrace environmental stewardship within its daily operations\\highlight0\\par\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDo you have any idea on how I can clean up the RTF safely with some regular expressions or something? I am using VB.NET to do the processing but any .NET language sample will do.x3C/px3E',1,9,'cscarbarrowm','2008-08-21 20:30:49'),(20510,'Executing JavaScript from Flex: Is this javascript function dangerous?','x3Cpx3EI have a flex application that needs the ability to generate and execute JavaScript. When I say this, I mean I need to execute raw JavaScript that I create in my Flex application (not just an existing JavaScript method)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI am currently doing this by exposing the following JavaScript method:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Efunction doScript(js){ eval(js);}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI can then do something like this in Flex (note: I am doing something more substantial then an alert box in the real Flex app):x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EExternalInterface.call(x22doScriptx22,x22alert(x27foox27));\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy question is does this impose any security risk, I am assuming itx27s not since the Flex and JasvaScript all run client side...x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there a better way to do this?x3C/px3E',1,1,'mschafflere','2008-08-21 20:55:09'),(20840,'SQL Server - Dirty Reads Pros x26 Cons','x3Cpx3EWhy should I or shouldnx27t I use dirty reads:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eset transaction isolation level read uncommitted\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ein SQL Server?x3C/px3E',1,3,'achancelier6','2008-08-21 23:12:59'),(20850,'How to stop NTFS volume auto-mounting on OS X?','x3Cpx3EIx27m a bit newbieish when it comes to the deeper parts of OSX configuration and am having to put up with a fairly irritating niggle which while I can put up with it, I know under Windows I could have sorted in minutes.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBasically, I have an external disk with two volumes: x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EOne is an HFS+ volume which I use for TimeMachine backups.\nThe other, an NTFS volume that I use for general file copying etc on Mac and Windows boxes.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo what happens is that whenever I plug in the disk into my Mac USB, OSX goes off and mounts both volumes and shows an icon on the desktop for each. The thing is that to remove the disk you have to eject the volume and in this case do it for both volumes, which causes an annoying warning dialog to be shown every time. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat Ix27d prefer is some way to prevent the NTFS volume from auto-mounting altogether. Ix27ve done some hefty googling and herex27s a list of things Ix27ve tried so far:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3EIx27ve tried going through options in Disk Utilityx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EIx27ve tried setting AutoMount to No in /etc/hostconfig but that is a bit too global for my liking.x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EIx27ve also tried the suggested approach to putting settings in fstab but it appears the OSX (10.5) is ignoring these settings.x3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny other suggestions would be welcomed. Just a little dissapointed that I canx27t just tick a box somewhere (or untick).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEDIT: Thanks heaps to hop for the answer it worked a treat. For the record it turns out that it wasnx27t OSX not picking up the settings I actually had x22msdosx22 instead of x22ntfsx22 in the fs type column.x3C/px3E',1,9,'aillidges','2008-08-21 23:16:27'),(20880,'Java JPanel redraw issues','x3Cpx3EI have a Java swing application with a panel that contains three JComboBoxes that do not draw properly.x3Cbrx3E\nThe combox boxes just show up as the down arrow on the right side, but without the label of the currently selected value.x3Cbrx3E\nThe boxes will redraw correctly if the window is resized either bigger or smaller by even one pixel.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAll of my googling has pointed to calling revalidate() on the JPanel to fix this, but that hasnx27t worked for me.x3Cbrx3E\nCalling updateUI() on the JPanel has changed it from always displaying incorrectly to displaying incorrectly half of the time.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHas anyone else seen this and found a different way to force a redraw of the combo boxes?x3C/px3E',1,8,'enewberryf','2008-08-21 23:26:44'),(20910,'Silverlight vs Flex','x3Cpx3EMy company develops several types of applications.  A lot of our business comes from doing multimedia-type apps, typically done in Flash.  However, now that side of the house is starting to migrate towards doing Flex development.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMost of our other development is done using .NET.  Ix27m trying to make a push towards doing Silverlight development instead, since it would take better advantage of the .NET developers on staff.  I prefer the Silverlight platform over the Flex platform for the simple fact that Silverlight is all .NET code.  We have more .NET developers on staff than Flash/Flex developers, and most of our Flash/Flex developers are graphic artists (not real programmers).  Only reason they push towards Flex right now is because it seems like the logical step from Flash.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve done development using both, and I honestly believe Silverlight is easier to work with.  But Ix27m trying to convince people who are only Flash developers. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo herex27s my question:  If Ix27m going to go into a meeting to praise Silverlight, why would a company want to go with Silverlight instead of Flex?  Other than the obvious x22not everyone has Silverlightx22, what are the pros and cons for each?x3C/px3E',1,4,'itrowla','2008-08-21 23:34:00'),(21060,'Is there any way to configure windows to not change the focus?','x3Cpx3EIx27m tired of being in the middle of typing something, having a pop-up with a question appear, and hitting enter before reading it... (it also happens with some windows that are not pop-ups)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDo you know if therex27s some setting I could touch for this not to happen?x3C/px3E',1,11,'gdodding5','2008-08-22 00:22:50'),(21280,'Am I missing something about LINQ?','x3Cpx3EI seem to be missing something about LINQ.  To me, it looks like itx27s taking some of the elements of SQL that I like the least and moving them into the C# language and using them for other things.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI mean, I could see the benefit of using SQL-like statements on things other than databases.  But if I wanted to write SQL, well, why not just write SQL and keep it out of C#?  What am I missing here?x3C/px3E',1,2,'gdodding5','2008-08-22 01:54:56'),(21460,'Does Hostmonster support Django','x3Cpx3EI know Hostmonster allows Python. Has anyone successfully run Django on there? Any problems? x3C/px3E',1,10,'enewberryf','2008-08-22 03:51:10'),(21560,'How to enable multisampling for a wxWidgets OpenGL program?','x3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multisample_anti-aliasingx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EMultisamplingx3C/ax3Ex3C/strongx3E is a way of applying x3Cstrongx3Efull screen anti-aliasingx3C/strongx3E (FSAA) in 3D applications. I need to use multisampling in my OpenGL program, which is currently embedded in a x3Cstrongx3EwxWidgetsx3C/strongx3E GUI. Is there a way to do this? Please respond only if you know the detailed steps to achieve this.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m aware of enabling multisampling using x3Cstrongx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms537544%28VS.85%29.aspxx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EWGLx3C/ax3Ex3C/strongx3E (Win32 extensions to OpenGL). However, since my OpenGL program isnx27t written in MFC (and I want the code to be multi-platform portable), thatx27s not an option for me.x3C/px3E',1,7,'itrowla','2008-08-22 05:16:26'),(21640,'.NET - Get protocol, host, and port','x3Cpx3EIs there a simple way in x3Cemx3E.NETx3C/emx3E to quickly get the current protocol, host, and port? For example, if Ix27m on the following URL:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ccodex3Ehttp://www.mywebsite.com:80/pages/page1.aspxx3C/codex3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI need to return:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ccodex3Ehttp://www.mywebsite.com:80x3C/codex3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI know I can use x3Ccodex3ERequest.Url.AbsoluteUrix3C/codex3E to get the complete URL, and I know I can use x3Ccodex3ERequest.Url.Authorityx3C/codex3E to get the host and port, but Ix27m not sure of the best way to get the protocol without parsing out the URL string.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny suggestions?x3C/px3E',1,2,'erowcliffe1d','2008-08-22 06:18:28'),(21830,'PostgreSQL: GIN or GiST indexes?','x3Cpx3EFrom what information I could find, they both solve the same problems - more esoteric operations like array containment and intersection (x26amp;x26amp;, @x3E, x26lt;@, etc). However I would be interested in advice about when to use one or the other (or neither possibly).x3Cbrx3E\nThe x3Ca href=x22http://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/static/textsearch-indexes.htmlx22x3EPostgreSQL documentationx3C/ax3E has some information about this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3EGIN index lookups are about three times faster than GiSTx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EGIN indexes take about three times longer to build than GiSTx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EGIN indexes are about ten times slower to update than GiSTx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EGIN indexes are two-to-three times larger than GiSTx3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHowever I would be particularly interested to know if there is a performance impact when the memory to index size ration starts getting small (ie. the index size becomes much bigger than the available memory)? Ix27ve been told on the #postgresql IRC channel that GIN needs to keep all the index in memory, otherwise it wonx27t be effective, because, unlike B-Tree, it doesnx27t know which part to read in from disk for a particular query? The question would be: is this true (because Ix27ve also been told the opposite of this)? Does GiST have the same restrictions? Are there other restrictions I should be aware of while using one of these indexing algorithms?x3C/px3E',1,5,'rdowdellz','2008-08-22 09:22:39'),(21870,'System.Web.Caching vs. Enterprise Library Caching Block','x3Cpx3EFor a .NET component that will be used in both web applications and rich client applications, there seem to be two obvious options for caching: System.Web.Caching or the Ent. Lib. Caching Block.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3EWhat do you use?x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EWhy?x3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Ch2x3Ex3Ca href=x22http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/system.web.caching.aspxx22x3ESystem.Web.Cachingx3C/ax3Ex3C/h2x3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs this safe to use outside of web apps?  Ix27ve seen mixed information, but I think the answer is maybe-kind-of-not-really.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Ca href=x22http://support.microsoft.com/kb/917411x22x3Ea KB article warning against 1.0 and 1.1 non web app usex3C/ax3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EThe 2.0 page has a x3Cemx3Ecommentx3C/emx3E that indicates itx27s OK: x3Ca href=x22http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/system.web.caching.cache(VS.80).aspxx22x3Ehttp://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/system.web.caching.cache(VS.80).aspxx3C/ax3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Ca href=x22http://www.hanselman.com/blog/UsingTheASPNETCacheOutsideOfASPNET.aspxx22x3EScott Hanselman is creeped out by the notionx3C/ax3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Ca href=x22http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/system.web.caching.cache.aspxx22x3EThe 3.5 pagex3C/ax3E includes a warning against such usex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3ERob Howard x3Ca href=x22http://weblogs.asp.net/cschittko/archive/2004/07/04/172684.aspxx22x3Eencouraged use outside of web appsx3C/ax3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI donx27t expect to use one of its highlights, x3Ca href=x22http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/system.web.caching.sqlcachedependency.aspxx22x3ESqlCacheDependencyx3C/ax3E, but the addition of x3Ca href=x22http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/system.web.caching.cacheitemupdatecallback.aspxx22x3ECacheItemUpdateCallbackx3C/ax3E in .NET 3.5 seems like a Really Good Thing.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Ch2x3Ex3Ca href=x22http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa480453.aspxx22x3EEnterprise Library Caching Application Blockx3C/ax3Ex3C/h2x3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3Eother blocks are already in use so the dependency already existsx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ecache persistence isnx27t necessary; regenerating the cache on restart is OKx3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESome cache items should always be available, but be refreshed periodically.  For these items, getting a callback x3Cemx3Eafterx3C/emx3E an item has been removed is not very convenient.  It looks like a client will have to just sleep and poll until the cache item is repopulated.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Ch2x3Ex3Ca href=x22http://jehiah.cz/projects/memcached-win32/x22x3EMemcached for Win32x3C/ax3E + x3Ca href=x22http://sourceforge.net/projects/memcacheddotnet/x22x3E.NET clientx3C/ax3Ex3C/h2x3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat are the pros and cons when you donx27t need a x3Cemx3Edistributedx3C/emx3E cache?x3C/px3E',1,8,'jsorel9','2008-08-22 10:07:29'),(22000,'Table cells larger than they are meant to be','x3Cpx3EIx27ve created a map system for a game that runs on the principle of drawing the picture of the map from tiles. There are many reasons for this which I wonx27t go into here but if you really want to know then Ix27m sure you can find out how to contact me ;)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have x3Ca href=x22http://woarl.com/board/rob.php?mode=mapx26amp;x=-1x26amp;y=9x26amp;w=2x26amp;h=2x22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Emade the latest version livex3C/ax3E so you can see exactly where the problem lies and the source. The issue is the line between the top 2 tiles and the bottom 2 tiles, I canx27t figure out why itx27s gone like this and any help would be appreciated.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn the source is a marker called x22stackoverflowx22, if you search for x22stackoverflowx22 when viewing source then it should take you to the table in question.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have also uploaded an x3Ca href=x22http://woarl.com/badMap.pngx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Eimage of the issuex3C/ax3E.x3C/px3E',1,4,'mheyward10','2008-08-22 13:55:34'),(22140,'Can you compile Apache HTTP Server and redeploy its binaries to a different location?','x3Cpx3EAs part of our product release we ship Apache HTTP Server binaries that we have compiled on our (UNIX) development machine.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWe tell our clients to install the binaries (on their UNIX servers) under the same directory structure that we compiled it under. For some clients this is not appropriate, e.g. where there are restrictions on where they can install software on their servers and they donx27t want to compile Apache themselves.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there a way of compiling Apache HTTP Server so its installation location(s) can be specified dynamically using environment variables ?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI spent a few days trying to sort this out and couldnx27t find a way to do it. It led me to believe that the Apache binaries were hard coding some directory paths at compilation preventing the portability we require.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHas anyone managed to do this ?x3C/px3E',1,7,'mschafflere','2008-08-22 15:57:53'),(22340,'WCF push to client through firewall?','x3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3ESee also x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1700917/how-does-a-wcf-server-inform-a-wcf-client-about-changes-better-solution-then-six22x3EHow does a WCF server inform\n  a WCF client about changes? (Better\n  solution then simple polling, e.g.\n  Coment or long polling)x3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI need to use push-technology with WCF through client firewalls. This must be a common problem, and I know for a fact it works in theory (see links below), but I have failed to get it working, and I havenx27t been able to find a code sample that demonstrates it.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ERequirements: x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3EWCFx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EClients connects to server through tcp port 80 (netTcpBinding).x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EServer pushes back information at irregular intervals (1 min to several hours).x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EUsers should not have to configure their firewalls, server pushes must pass through firewalls that have all inbound ports closed. TCP duplex on the same connection is needed for this, a dual binding does not work since a port has to be opened on the client firewall.x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EClients sends heartbeats to server at regular intervals (perhaps every 15 mins) so server knows client is still alive.x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EServer is IIS7 with WAS.x3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe solution seems to be duplex netTcpBinding. Based on this information:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://blogs.msdn.com/drnick/archive/2006/05/01/configuring-wcf-for-nats-and-firewalls.aspxx22x3EWCF through firewalls and NATsx3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://blogs.msdn.com/drnick/archive/2006/10/20/keeping-connections-open-in-iis.aspxx22x3EKeeping connections open in IISx3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBut I have yet to find a code sample that works.. Ix27ve tried combining the x22Duplexx22 and x22TcpActivationx22 samples from Microsoftx27s WCF Samples without any luck. Please can someone point me to example code that works, or build a small sample app. Thanks a lot!x3C/px3E',1,2,'hbuxcy1c','2008-08-22 17:27:53'),(22500,'What are the major differences between ANSI C and Kx26R C?','x3Cpx3EThe x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ANSI_Cx22x3EWikipedia article on ANSI Cx3C/ax3E says:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3EOne of the aims of the ANSI C standardization process was to produce a superset of Kx26amp;R C (the first published standard), incorporating many of the unofficial features subsequently introduced. However, the standards committee also included several new features, such as function prototypes (borrowed from the C++ programming language), and a more capable preprocessor. The syntax for parameter declarations was also changed to reflect the C++ style.x3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThat makes me think that there are differences. However, I didnx27t see a comparison between Kx26amp;R C and ANSI C. Is there such a document? If not, what are the major differences?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEDIT: I believe the Kx26amp;R book says x22ANSI Cx22 on the cover. At least I believe the version that I have at home does. So perhaps there isnx27t a difference anymore?x3C/px3E',1,4,'ajan8','2008-08-22 18:29:27'),(22570,'Whatx27s a good way to check if two datetimes are on the same calendar day in TSQL?','x3Cpx3EHere is the issue I am having: I have a large query that needs to compare datetimes in the where clause to see if two dates are on the same day.  My current solution, which sucks, is to send the datetimes into a UDF to convert them to midnight of the same day, and then check those dates for equality.  When it comes to the query plan, this is a disaster, as are almost all UDFs in joins or where clauses.  This is one of the only places in my application that I havenx27t been able to root out the functions and give the query optimizer something it can actually use to locate the best index.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn this case, merging the function code back into the query seems impractical.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI think I am missing something simple here.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHerex27s the function for reference.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eif not exists (select * from dbo.sysobjects \n              where id = object_id(Nx27dbo.f_MakeDatex27) and               \n              type in (Nx27FNx27, Nx27IFx27, Nx27TFx27, Nx27FSx27, Nx27FTx27))\n  exec(x27create function dbo.f_MakeDate() returns int as \n         begin declare @retval int return @retval endx27)\ngo\n\nalter function dbo.f_MakeDate\n(\n    @Day datetime, \n    @Hour int, \n    @Minute int\n)\nreturns datetime\nas\n\n/*\n\nCreates a datetime using the year-month-day portion of @Day, and the \n@Hour and @Minute provided\n\n*/\n\nbegin\n\ndeclare @retval datetime\nset @retval = cast(\n    cast(datepart(m, @Day) as varchar(2)) + \n    x27/x27 + \n    cast(datepart(d, @Day) as varchar(2)) + \n    x27/x27 + \n    cast(datepart(yyyy, @Day) as varchar(4)) + \n    x27 x27 + \n    cast(@Hour as varchar(2)) + \n    x27:x27 + \n    cast(@Minute as varchar(2)) as datetime)\nreturn @retval\nend\n\ngo\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ETo complicate matters, I am joining on time zone tables to check the date against the local time, which could be different for every row:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ewhere \ndbo.f_MakeDate(dateadd(hh, tz.Offset + \n    case when ds.LocalTimeZone is not null \n    then 1 else 0 end, t.TheDateINeedToCheck), 0, 0) = @activityDateMidnight\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3E[Edit]x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m incorporating @Toddx27s suggestion:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ewhere datediff(day, dateadd(hh, tz.Offset + \n    case when ds.LocalTimeZone is not null \n    then 1 else 0 end, t.TheDateINeedToCheck), @ActivityDate) = 0\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy misconception about how datediff works (the same day of year in consecutive years yields 366, not 0 as I expected) caused me to waste a lot of effort.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBut the query plan didnx27t change.  I think I need to go back to the drawing board with the whole thing.x3C/px3E',1,8,'rdowdellz','2008-08-22 18:53:47'),(22590,'How do I cluster an upload folder with ASP.Net?','x3Cpx3EWe have a situation where users are allowed to upload content, and then separately make some changes, then submit a form based on those changes.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis works fine in a single-server, non-failover environment, however we would like some sort of solution for sharing the files between servers that supports failover.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHas anyone run into this in the past?  And what kind of solutions were you able to develop?  Obviously persisting to the database is one option, but wex27d prefer to avoid that.x3C/px3E',1,6,'aauger2','2008-08-22 19:02:06'),(22720,'Configure a Java Socket to fail-fast on disconnect?','x3Cpx3EI have a listening port on my server that Ix27m connecting to using a Java class and the x3Ccodex3ESocketx3C/codex3E interface, i.e.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3ESocket mySocket = new Socket(host,port);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI then grab an x3Ccodex3EOutputStreamx3C/codex3E, decorate with a x3Ccodex3EPrintWriterx3C/codex3E in autoflush mode and Ix27m laughing - except if the listening port closes. Then I get x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Etcp4       0      0  *.9999                 *.*                    LISTEN\ntcp        0      0  127.0.0.1.45737        127.0.0.1.9999         CLOSE_WAIT\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Eand I canx27t seem to detect the problem in the program - Ix27ve tried using the x3Ccodex3EisConnected()x3C/codex3E method on the socket but it doesnx27t seem to know that the connection is closed.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI want to be aware of the problem the next time I try and write to the Socket so that I can try and reconnect and report the issue.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny advice please?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThanks allx3C/px3E',1,8,'hschade12','2008-08-22 19:58:13'),(22880,'What is the best way to prevent session hijacking?','x3Cpx3ESpecifically this is regarding when using a client session cookie to identify a session on the server.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs the best answer to use SSL/HTTPS encryption for the entire web site, and you have the best guarantee that no man in the middle attacks will be able to sniff an existing client session cookie?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnd perhaps second best to use some sort of encryption on the session value itself that is stored in your session cookie?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIf a malicious user has physical access to a machine, they can still look at the filesystem to retrieve a valid session cookie and use that to hijack a session?x3C/px3E',1,6,'cribbens4','2008-08-22 21:02:26'),(22980,'Acts-as-readable Rails plugin Issue','x3Cpx3EIx27m using Intrideax27s x3Ca href=x22http://www.intridea.com/2008/2/29/acts-as-readable-drop-in-mark-as-read-functionalityx22x3EActs as Readablex3C/ax3E Rails plugin for a messaging system Ix27m currently building.\nIx27ve defined my message class accordingly:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eclass Post x26lt; ActiveRecord::Base\n  acts-as-readable\nend\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnd everything seems to be working according to plan, but when trying to execute to show unread messages in my message view, Ix27m running into problems.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ETheir example: (Ix27ve changed underscores to hyphens due to formatting issues)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ebob = User.find_by_name(x22bobx22)\n\nbob.readings                      # =x26gt; []\n\nPost.find_unread_by(bob)          # =x26gt; [x26lt;Post 1x26gt;,x26lt;Post 2x26gt;,x26lt;Post 3x26gt;...]\nPost.find_read_by(bob)            # =x26gt; []\n\nPost.find(1).read_by?(bob)        # =x26gt; false\nPost.find(1).read_by!(bob)        # =x26gt; x26lt;Reading 1x26gt;\nPost.find(1).read_by?(bob)        # =x26gt; true\nPost.find(1).users_who_read       # =x26gt; [x26lt;User bobx26gt;]\n\nPost.find_unread_by(bob)          # =x26gt; [x26lt;Post 2x26gt;,x26lt;Post 3x26gt;...]\nPost.find_read_by(bob)            # =x26gt; [x26lt;Post 1x26gt;]\n\nbob.readings                      # =x26gt; [x26lt;Reading 1x26gt;]\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo it seems as though if I wanted to list the number of unread messages sitting in a mailbox (for example Inbox (39) ), I should be able to do something like:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ex26lt;%= Post.find_unread_by(current-user).count %x26gt;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBut to no avail.  I always seem to get stuck on the simple view issues after everythingx27s set.\nAny ideas?x3C/px3E',1,1,'awrefford16','2008-08-22 21:37:51'),(23190,'How Does One Sum Dimensions of an Array Specified at Run-Time?','x3Cpx3EI am working on a function to establish the entropy of a distribution.  It uses a copula, if any are familiar with that.  I need to sum up the values in the array based on which dimensions are x22cared about.x22x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EExample:  Consider the following example... x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3E\nDimension 0 (across)\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _\n|_ 0 _|_ 0 _|_ 0 _|_ 2 _|  Dimension 1\n|_ 1 _|_ 0 _|_ 2 _|_ 0 _|   (down)\n|_ 0 _|_ 3 _|_ 0 _|_ 6 _|\n|_ 0 _|_ 0 _|_ 0 _|_ 0 _|\n\nI x22care aboutx22 dimension 0 only, and x22donx27t carex22 about the rest (dim 1).\nSumming this array with the above specifications will\nx22collapsex22 the x22stacksx22 of dimension 1 down to a single 4 x 1 array:\n\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ \n|_ 1 _|_ 3 _|_ 2 _|_ 8 _|\n\nThis can then be summed, or have any operation performed.\nx3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI need to do this with an array of x27nx27 dimensions, which could feasibly be 20. Also, I need to be able to do this, caring about certain dimensions, and collapsing the rest.  I am having an especially hard time with this because I cant visualize 20 dimensions :p . If anyone could help me set up some c/c++ code to collapse/sum, I would be very very grateful.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Ch3x3EUpdate:x3C/h3x3E\n\nx3Cpx3EJust got home.  Here is some info to answer your questions:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Colx3E\nx3Clix3ESorry for rolling back the edits, I was hoping when I clicked roll-back it would show me the changes so I could see what I messed up, a bit like wikipedia.  This wasnx27t the case, as I found out.x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3E@jeff - What doesnt make sense?  I am using this great service for (what I think is) a legit reason.  I want to get better at my hobby, which is all it is, as I am in high school.  Many of my posts regard implementing a genetic algorithm (This post, sparsearray, rank an array, pointer manipulation).x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EI am using a sparse array representation, as it is possible to exceed the number of molecules in the universe using a traditional (dense) array.  For now, the implementation of the sparsearray itself doesnt matter a whole lot, as I am working to make it work with a standard array before going to a sparse representation.  For those who havent seen my previous questions, I am using a binary search tree as the structure to contain the sparse array points, and a x22driverx22 function to traverse the tree as necessary, returning whatever the function is designed to do.  This is flexible, so I can accomodate a lot of different methods of accessing the array. x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EThe structure is a hypercube, and the number of dimensions is specified at run time, as well as the length of each dimension (which are all the same, as it is a hypercube).x3C/lix3E\nx3C/olx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThanks everyone for your imput.x3C/px3E',1,9,'nivakhnov17','2008-08-22 22:56:04'),(23250,'When do you use the x22thisx22 keyword?','x3Cpx3EI was curious about how other people use the x3Cstrongx3Ethisx3C/strongx3E keyword. I tend to use it in constructors, but I may also use it throughout the class in other methods. Some examples:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn a constructor:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Epublic Light(Vector v)\n{\n    this.dir = new Vector(v);\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EElsewherex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Epublic void SomeMethod()\n{\n    Vector vec = new Vector();\n    double d = (vec * vec) - (this.radius * this.radius);\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E',1,1,'awrefford16','2008-08-22 23:21:25'),(23270,'How IE7 determines a sitex27s Security Zone','x3Cpx3EDoes anyone know how IE7 determines what Security Zone to use for a site?  I see the basics for IE6 x3Ca href=x22http://www.microsoft.com/technet/prodtechnol/ie/reskit/6/default.mspx?mfr=truex22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Eherex3C/ax3E, but I canx27t find the equivalent for IE7.x3C/px3E',1,5,'sspindlerw','2008-08-22 23:28:00'),(23310,'Source Control Beginners','x3Cpx3EWhat would be the best version control system to learn as a beginner to source control?x3C/px3E',1,9,'osilley7','2008-08-22 23:49:05'),(23370,'Notification of drop in drag-drop in Windows','x3Cpx3EMy C# program has a list of files that can be dragged from it and dropped into another program. My requirements are that the file be copied to a different directory first.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo, can I be notified of the drop operation so that I can only copy the file if operation succeeds? Ix27d rather wait till I know it needs to be copied before actually performing the copy.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAlso, is it possible to know what program the drop operation is occurring in? Ideally Ix27d like to alter the filepath based on who or what its being dropped.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe solution to this can be in any .NET language or C/C++ with COM.x3C/px3E',1,7,'gdodding5','2008-08-23 00:16:42'),(23490,'What is your best list of x27must havex27 development tools?','x3Cpx3EI recently burned up my development laptop (it literally emitted smoke from the vents). After pulling the hd I was unable to get it to spin with a USB device attached to a home tower. Since I was on a deadline I had to rush and buy a new laptop (Turion 64 x2) running Vista.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAfter I installed my required applications VS2005/2008, Sql Server editions client tools, Adobe CS3, and source control clients: x3Cstrongx3EI am wondering what list of “must haves” developer tools that are out there these days?x3C/strongx3E I’m a big fan of Fiddler and LinqPad, but I am wondering what I am missing?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3E[edit]I read the other question here and I am aware of Hanselmanx27s list. I was not specific enough in my original question. By x22these daysx22 I meant new and latest tools (perhaps available only 64 bit), which in geek years might just be 12 days, I dunno. :)[/edit]x3C/px3E',1,3,'abaterb','2008-08-23 01:08:32'),(23610,'Windows / Active Directory - User / Groups','x3Cpx3EIx27m looking for a way to find a the windows login associated with a specific group. Ix27m trying to add permissions to a tool that only allows names formatted like:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EDOMAIN\\USER \nDOMAIN\\GROUP\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have a list of users in active directory format that I need to add:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eou=group1;ou=group2;ou=group3\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have tried adding DOMAIN\\Group1, but I get a x27user not foundx27 error.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EP.S.  should also be noted that Ix27m not a Lan admin x3C/px3E',1,1,'jsorel9','2008-08-23 01:54:34'),(23620,'What Javascript rich text editor will not break the browserx27s spellcheck?','x3Cpx3EIx27m using TinyMCE in an ASP.Net project, and I need a spell check. The only TinyMCE plugins Ix27ve found use PHP on the server side, and I guess I could just break down and install PHP on my server and do that, but quite frankly, what a pain. I donx27t want to do that.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAs it turns out, Firefoxx27s built-in spell check will work fine for me, but it doesnx27t seem to work on TinyMCE editor boxes. Ix27ve enabled the gecko_spellcheck option, which is supposed to fix it, but it doesnx27t.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDoes anybody know of a nice rich-text editor that doesnx27t break the browserx27s spell check?x3C/px3E',1,5,'aauger2','2008-08-23 02:03:03'),(23640,'Free or Open Source Collaboration/eLearning Software','x3Cpx3EI am looking for open source or free data collaboration software. Specifically this is for a non-profit organization that wants to teach remote students how a foreign language.  The idea is that an instructor would teach a class and there would be up to 10 students in the class at a time.  The instructor would be able to post slides or other teaching material and the students would be able to see it on their computers remotely.  Video is not required but audio is a must.  Any recommendations?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAlso if there have been any reviews or feature comparison amongst these products, I would be interested in hearing about them.x3C/px3E',1,3,'civakhnop','2008-08-23 02:13:06'),(23770,'Good strategy for leaving an audit trail/change history for DB applications?','x3Cpx3EWhat are some strategies that people have had success with for maintaining a change history for data in a fairly complex database. One of the applications that I frequently use and develop for could really benefit from a more comprehensive way of tracking how records have changed over time. For instance, right now records can have a number of timestamp and modified user fields, but we currently donx27t have a scheme for logging multiple change, for instance if an operation is rolled back. In a perfect world, it would be possible to reconstruct the record as it was after each save, etc.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESome info on the DB:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3ENeeds to have the capacity to grow by thousands of records per weekx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3E50-60 Tablesx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EMain revisioned tables may have several million records eachx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EReasonable amount of foreign keys and indexes setx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EUsing PostgreSQL 8.xx3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E',1,5,'srm9547','2008-08-23 04:05:58'),(23930,'Factorial Algorithms in different languages','x3Cpx3EI want to see all the different ways you can come up with, for a factorial subroutine, or program. The hope is that anyone can come here and see if they might want to learn a new language.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Ch2x3EIdeas:x3C/h2x3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3EProceduralx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EFunctionalx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EObject Orientedx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EOne linersx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EObfuscatedx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EOddballx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EBad Codex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polyglot_%28computing%29x22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EPolyglotx3C/ax3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBasically I want to see an example, of different ways of writing an algorithm, and what they would look like in different languages.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EPlease limit it to one example per entry.\nI will allow you to have more than one example per answer, if you are trying to highlight a specific style, language, or just a well thought out idea that lends itself to being in one post.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe only real requirement is it must find the factorial of a given argument, in all languages represented.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Ch1x3EBe Creative!x3C/h1x3E\n\nx3Ch2x3ERecommended Guideline:x3C/h2x3E\n\nx3Cprex3E\n# Language Name: Optional Style type\n\n   - Optional bullet points\n\n    Code Goes Here\n\nOther informational text goes here\nx3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI will ocasionally go along and edit any answer that does not have decent formatting.x3C/px3E',1,11,'astarmoreq','2008-08-23 07:46:32'),(23950,'Best method to get objects from a BlockingQueue in a concurrent program?','x3Cpx3EWhat is the best method to get objects out of a BlockingQueue, in a concurrent program, without hitting a race condition?  Ix27m currently doing the following and Ix27m not convinced it is the best method:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EBlockingQueuex26lt;Violationx26gt; vQueue;\n/* \nin the constructor I pass in a BlockingQueue object \nfull of violations that need to be processed - cut out for brevity\n*/\n\nViolation v;\nwhile ( ( v = vQueue.poll(500, TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS) ) != null ) {\n    // do stuff with the violation\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have yet to hit a race condition... but, Ix27m none too sure if this is truly safe.x3C/px3E',1,11,'civakhnop','2008-08-23 08:03:18'),(23970,'How do I marshal a lambda (Proc) in Ruby?','x3Cpx3EJoe Van Dyk x3Ca href=x22http://www.zenspider.com/pipermail/ruby/2008-August/004223.htmlx22x3Easked the Ruby mailing listx3C/ax3E:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3EHi,x3C/px3E\n  \n  x3Cpx3EIn Ruby, I guess you canx27t marshal a lambda/proc object, right?  Is\n  that possible in lisp or other languages?x3C/px3E\n  \n  x3Cpx3EWhat I was trying to do:x3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3El = lamda { ... }\nBj.submit x22/path/to/ruby/programx22, :stdin =x26gt; Marshal.dump(l)\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3ESo, Ix27m sending BackgroundJob a lambda object, which contains the\n  context/code for what to do.  But, guess that wasnx27t possible.  I\n  ended up marshaling a normal ruby object that contained instructions\n  for what to do after the program ran.x3C/px3E\n  \n  x3Cpx3EJoex3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E',1,1,'erowcliffe1d','2008-08-23 08:22:44'),(24040,'Is there a site for detailed unit testing samples?','x3Cpx3EIs there a site for unit testing as x3Ca href=x22http://refactormycode.com/x22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3ERefactorMyCodex3C/ax3E for refactoring? I think it would be a great help for beginners like me.x3C/px3E',1,10,'mschafflere','2008-08-23 10:33:08'),(24130,'Classes vs 2D arrays','x3Cpx3EWhich is better to use in PHP, a 2D array or a class? Ix27ve included an example of what I mean by this.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E// Using a class\nclass someClass\n{\n    public  $name;\n    public  $height;\n    public  $weight;\n\n    function __construct($name, $height, $weight)\n    {\n        $this -x26gt; name       = $name;\n        $this -x26gt; height = $height;\n        $this -x26gt; weight = $weight;\n    }\n}\n\n$classArray[1] = new someClass(x27Bobx27, 10, 20);\n$classArray[2] = new someClass(x27Fredx27, 15, 10);\n$classArray[3] = new someClass(x27Nedx27, 25, 30);\n\n\n// Using a 2D array\n$normalArray[1][x27namex27] = x27Bobx27;\n$normalArray[1][x27heightx27]   = 10;\n$normalArray[1][x27weightx27]   = 20;\n\n$normalArray[2][x27namex27] = x27Fredx27;\n$normalArray[2][x27heightx27]   = 15;\n$normalArray[2][x27weightx27]   = 10;\n\n$normalArray[3][x27namex27] = x27Nedx27;\n$normalArray[3][x27heightx27]   = 25;\n$normalArray[3][x27weightx27]   = 30;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAssuming that somebody doesnx27t come out and show that classes are too slow, it looks like class wins.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve not idea which answer I should accept to Ix27ve just upvoted all of them.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnd I have now written two near identical pages, one using the 2D array (written before this question was posted) and now one using a class and I must say that the class produces much nicer code. I have no idea how much overhead is going to be generated but I doubt it will rival the improvement to the code itself.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThank you for helping to make me a better programmer.x3C/px3E',1,2,'chenburyh','2008-08-23 14:41:36'),(24200,'Whatx27s the fastest way to bulk insert a lot of data in SQL Server (C# client)','x3Cpx3EI am hitting some performance bottlenecks with my C# client inserting bulk data into a SQL Server 2005 database and Ix27m looking for ways in which to speed up the process.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI am already using the SqlClient.SqlBulkCopy (which is based on TDS) to speed up the data transfer across the wire which helped a lot, but Ix27m still looking for more.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have a simple table that looks like this: x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E CREATE TABLE [BulkData](\n [ContainerId] [int] NOT NULL,\n [BinId] [smallint] NOT NULL,\n [Sequence] [smallint] NOT NULL,\n [ItemId] [int] NOT NULL,\n [Left] [smallint] NOT NULL,\n [Top] [smallint] NOT NULL,\n [Right] [smallint] NOT NULL,\n [Bottom] [smallint] NOT NULL,\n CONSTRAINT [PKBulkData] PRIMARY KEY CLUSTERED \n (\n  [ContainerIdId] ASC,\n  [BinId] ASC,\n  [Sequence] ASC\n))\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m inserting data in chunks that average about 300 rows where ContainerId and BinId are constant in each chunk and the Sequence value is 0-n and the values are pre-sorted based on the primary key.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe %Disk time performance counter spends a lot of time at 100% so it is clear that disk IO is the main issue but the speeds Ix27m getting are several orders of magnitude below a raw file copy.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDoes it help any if I:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Colx3E\nx3Clix3EDrop the Primary key while I am doing the inserting and recreate it laterx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EDo inserts into a temporary table with the same schema and periodically transfer them into the main table to keep the size of the table where insertions are happening smallx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EAnything else?x3C/lix3E\nx3C/olx3E\n\nx3Cpx3E--\nBased on the responses I have gotten, let me clarify a little bit:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EPortman: Ix27m using a clustered index because when the data is all imported I will need to access data sequentially in that order.  I donx27t particularly need the index to be there while importing the data.  Is there any advantage to having a nonclustered PK index while doing the inserts as opposed to dropping the constraint entirely for import?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EChopeen:  The data is being generated remotely on many other machines (my SQL server can only handle about 10 currently, but I would love to be able to add more).  Itx27s not practical to run the entire process on the local machine because it would then have to process 50 times as much input data to generate the output.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EJason: I am not doing any concurrent queries against the table during the import process, I will try dropping the primary key and see if that helps.x3C/px3E',1,11,'aa9279','2008-08-23 16:53:09'),(24270,'Whatx27s the point of OOP?','x3Cpx3EAs far as I can tell, in spite of the countless millions or billions spent on OOP education, languages, and tools, OOP has not improved developer productivity or software reliability, nor has it reduced development costs. Few people use OOP in any rigorous sense (few people adhere to or understand principles such as LSP); there seems to be little uniformity or consistency to the approaches that people take to modelling problem domains.  All too often, the class is used simply for its syntactic sugar; it puts the functions for a record type into their own little namespace.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve written a large amount of code for a wide variety of applications. Although there have been places where true substitutable subtyping played a valuable role in the application, these have been pretty exceptional. In general, though much lip service is given to talk of x22re-usex22 the reality is that unless a piece of code does x3Cemx3Eexactlyx3C/emx3E what you want it to do, therex27s very little cost-effective x22re-usex22.  Itx27s extremely hard to design classes to be extensible x3Cemx3Ein the right wayx3C/emx3E, and so the cost of extension is normally so great that x22re-usex22 simply isnx27t worthwhile.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn many regards, this doesnx27t surprise me.  The real world isnx27t x22OOx22, and the idea implicit in OO--that we can model things with some class taxonomy--seems to me very fundamentally flawed (I can sit on a table, a tree stump, a car bonnet, someonex27s lap--but not one of those is-a chair).  Even if we move to more abstract domains, OO modelling is often difficult, counterintuitive, and ultimately unhelpful (consider the classic examples of circles/ellipses or squares/rectangles).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo what am I missing here? Wherex27s the value of OOP, and why has all the time and money failed to make software any better?x3C/px3E',1,3,'mheyward10','2008-08-23 18:40:28'),(24310,'Programming a simple IRC (Internet-Relay-Chat) Client','x3Cpx3EI started using IRC at a young age, and I have always been fascinated with it.  As a language exercise, I was thinking about programming a simple IRC client in Ruby with x3Ca href=x22http://www.shoooes.net/x22x3EShoesx3C/ax3E as a graphical front-end.  My question to you, kind-sirs, what do I need to become familiar with to start on this great adventure (besides shoes and Ruby of course)?  I imagine there is some-sort of specification on IRC Protocol.  Any pointers?x3C/px3E',1,7,'tyurkiewicz19','2008-08-23 19:49:06'),(24450,'What are the best MVC web frameworks on the market?','x3Cpx3EI am looking for a Web Framework to move windows based applications to the web.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe main requirements to WF are the following:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Colx3E\nx3Clix3Eunit tests supportx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Edesktop and mobile browsers supportx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Elong term viabilityx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ematurity of the frameworkx3C/lix3E\nx3C/olx3E',1,10,'jsorel9','2008-08-23 22:16:13'),(24470,'SQL Server: Examples of PIVOTing String data','x3Cpx3ETrying to find some simple SQL Server PIVOT examples.  Most of the examples that I have found involve counting or summing up numbers.  I just want to pivot some string data.  For example, I have a query returning the following.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EAction1 VIEW  \nAction1 EDIT  \nAction2 VIEW  \nAction3 VIEW  \nAction3 EDIT  \nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI would like to use PIVOT (if even possible) to make the results like so:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EAction1 VIEW EDIT  \nAction2 VIEW NULL  \nAction3 VIEW EDIT  \nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs this even possible with the PIVOT functionality?x3C/px3E',1,7,'aauger2','2008-08-23 22:36:33'),(24580,'How do you automate a Visual Studio build?','x3Cpx3EHow do you turn a Visual Studio build that youx27d perform in the IDE into a script that you can run from the command line?x3C/px3E',1,9,'itrowla','2008-08-24 00:42:25'),(24610,'Vi editing for Visual Studio','x3Cpx3EIx27m used to the Vi(m) editor and am using MS Visual Studio 2005 at work. I couldnx27t find a free Vi add-in (therex27s only one for the 2003 version). I googled a bit, saw that there was a x27Google summer of 