/malloc was called from, but I have a wrapper for allocations, so a full symbolic stack trace would be best.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe detector would also be able to detect for a leak in both the .exe and its accompanying plug-in .dll modules.x3C/px3E',1,7,'abaterb','2008-08-25 11:31:46'),(25950,'Ruby Performance','x3Cpx3EIx27m pretty keen to develop my first Ruby app, as my company has finally blessed its use internally.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn everything Ix27ve read about Ruby up to v1.8, there is never anything positive said about performance, but Ix27ve found nothing about version 1.9. The last figures I saw about 1.8 had it drastically slower than just about everything out there, so Ix27m hoping this was addressed in 1.9.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHas performance drastically improved? Are there some concrete things that can be done with Ruby apps (or things to avoid) to keep performance at the best possible level?x3C/px3E',1,3,'wscreen1b','2008-08-25 16:34:21'),(26020,'What is the best way to connect and use a sqlite database from C#','x3Cpx3EIx27ve done this before in C++ by including sqlite.h but is there a similarly easy way in C#?x3C/px3E',1,1,'erowcliffe1d','2008-08-25 17:25:44'),(26230,'Revoke shared folders in windows','x3Cpx3EOver the last few months/years, I have shared a folder or two with numerous people on my domain. How do I easily revoke those shares to keep access to my system nice and tidy?x3C/px3E',1,9,'sfitzhenryv','2008-08-25 19:22:19'),(26260,'Asp.net website first start is very slow','x3Cpx3EThe first time I load the website in the production web server, it start very slow, subsequent pages load very quickly (included the home page).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI precompiled the site, but nothing changes. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI donx27t have any code at Application start.\nI donx27t have cached items.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny ideas? How can I find out what is happening?x3C/px3E',1,5,'scurraghy','2008-08-25 19:32:46'),(26450,'Hibernate saveOrUpdate with another object in the session','x3Cpx3EIs there any way to save an object using Hibernate if there is already an object using that identifier loaded into the session?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3EDoing session.contains(obj) seems to only return true if the session contains that exact object, not another object with the same ID.x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EUsing merge(obj) throws an exception if the object is newx3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E',1,2,'dperrenl','2008-08-25 21:25:22'),(26570,'sizeof() equivalent for reference types?','x3Cpx3EIx27m looking for a way to get the size of an instance of a reference type. sizeof is only for value types. Is this possible?x3C/px3E',1,4,'enewberryf','2008-08-25 22:19:57'),(26620,'How to set encoding in .getJSON JQuery','x3Cpx3EIn my web app, I submit some form fields with jQuery x3Ccodex3E$.getJSON()x3C/codex3E Method. I am having some problems with the encoding. The character-set of my app is x3Ccodex3Echarset=ISO-8859-1x3C/codex3E but I think these fields are submitted with x3Ccodex3EUTF-8x3C/codex3E. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDoes anyone know, how I can set encoding in x3Ccodex3E$.getJSONx3C/codex3E calls? x3C/px3E',1,11,'sdally1','2008-08-25 22:45:27'),(26670,'Why is my PDF footer text invisible?','x3Cpx3EIx27m creating PDFs on-demand with ColdFusionx27s x3Ca href=x22http://cfquickdocs.com/cf8/?getDoc=cfdocumentx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3ECFDocumentx3C/ax3E tag, like so:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ex26lt;cfdocument format=x22PDFx22 filename=x22#attributes.fileName#x22 overwrite=x22truex22x26gt;\n    x26lt;cfdocumentitem type=x22footerx22x26gt;\n        x26lt;table border=x220x22 cellpadding=x220x22 cellspacing=x220x22 width=x22100%x22x26gt;\n            x26lt;trx26gt;\n                x26lt;td align=x22leftx22x26gt;x26lt;font face=x22Tahomax22 color=x22blackx22x26gt;x26lt;strongx26gt;My Clientx27s Corporationx26lt;/strongx26gt;x26lt;br/x26gt;Street addressx26lt;br/x26gt;City, ST 55555x26lt;/fontx26gt;x26lt;/tdx26gt;\n                x26lt;td align=x22rightx22x26gt;x26lt;font face=x22Tahomax22 color=x22blackx22x26gt;Phone: 555.555.5555x26lt;br/x26gt;Fax: 555.555.5555x26lt;br/x26gt;Email: info@domain.comx26lt;/fontx26gt;x26lt;/tdx26gt;\n            x26lt;/trx26gt;\n        x26lt;/tablex26gt;\n    x26lt;/cfdocumentitemx26gt;\n    x26lt;htmlx26gt;\n        x26lt;bodyx26gt;\n            x26lt;table border=x220x22 cellpadding=x220x22 cellspacing=x220x22 width=x22100%x22x26gt;\n            x26lt;!--- some content here ... ---x26gt;\n            x26lt;/tablex26gt;\n        x26lt;/bodyx26gt;\n    x26lt;/htmlx26gt;\nx26lt;/cfdocumentx26gt;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe problem Ix27m having is that sometimes (actually, most of the time, but not always) x3Cstrongx3Ex3Cemx3Esomex3C/emx3Ex3C/strongx3E of the footer text is there, but invisible. I can highlight it and copy/paste it into notepad, where I can see it all -- but in the generated PDF only the first line of the left column of the footer is visible, the rest is invisible. Hence why I added the font color of black in the code.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cimg src=x22http://i.stack.imgur.com/LHZ96.pngx22 alt=x22screenshot of problemx22x3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny ideas on how to correct this?x3C/px3E',1,9,'scurraghy','2008-08-25 23:14:07'),(26760,'Parse string to TimeSpan','x3Cpx3EI have some strings of xxh:yym format where xx is hours and yy is minutes like x2205h:30mx22. What is an elegant way to convert a string of this type to TimeSpan?x3C/px3E',1,8,'dmatuszinski15','2008-08-26 00:16:26'),(26800,'XPath and Selecting a single node','x3Cpx3EIx27m using XPath in .NET to parse an XML document, along the lines of:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpre class=x22lang-cs prettyprint-overridex22x3Ex3Ccodex3EXmlNodeList lotsOStuff = doc.SelectNodes(x22//stuffx22);\n\nforeach (XmlNode stuff in lotsOStuff)\n{\n   XmlNode stuffChild = stuff.SelectSingleNode(x22//stuffChildx22);\n   // ... etc\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe issue is that the XPath Query for x3Ccodex3EstuffChildx3C/codex3E is always returning the child of the first x3Ccodex3Estuffx3C/codex3E element, never the rest. Can XPath not be used to query against an individual x3Ccodex3EXMLElementx3C/codex3E?x3C/px3E',1,10,'hginglell13','2008-08-26 00:32:36'),(26860,'Limitations of screen readers','x3Cpx3EIx27m a web developer, and I want to make the web sites I develop more accessible to those using screen readers.  What limitations do screen readers have that I should be most aware of, and what can I do to avoid hitting these limitations.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis question was sparked by reading another question about x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/8472/best-non-image-based-captchax22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Enon-image based captchasx3C/ax3E.  In there, a commenter said that honey pot form fields (form fields hidden with CSS that only a bot would fill in), are a bad idea, because screen readers would still pick them up. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAre screen readers really so primitive that they would read text that isnx27t even displayed on the screen?  Ideally, couldnx27t you make a screen reader that waited until the page was finished loading, applied all css, and even ran Javascript onload functions before it figured out what was actually displayed, and then read that off to the user?  You could probably even identify parts of the page that are menus or table of contents, and give some sort of easy way for those parts to be read exclusively or skipped over. I would think that the programming community could come up with a better solution to this problem.  x3C/px3E',1,4,'mlowried','2008-08-26 00:51:33'),(27020,'Alternating coloring groups of rows in Excel','x3Cpx3EI have an Excel Spreadsheet like thisx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3E\nid | data for id\n   | more data for id\nid | data for id\nid | data for id\n   | more data for id\n   | even more data for id\nid | data for id\n   | more data for id\nid | data for id\nid | data for id\n   | more data for id\nx3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENow I want to group the data of one id by alternating the background color of the rowsx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3E\nvar color = white\nfor each row\n    if the first cell is not empty and color is white\n        set color to green\n    if the first cell is not empty and color is green\n        set color to white\n    set background of row to color\nx3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECan anyone help me with a macro or some VBA codex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThanksx3C/px3E',1,9,'scurraghy','2008-08-26 02:11:30'),(27030,'Comparing Arrays of Objects in JavaScript','x3Cpx3EI want to compare 2 arrays of objects in JavaScript code.  The objects have 8 total properties, but each object will not have a value for each, and the arrays are never going to be any larger than 8 items each, so maybe the brute force method of traversing each and then looking at the values of the 8 properties is the easiest way to do what I want to do, but before implementing, I wanted to see if anyone had a more elegant solution. Any thoughts?x3C/px3E',1,1,'ajan8','2008-08-26 02:15:21'),(27220,'How to convert std::string to LPCWSTR in C++ (Unicode)','x3Cpx3EIx27m looking for a method, or a code snippet for converting std::string to LPCWSTRx3C/px3E',1,5,'kgrenkovu','2008-08-26 05:46:31'),(27240,'Why arenx27t Enumerations Iterable?','x3Cpx3EIn Java 5 and above you have the foreach loop, which works magically on anything that implements x3Ccodex3EIterablex3C/codex3E:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Efor (Object o : list) {\n  doStuff(o);\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHowever, x3Ccodex3EEnumerablex3C/codex3E still does not implement x3Ccodex3EIterablex3C/codex3E, meaning that to iterate over an x3Ccodex3EEnumerationx3C/codex3E you must do the following:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Efor(; e.hasMoreElements() ;) {\n  doStuff(e.nextElement());\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDoes anyone know if there is a reason why x3Ccodex3EEnumerationx3C/codex3E still does not implement x3Ccodex3EIterablex3C/codex3E?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EEdit:x3C/strongx3E As a clarification, Ix27m not talking about the language concept of an x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enumerated_typex22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Eenumx3C/ax3E, Ix27m talking a Java-specific class in the Java API called x27x3Ca href=x22http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/docs/api/java/util/Enumeration.htmlx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EEnumerationx3C/ax3Ex27. x3C/px3E',1,11,'ajan8','2008-08-26 05:57:51'),(27570,'Find number of files with a specific extension, in all subdirectories','x3Cpx3EIs there a way to find the number of files of a specific type without having to loop through all results inn a Directory.GetFiles() or similar method? I am looking for something like this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eint ComponentCount = MagicFindFileCount(@x22c:\\windows\\system32x22, x22*.dllx22);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI know that I can make a recursive function to call Directory.GetFiles , but it would be much cleaner if I could do this without all the iterating.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EEDIT:x3C/strongx3E If it is not possible to do this without recursing and iterating yourself, what would be the best way to do it?x3C/px3E',1,8,'srm9547','2008-08-26 12:42:25'),(27610,'How to add (simple) tracing in C#?','x3Cpx3EI want to introduce some tracing to a C# application I am writing. Sadly, I can never really remember how it works and would like a tutorial with reference qualities to check up on every now and then. It should include:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3EApp.config / Web.config stuff to add for registering TraceListenersx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ehow to set it up in the calling applicationx3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDo you know the uber tutorial that we should link to?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EEDIT:x3C/strongx3E Glenn Slaven pointed me in the right direction. Add this to your App.config/Web.config inside x3Ccodex3Ex26lt;configuration/x26gt;x3C/codex3E:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ex26lt;system.diagnosticsx26gt;\n    x26lt;trace autoflush=x22truex22x26gt;\n      x26lt;listenersx26gt;\n        x26lt;add type=x22System.Diagnostics.TextWriterTraceListenerx22 name=x22TextWriterx22\n             initializeData=x22trace.logx22 /x26gt;\n      x26lt;/listenersx26gt;\n    x26lt;/tracex26gt;\nx26lt;/system.diagnosticsx26gt;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis will add a x3Ccodex3ETextWriterTraceListenerx3C/codex3E that will catch everything you send to with x3Ccodex3ETrace.WriteLinex3C/codex3E etc.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EEDIT:x3C/strongx3E @DanEsparza pointed out that you should use x3Ccodex3ETrace.TraceInformationx3C/codex3E, x3Ccodex3ETrace.TraceWarningx3C/codex3E and x3Ccodex3ETrace.TraceErrorx3C/codex3E instead of x3Ccodex3ETrace.WriteLinex3C/codex3E, as they allow you to format messages the same way as x3Ccodex3Estring.Formatx3C/codex3E.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3ETip:x3C/strongx3E If you donx27t add any listeners, then you can still see the trace output with the SysInternals program DebugView (x3Ccodex3EDbgview.exex3C/codex3E): x3Ca href=x22http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/sysinternals/bb896647.aspxx22x3Ehttp://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/sysinternals/bb896647.aspxx3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E',1,6,'dmatuszinski15','2008-08-26 13:12:56'),(27640,'Integrating Qt into legacy MFC applications','x3Cpx3EWe currently maintain a suit of MFC applications that are fairly well designed, however the user interface is beginning to look tired and a lot of the code is in need quite a bit of refactoring to tidy up some duplication and/or performance problems.  We make use of quite a few custom controls that handle all their own drawing (all written using MFC).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ERecently Ix27ve been doing more research into Qt and the benefits it provides (cross-platform and supports what you might call a more x22professionalx22 looking framework for UI development).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy question is - x3Cstrongx3Ewhat would be the best approach to perhaps moving to the Qt frameworkx3C/strongx3E?  Does Qt play nice with MFC?  Would it be better to start porting some of our custom controls to Qt and gradually integrate more and more into our existing MFC apps? (is this possible?).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny advice or previous experience is appreciated.x3C/px3E',1,2,'abaterb','2008-08-26 13:37:52'),(27670,'Microsoft .Net framework 3.5 SP1 Setup Fails','x3Cpx3EOn my Vista machine I cannot install the .Net framework 3.5 SP1. Setup ends few moments after ending the download of the required files, stating in the log that: x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E[08/26/08,09:46:11] Microsoft .NET Framework 2.0SP1 (CBS): [2] Error: Installation failed for component Microsoft .NET Framework 2.0SP1 (CBS). MSI returned error code 1\n[08/26/08,09:46:13] WapUI: [2] DepCheck indicates Microsoft .NET Framework 2.0SP1 (CBS) is not installed.\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EFirst thing I did was trying to install 2.0 SP1, but this time setup states that the x22product is not supported on Vista systemx22. Uhm.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe real big problem is that this setup fails also when it is called by the Visual Studio 2008 SP1.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENow, I searched the net for this, but Ix27m not finding a real solution... Any idea / hint? Did anybody have problems during SP1 install?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThanksx3C/px3E',1,4,'rdowdellz','2008-08-26 14:01:56'),(27700,'C++ : Opening a file in non exclusive mode','x3Cpx3EI have to develop an application which parses a log file and sends specific data to a server. It has to run on both Linux and Windows. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe problem appears when I want to test the log rolling system (which appends .1 to the name of the creates a new one with the same name). On Windows (havenx27t tested yet on Linux) I canx27t rename a file that I have opened with std::ifstream() (exclusive access?) even if I open it in x22input modex22 (ios::in).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there a cross-platform way to open file in a non-exclusive way?x3C/px3E',1,3,'clawrence3','2008-08-26 14:24:10'),(27850,'What are models for storing tree structures and what are their characteristics?','x3Cpx3ESo far I have encountered adjacency list, nested sets and nested intervals as models for storing tree structures in a database. I know these well enough and have migrated trees from one to another.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat are other popular models? What are their characteristics? What are good resources (books, web, etc) on this topic?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m not only looking for db storage but would like to expand my knowledge on trees in general. For example, I understand that nested sets/intervals are especially favorable for relational database storage and have asked myself, are they actually a x3Cix3Ebadx3C/ix3E choice in other contexts?x3C/px3E',1,3,'dperrenl','2008-08-26 16:11:05'),(27910,'Finding a DOI in a document or page','x3Cpx3EThe x3Ca href=x22http://doi.org/x22x3EDOIx3C/ax3E system places basically no useful limitations on what constitutes x3Ca href=x22http://doi.org/handbook_2000/enumeration.html#2.2x22x3Ea reasonable identifierx3C/ax3E. However, being able to pull DOIs out of PDFs, web pages, etc. is quite useful for citation information, etc.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there a reliable way to identify a DOI in a block of text without assuming the x27doi:x27 prefix? (any language acceptable, regexes preferred, and avoiding false positives a must)x3C/px3E',1,8,'rdowdellz','2008-08-26 16:37:33'),(28080,'How bad is dynamic casting?','x3Cpx3EWe often hear/read that one should avoid dynamic casting. I was wondering what would be x27good usex27 examples of it, according to you?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEdit:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EYes, Ix27m aware of x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/28002/regular-cast-vs-staticcast-vs-dynamiccastx22x3Ethat other threadx3C/ax3E: it is indeed when reading one of the first answers there that I asked my question!x3C/px3E',1,2,'wscreen1b','2008-08-26 17:49:47'),(28110,'SQL Server DateTime conversion failure','x3Cpx3EI have a large table with 1 million+ records. Unfortunately, the person who created the table decided to put dates in a x3Ccodex3Evarchar(50)x3C/codex3E field.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI need to do a simple date comparison -x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Edatediff(dd, convert(datetime, lastUpdate, 100), getDate()) x26lt; 31\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBut it fails on the x3Ccodex3Econvert()x3C/codex3E:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EConversion failed when converting datetime from character string.\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EApparently there is something in that field it doesnx27t like, and since there are so many records, I canx27t tell just by looking at it. How can I properly sanitize the entire date field so it does not fail on the x3Ccodex3Econvert()x3C/codex3E? Here is what I have now:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eselect count(*)\nfrom MyTable\nwhere\n    isdate(lastUpdate) x26gt; 0\n    and datediff(dd, convert(datetime, lastUpdate, 100), getDate()) x26lt; 31\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/28110/ms-sql-datetime-conversion-failure#28209x22x3E@SQLMenacex3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m not concerned about performance in this case. This is going to be a one time query. Changing the table to a datetime field is not an option.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/28110/ms-sql-datetime-conversion-failure#28139x22x3E@Jon Limjapx3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve tried adding the third argument, and it makes no difference.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/28110/ms-sql-datetime-conversion-failure#28209x22x3E@SQLMenacex3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3EThe problem is most likely how the data is stored, there are only two safe formats; ISO YYYYMMDD; ISO 8601 yyyy-mm-dd Thh:mm:ss:mmm (no spaces)x3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWouldnx27t the x3Ccodex3Eisdate()x3C/codex3E check take care of this?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI donx27t have a need for 100% accuracy. I just want to get most of the records that are from the last 30 days.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/28110/ms-sql-datetime-conversion-failure#28209x22x3E@SQLMenacex3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eselect isdate(x2720080131x27) -- returns 1\nselect isdate(x2701312008x27) -- returns 0\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/28110/ms-sql-datetime-conversion-failure#28209x22x3E@Brian Schkerkex3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3EPlace the CASE and ISDATE inside the CONVERT() function.x3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThanks! That did it.x3C/px3E',1,2,'wscreen1b','2008-08-26 18:01:43'),(28150,'Create an Attribute to Break the Build','x3Cpx3EOK, this kind of follows on from x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/27758/notify-developer-of-a-do-not-use-methodx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Emy previous questionx3C/ax3E.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat I would really like to do is create some sort of attribute which allows me to decorate a method that will x3Cstrongx3Ebreak the buildx3C/strongx3E. Much like the x3Cemx3EObsolete(x22reasonx22, true)x3C/emx3E attribute, but without falsely identifying obsolete code.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3ETo clarifyx3C/strongx3E: I dont want it to break the build on x3Cemx3EANYx3C/emx3E F6 (Build) press, I only want it to break the build if a method decorated with the attribute is called somewhere else in the code. Like I said, x3Cemx3Esimilarx3C/emx3E to obsolete, but not the same.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI know I am not alone in this, since x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/27758/notify-developer-of-a-do-not-use-method#27796x22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Eother users want to use it for other reasonsx3C/ax3E. I have never created custom attributes before so it is all new to me!x3C/px3E',1,1,'aillidges','2008-08-26 18:15:08'),(28160,'Multiple classes in a header file vs. a single header file per class','x3Cpx3EFor whatever reason, our company has a coding guideline that states:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ccodex3EEach class shall have itx27s own header and implementation file.x3C/codex3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo if we wrote a class called x3Ccodex3EMyStringx3C/codex3E we would need an associated x3Cstrongx3EMyStringh.hx3C/strongx3E and x3Cstrongx3EMyString.cxxx3C/strongx3E.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDoes anyone else do this?  Has anyone seen any compiling performance repercussions as a result?  Does 5000 classes in 10000 files compile just as quickly as 5000 classes in 2500 files?  If not, is the difference noticeable?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3E[We code C++ and use GCC 3.4.4 as our everyday compiler]x3C/px3E',1,7,'aa9279','2008-08-26 18:19:34'),(28280,'Can I maintain state between calls to a SQL Server UDF?','x3Cpx3EI have a SQL script that inserts data (via INSERT statements currently numbering in the thousands) One of the columns contains a unique identifier (though not an IDENTITY type, just a plain olx27 int) thatx27s actually unique across a few different tables. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27d like to add a scalar function to my script that gets the next available ID (i.e. last used ID + 1) but Ix27m not sure this is possible because there doesnx27t seem to be a way to use a global or static variable from within a UDF, I canx27t use a temp table, and I canx27t update a permanent table from within a function. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECurrently my script looks like this: x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3E\n   declare @v_baseID int \n   exec dbo.getNextID @v_baseID out  --sproc to get the next available id\n   --Lots of these - where n is a hardcoded value\n   insert into tableOfStuff (someStuff, uniqueID) values (x27stuffx27, @v_baseID + n ) \n   exec dbo.UpdateNextID @v_baseID + lastUsedn  --sproc to update the last used id\nx3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBut I would like it to look like this: x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3E\n   --Lots of these\n   insert into tableOfStuff (someStuff, uniqueID) values (x27stuffx27, getNextID() ) \nx3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHardcoding the offset is a pain in the arse, and is error prone.  Packaging it up into a simple scalar function is very appealing, but Ix27m starting to think it canx27t be done that way since there doesnx27t seem to be a way to maintain the offset counter between calls.  Is that right, or is there something Ix27m missing.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWex27re using SQL Server 2005 at the moment. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3Eedits for clarification:x3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ETwo users hitting it wonx27t happen.  This is an upgrade script that will be run only once, and never concurrently. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe actual sproc isnx27t prefixed with sp_, fixed the example code. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn normal usage, we do use an id table and a sproc to get IDs as needed, I was just looking for a cleaner way to do it in this script, which essentially just dumps a bunch of data into the db. x3C/px3E',1,3,'mschafflere','2008-08-26 19:01:50'),(28380,'Proxy which requires authentication with Android Emulator','x3Cpx3EHas anybody managed to get the Android Emulator working behind a proxy which requires authentication?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve tried setting the -http-proxy argument to x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ehttp://DOMAIN/USERNAME:PASSWORD@IP:PORT\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ebut am having no success. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve tried following the docs to no avail. Ix27ve also tried the x3Ccodex3E-verbose-proxyx3C/codex3E setting but this no longer seems to exist.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny pointers?x3C/px3E',1,11,'awrefford16','2008-08-26 19:30:38'),(28530,'Corporate-Friendly Open Source Licenses','x3Cpx3EWhat open source licenses are more corporate-friendly, i.e., they can be used in commercial products without the need to open source the commercial product?x3C/px3E',1,10,'awrefford16','2008-08-26 20:26:51'),(28560,'Is it possible to use nHibernate with Paradox database?','x3Cpx3EIs it possible to configure nHibernate to connect to Paradox database (x3Ccodex3E*.dbx3C/codex3E files)?x3C/px3E',1,5,'rdowdellz','2008-08-26 20:38:05'),(28590,'Why is it bad practice to make multiple database connections in one request?','x3Cpx3EA discussion about Singletons in x3Cstrongx3EPHPx3C/strongx3E has me thinking about this issue more and more. Most people instruct that you shouldnx27t make a bunch of DB connections in one request, and Ix27m just curious as to what your reasoning is. My first thought is the expense to your script of making that many requests to the DB, but then I counter myself with the question: wouldnx27t multiple connections make concurrent querying more efficient?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow about some answers (with evidence, folks) from some people in the know?x3C/px3E',1,8,'erowcliffe1d','2008-08-26 20:53:53'),(28820,'Windows Mobile - What scripting platforms are available?','x3Cpx3EWe have a number of users with Windows Mobile 6 and need to apply minor changes. eg. update a registry setting. One option is push and execute an executable file using our device management software.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27d like this to be a little more friendly for the admins who are familiar with scripting in VBScript/JScript etc. What are the options for scripting on Windows Mobile devices?x3C/px3E',1,6,'rtomeo0','2008-08-26 22:42:14'),(28840,'Scrum - How to get better input from the functional/commercial team','x3Cpx3EWe are a small team of 3 developers (2 experienced but new to  this particular business sector) developing a functionally complex product.  Wex27re using Scrum and have a demo at the end of each sprint.  Its clear that the functional team have plenty of ideas but these are not well communicated to the development team and the demo poses more questions than answers. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHave you any recommendations for improving the the quality of input from the functional people?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EFurther info:x3C/strongx3E I think part of the problem is that there are no x3Cemx3Especsx3C/emx3E or  User Stories as such.  Personally I think they need to be writing down some sort of requirements - what sort of things should they be writing down and to what complexity given its an agile process?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ETIAx3C/px3E',1,1,'civakhnop','2008-08-26 22:54:01'),(28950,'Guide to choosing between REST vs SOAP services?','x3Cpx3EDoes anyone have links to documentation or guides on making the decision between REST vs. SOAP? I understand both of these but am looking for some references on the key decision points, eg, security, which may make you lean towards one or the other.x3C/px3E',1,10,'erowcliffe1d','2008-08-26 23:46:56'),(29030,'SharePoint SPContext.List in a custom application page','x3Cpx3EI have a custom SharePoint application page deployed to the _layouts folder.  Itx27s a custom x22new formx22 for a custom content type.  During my interactions with this page, I will need to add an item to my list.  When the page first loads, I can use SPContext.Current.List to see the current list Ix27m working with.  But after I fill in my form and the form posts back onto itself and IsPostBack is true, then SPContext.Current.List is null so I canx27t find the list that I need to add my stuff into.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs this expected?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow should I retain some info about my context list across the postback?  Should I just populate some asp:hidden control with my listx27s guid and then just pull it back from that on the postback?  That seems safe, I guess.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EFWIW, this is the MOSS 2007 Standard version.x3C/px3E',1,1,'ofaircloughi','2008-08-27 01:47:22'),(29040,'Linq To SQL: Can I eager load only one field in a joined table?','x3Cpx3EI have one table x22ordersx22 with a foreing key x22ProductIDx22.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI want to show the orders in a grid with the x3Cstrongx3Eproduct namex3C/strongx3E, without x3Cstrongx3ELazyLoadx3C/strongx3E for better performance, but I if use x3Cstrongx3EDataLoadOptionsx3C/strongx3E it retrieves x3Cstrongx3Eallx3C/strongx3E Product fields, which seams like a x3Cstrongx3Eoverkillx3C/strongx3E.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there a way to retrieve x3Cstrongx3Eonlyx3C/strongx3E the Product name in the first query?\nCan I set some attribute in the DBML?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn this x3Ca href=x22http://visualstudiomagazine.com/listings/list.aspx?id=566x22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Etablex3C/ax3E says that x22Foreign-key valuesx22 are x22Visiblex22 in Linq To SQL, but donx27t know what this means.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EEditx3C/strongx3E: Changed the title, because Ix27m not really sure the there is no solution.x3Cbr /x3E\nCanx27t believe no one has the same problem, it is a very common scenario.x3C/px3E',1,6,'srm4902','2008-08-27 01:55:09'),(29100,'How are you generating tests from specifications?','x3Cpx3EI came across a printed x3Ca href=x22http://www.eiffel.com/general/column/2008/02.htmlx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Earticle by Bertrand Meyerx3C/ax3E where he states that tests can be generated from specifications. My development team does nothing like this, but it sounds like a good technique to consider. How are you generating tests from specifications? How would you describe the success your having in discovering program faults via this method?x3C/px3E',1,10,'kgrenkovu','2008-08-27 02:28:22'),(29370,'SQL1159 Initialization error with DB2 .NET Data Provider, reason code 7, tokens 9.5.0.DEF.2, SOFTWARE\\IBM\\DB2\\InstalledCopies','x3Cpx3EI am trying to get the DB2 data provider from a 32-bit .Net application to connect to DB2 running as a 32-bit application on Vista 64 (is that confusing enough yet)?  Unfortunately, I am getting the following error:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3ESQL1159 Initialization error with DB2 .NET Data Provider, reason code 7, tokens 9.5.0.DEF.2, SOFTWARE\\IBM\\DB2\\InstalledCopiesx3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThere are several x3Ca href=x22http://www-128.ibm.com/developerworks/forums/thread.jspa?threadID=207638x26amp;tstart=45x22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EIBM forum postsx3C/ax3E mentioning it, but little useful guidance.  Has anyone experienced this before?  Or do you have better ideas for fixing it?x3C/px3E',1,11,'gdodding5','2008-08-27 06:20:39'),(29460,'Stop the taskbar flashing','x3Cpx3EI know I can programatically make the taskbar item for a particular window start flashing when something changes, but is there any way I can stop it from flashing either programatically after a certain period of time or at least is there a keyboard shortcur I can give to my users to somehow stop the flashing?x3C/px3E',1,10,'enewberryf','2008-08-27 07:38:10'),(29580,'Why is pagination so resource-expensive?','x3Cpx3EItx27s one of those things that seems to have an odd curve where the more I think about it, the more it makes sense.  To a certain extent, of course.  And then it doesnx27t make sense to me at all.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECare to enlighten me?x3C/px3E',1,1,'chenburyh','2008-08-27 09:21:23'),(29630,'What is the best way to package and distribute an Excel application','x3Cpx3EIx27ve writen an Excel-based, database reporting tool. Currentely, all the VBA code is associated with a single XLS file. The user generates the report by clicking a button on the toolbar. Unfortunately, unless the user has saved the file under another file name, all the reported data gets wiped-out.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhen I have created similar tools in Word, I can put all the code in a template (.dot) file and call it from there. If I put the template file in the Office startup folder, it will launch everytime I start Word. Is there a similar way, to package and distribute my code in Excel? Ix27ve tried using Add-ins, but I didnx27t find a way to call the code from the application window.x3C/px3E',1,9,'ofaircloughi','2008-08-27 10:40:13'),(29680,'Suppress NTLM dialog box after unauthorized request','x3Cpx3EIn a recent sharepoint project, I implemented an authentication webpart which should replace the NTLM authentication dialog box. It works fine as long as the user provides valid credentials. Whenever the user provides invalid credentials, the NTLM dialog box pops up in Internet Explorer.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy Javascript code which does the authentication via XmlHttpRequest looks like this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Efunction Login() {\n   var request = GetRequest(); // retrieves XmlHttpRequest\n   request.onreadystatechange = function() {\n      if (this.status == 401) {     // unauthorized request -x26gt; invalid credentials\n         // do something to suppress NTLM dialog box...\n         // already tried location.reload(); and window.location = x26lt;url to authentication formx26gt;;\n      }\n   }\n   request.open(x22GETx22, x22http://myServerx22, false, x22domain\\\\usernamex22, x22passwordx22);\n   request.send(null);\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI donx27t want the NTLM dialog box to be displayed when the user provides invalid credentials. Instead the postback by the login button in the authentication form should be executed. In other words, the browser should not find out about my unauthorized request.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there any way to do this via Javascript?x3C/px3E',1,6,'ajan8','2008-08-27 11:40:01'),(29700,'Can someone point me to some guides for WPF','x3Cpx3EI am having trouble finding good guides for WPF.x3Cbr /x3E\nI have experience in C# and .NET but  I donx27t know anything about WPF except for the regular marketing-ish description of the technology as a whole.x3Cbr /x3E\nCan anyone point me to a good beginnerx27s tutorial/guide on WPF.x3C/px3E',1,4,'eburnyaten','2008-08-27 12:01:42'),(29760,'Stopping MSI from launching an EXE in the SYSTEM context','x3Cpx3EIx27ve got a problem here with an MSI deployment that Ix27m working on (using x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/InstallShieldx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EInstallShieldx3C/ax3E). We have a program running in the background that needs to run per-user, and it needs to start automatically without user intervention.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe problem is with x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Group_Policy#Operationx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EGroup Policy Objectx3C/ax3E/x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Active_Directoryx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EActive Directoryx3C/ax3E (GPO/AD) deployment the application is started in the SYSTEM context before anyone is logged in rather than as the user who is about to log in. The application can only run once per user, and it seems that the SYSTEM process prevents the USER process from starting. This means the PCs need to be rebooted twice before the software can be deployed to the users. How do we to stop this?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBasically the current workflow is: x3C/px3E\n\nx3Colx3E\nx3Clix3EInstallation/upgrade runs... kill background applicationx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EInstall new filesx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EStartup background applicationx3C/lix3E\nx3C/olx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis works for published applications and interactive x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows_Installerx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EMSIx3C/ax3E installations - itx27s only x27assignedx27 applications that seem to have the problem. As step 3 happens in the SYSTEM context rather than the user context :(x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIdeally, Ix27d have the development team patch the EXE file to prevent launching in the SYSTEM context, but thatx27s a release cycle away, and Ix27m looking for an installer-based solution for the interim.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3E(I donx27t know Installscript... So Ix27m guessing x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VBScriptx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EVBScriptx3C/ax3E is probably the way to go if therex27s no native InstallShield stuff I can use.)x3C/px3E',1,11,'rtomeo0','2008-08-27 12:52:35'),(29810,'Is version control (ie. Subversion) applicable in document tracking?','x3Cpx3EI am in charge of about 100+ documents (word document, not source code) that needs revision by different people in my department. Currently all the documents are in a shared folder where they will retrieve, revise and save back into the folder. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat I am doing now is looking up the x22date modifiedx22 in the shared folder, opened up recent modified documents and use the x22Track Changex22 function in MS Word to apply the changes. I find this a bit tedious.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo will it be better and easier if I commit this in a version control database?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBasically I want to keep different version of a file.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Chrx3E\nWhat have I learn from answers:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3EUse Time Machine to save different\nversion (or Shadow copy in Vista)x3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3EThere is a difference between text\nand binary documents when you use\nversion control app. (I didnx27t know\nthat)x3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3EDiff wonx27t work on binary filesx3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3EA notification system (ie email) for revision is greatx3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3EGoogle Docs revision feature.x3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EUpdatex3C/strongx3E : x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI played around with Google Docs revision feature and feel that it is almost right for me. Just a bit annoyed with the too frequent versioning (autosaving). x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBut what feels right for me doesnx27t mean it feels right for my dept. Will they be okay with saving all these documents with Google? x3C/px3E',1,5,'tplumsteadj','2008-08-27 13:42:59'),(29820,'Java return copy to hide future changes','x3Cpx3EIn Java, say you have a class that wraps an x3Ccodex3EArrayListx3C/codex3E (or any collection) of objects. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow would you return one of those objects such that the caller will not see any future changes to the object made in the ArrayList? x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ei.e. you want to return a deep copy of the object, but you donx27t know if it is cloneable.x3C/px3E',1,8,'prihak','2008-08-27 13:48:00'),(29870,'How to bring in a web app','x3Cpx3EI run a game and the running is done by hand, I have a few scripts that help me but essentially itx27s me doing the work. I am at the moment working on web app that will allow the users to input directly some of their game actions and thus save me a lot of work.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe problem is that Ix27m one man working on a moderately sized (upwards of 20 tables) project, the workload isnx27t the issue, itx27s that bugs will have slipped in even though I test as I write. So my question is thus two-fold.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Colx3E\nx3Clix3EBeta testing, I love open betax27s but would a closed beta be somehow more effective and give better results?x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EHow should I bring in the app? Should I one turn drop it in and declare itx27s being used or should I use it alongside the normal construct of the game?x3C/lix3E\nx3C/olx3E',1,2,'idevey11','2008-08-27 14:43:53'),(29890,'How to get your own (local) IP-Address from an udp-socket (C/C++)','x3Colx3E\nx3Clix3EYou have multiple network adapters.x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EBind a UDP socket to an local port, without specifying an address.x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EReceive packets on one of the adapters.x3C/lix3E\nx3C/olx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow do you get the local ip address of the adapter which received the packet?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe question is, x22What is the ip address from the receiver adapter?x22 not the address from the sender which we get in the x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ereceive_from( ..., x26amp;senderAddr, ... );\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ecall.x3C/px3E',1,5,'abaterb','2008-08-27 14:54:29'),(29980,'How should I test a method that populates a list from a DataReader?','x3Cpx3ESo Ix27m working on some legacy code thatx27s heavy on the manual database operations. Ix27m trying to maintain some semblance of quality here, so Ix27m going TDD as much as possible.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe code Ix27m working on needs to populate, letx27s say a x3Ccodex3EListx26lt;Foox26gt;x3C/codex3E from a DataReader that returns all the fields required for a functioning Foo. However, if I want to verify that the code in fact returns one list item per one database row, Ix27m writing test code that looks something like this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EExpect.Call(reader.Read()).Return(true);\nExpect.Call(reader[x22foo_idx22]).Return((long) 1);\n// ....\nExpect.Call(reader.Read()).Return(true);\nExpect.Call(reader[x22foo_idx22]).Return((long) 2);\n// ....\nExpect.Call(reader.Read()).Return(false);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhich is rather tedious and rather easily broken, too. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow should I be approaching this issue so that the result wonx27t be a huge mess of brittle tests?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBtw Ix27m currently using Rhino.Mocks for this, but I can change it if the result is convincing enough. Just as long as the alternative isnx27t TypeMock, because their EULA was a bit too scary for my tastes last I checked.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEdit: Ix27m also currently limited to C# 2.x3C/px3E',1,5,'ajan8','2008-08-27 16:29:09'),(30080,'How to know if a line intersects a plane in C#? - Basic 2D geometry','x3Cpx3Emy school maths are very rusty and I think this is a good opportunity to take advance of this community :Dx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have two points (a line) and a rectangle, I would like to know how to calculate if the line intersects the rectangle, my first approach had so many x22ifx22 statements that the compiler sent me a link to this site.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThanks for your time!x3C/px3E',1,7,'cribbens4','2008-08-27 17:26:56'),(30160,'Is there a Java Console/Editor similar to the GroovyConsole?','x3Cpx3EIx27m giving a presentation to a Java Userx27s Group on Groovy and Ix27m going to be doing some coding during the presentation to show some side-by-side Java/Groovy.  I really like the GroovyConsole as itx27s simple and I can resize the text easily.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m wondering if there is anything similar for Java?  I know I could just use Eclipse but Ix27d rather have a smaller app to use without having to customize a view.  Whatx27s the community got?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EScreen shot of GroovyConsole:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cimg src=x22http://i.stack.imgur.com/GiR7b.jpgx22 alt=x22enter image description herex22x3Ex3C/px3E',1,5,'mlowried','2008-08-27 17:50:26'),(30170,'Avoiding repeated constants in CSS','x3Cpx3EAre there any useful techniques for reducing the repetition of constants in a CSS file?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3E(For example, a bunch of different selectors which should all apply the same colour, or the same font size)?x3C/px3E',1,9,'rtomeo0','2008-08-27 17:53:51'),(30230,'enter key to insert newline in asp.net multiline textbox control','x3Cpx3EI have some C# / asp.net code I inherited which has a textbox which I want to make multiline. I did so by adding textmode=x22multilinex22 but when I try to insert a newline, the enter key instead submits the form :Px3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI googled around and it seems like the default behavior should be for enter (or control-enter) to insert a newline. Like I said I inherited the code so Ix27m not sure if therex27s javascript monkeying around or if therex27s just a simple asp.net thing I have to do.x3C/px3E',1,7,'mheyward10','2008-08-27 18:12:30'),(30310,'Asp.Net MVC: How do I enable dashes in my urls?','x3Cpx3EIx27d like to have dashes separate words in my URLs.  So instead of:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E/MyController/MyAction\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27d like:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E/My-Controller/My-Action\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs this possible?x3C/px3E',1,1,'srm9547','2008-08-27 18:41:31'),(30430,'Moving from Visual Studio 2005 to 2008 and .NET 2.0','x3Cpx3EIx27m currently using VS2005 Profesional and .NET 2.0, and since our project is rather large (25 projects in the solution), Ix27d like to try VS 2008, since its theoretically faster with larger projects. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBefore doing such thing, ix27d like to know if what Ix27ve read is true: can I use VS2008 in x22.net 2.0x22 mode? I donx27t want my customers to install .net 3.0 or .3.5, I just want to install VS2008, open my solution and start working from there. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs this possible?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EP.D.: the solution is a c# Window Forms project.x3C/px3E',1,8,'aillidges','2008-08-27 19:22:52'),(30540,'What does this javascript error mean? Permission denied to call method to Location.toString','x3Cpx3EThis error just started popping up all over our site.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3Ex3Cemx3EPermission denied to call method to Location.toStringx3C/emx3Ex3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m seeing google posts that suggest that this is related to flash and our crossdomain.xml.  What caused this to occur and how do you fix?x3C/px3E',1,4,'cgaweno','2008-08-27 20:02:00'),(30660,'MySQL Binary Log Replication: Can it be set to ignore errors?','x3Cpx3EIx27m running a master-slave MySQL binary log replication system (phew!) that, for some data, is not in sync (meaning, the master holds more data than the slave). But the slave stops very frequently on the slightest MySQL error, can this be disabled? (perhaps a my.cnf setting for the replicating slave ignore-replicating-errors or some of the sort ;) )x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis is what happens, every now and then, when the slave tries to replicate an item that does not exist, the slave just dies. a quick check at x3Cstrongx3ESHOW SLAVE STATUS \\G;x3C/strongx3E givesx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E       Slave-IO-Running: Yes\n      Slave-SQL-Running: No\n        Replicate-Do-DB: \n             Last-Errno: 1062\n             Last-Error: Error x27Duplicate entry x2715218x27 for key 1x27 on query. Default database: x27dbx27. Query: x27INSERT INTO db.table ( FIELDS ) VALUES ( VALUES )x27\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ewhich I promptly fix (once I realize that the slave has been stopped) by doing the following:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3ESTOP SLAVE;\nRESET SLAVE;\nSTART SLAVE;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3E... lately this has been getting kind of tiresome, and before I spit out some sort of PHP which does this for me, i was wondering if therex27s some my.cnf entry which will not kill the slave on the first error.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECheers,x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3E/mpx3C/px3E',1,9,'dperrenl','2008-08-27 21:11:09'),(30710,'How to unit test an object with database queries','x3Cpx3EIx27ve heard that unit testing is x22totally awesomex22, x22really coolx22 and x22all manner of good thingsx22 but 70% or more of my files involve database access (some read and some write) and Ix27m not sure how to write a unit test for these files.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m using PHP and Python but I think itx27s a question that applies to most/all languages that use database access.x3C/px3E',1,10,'achancelier6','2008-08-27 21:46:02'),(30770,'Update Panel inside of a UserControl inside of a Repeater inside of another UpdatePanel','x3Cpx3EYes, it sounds crazy....It might be.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe final updatepanel does not appear to trigger anything, it just refreshes the update panels and does not call back to the usercontrol hosting it.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny ideas?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEDIT: I got it posting back, however the controls inside the final usercontrol have lost their data...Ix27m thinking its because the main repeater is rebinding on each postback...Not sure where to take this one now.x3C/px3E',1,1,'dperrenl','2008-08-27 22:14:46'),(30790,'Is there a Way to use Linq to Oracle','x3Cpx3EI can connect with the DataContext to the Oracle database however I get errors in running the query against the oracle database.  I looked at the SQL generated and it is for MSSQL and not Oracle PSQL.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDoes anybody know of a decent easy to use wrapper to use LINQ against an Oracle Database?x3C/px3E',1,2,'dsizland14','2008-08-27 22:18:29'),(30800,'How can I authenticate using client credentials in WCF just once?','x3Cpx3EWhat is the best approach to make sure you only need to authenticate once when using an API built on WCF?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy current bindings and behaviors are listed belowx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E	x26lt;bindingsx26gt;\n		x26lt;wsHttpBindingx26gt;\n			x26lt;binding name=x22wsHttpx22x26gt;\n				x26lt;security mode=x22TransportWithMessageCredentialx22x26gt;\n					x26lt;transport/x26gt;\n					x26lt;message clientCredentialType=x22UserNamex22 negotiateServiceCredential=x22falsex22 establishSecurityContext=x22truex22/x26gt;\n				x26lt;/securityx26gt;\n			x26lt;/bindingx26gt;\n		x26lt;/wsHttpBindingx26gt;\n	x26lt;/bindingsx26gt;\n	x26lt;behaviorsx26gt;\n		x26lt;serviceBehaviorsx26gt;\n			x26lt;behavior name=x22NorthwindBehaviorx22x26gt;\n				x26lt;serviceMetadata httpGetEnabled=x22truex22/x26gt;\n				x26lt;serviceAuthorization principalPermissionMode=x22UseAspNetRolesx22/x26gt;\n				x26lt;serviceCredentialsx26gt;\n					x26lt;userNameAuthentication userNamePasswordValidationMode=x22MembershipProviderx22/x26gt;\n				x26lt;/serviceCredentialsx26gt;\n			x26lt;/behaviorx26gt;\n		x26lt;/serviceBehaviorsx26gt;\n	x26lt;/behaviorsx26gt;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3ENext is what I am using in my client app to authenticate (currently I must do this everytime I want to make a call into WCF)x3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EDim client As ProductServiceClient = New ProductServiceClient(x22wsHttpProductServicex22)\nclient.ClientCredentials.UserName.UserName = x22foox22\nclient.ClientCredentials.UserName.Password = x22barx22\nDim ProductList As List(Of Product) = client.GetProducts()\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat I would like to do is auth w/ the API once using these credentials, then get some type of token for the period of time my client application is using the web service project.  I thought establishsecuritycontext=true did this for me?x3C/px3E',1,6,'aa9279','2008-08-27 22:23:20'),(30940,'How to handle error logging','x3Cpx3EUntil recently Ix27ve been using x3Ccodex3Esyslogx3C/codex3E in my x3Ccodex3ESystem_Exceptionx3C/codex3E exception handler to log important errors - a pretty useful concept I thought. However my host just cut me off, and it appears that 