missing a link or something, but it seems like the official documentation isnx27t very thorough on the subject, and I havenx27t been able to find a good write-up.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EFrom what I can tell, only one thread can be running at once, and the active thread switches every 10 instructions or so?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhere is there a good explanation, or can you provide one? It would also be very nice to be aware of common problems that you run into while using threads with Python.x3C/px3E',1,5,'osilley7','2008-08-28 03:44:47'),(31380,'Is there a reason to use BufferedReader over InputStreamReader when reading all characters?','x3Cpx3EI currently use the following function to do a simple HTTP GET.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Epublic static String download(String url) throws java.io.IOException {\n    java.io.InputStream s = null;\n    java.io.InputStreamReader r = null;\n    //java.io.BufferedReader b = null;\n    StringBuilder content = new StringBuilder();\n    try {\n        s = (java.io.InputStream)new URL(url).getContent();\n\n        r = new java.io.InputStreamReader(s);\n        //b = new java.io.BufferedReader(r);\n\n        char[] buffer = new char[4*1024];\n        int n = 0;\n        while (n x26gt;= 0) {\n            n = r.read(buffer, 0, buffer.length);\n            if (n x26gt; 0) {\n                content.append(buffer, 0, n);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    finally {\n        //if (b != null) b.close();\n        if (r != null) r.close();\n        if (s != null) s.close();\n    }\n    return content.toString();\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI see no reason to use the x3Ccodex3EBufferedReaderx3C/codex3E since I am just going to download everything in sequence. Am I right in thinking there is no use for the x3Ccodex3EBufferedReaderx3C/codex3E in this case?x3C/px3E',1,6,'rmaccurlyer','2008-08-28 04:07:06'),(31410,'Visual Studio 2008 debugging issue','x3Cpx3EIx27m working in VS 2008 and have three projects in one solution.  Ix27m debugging by attaching to a .net process invoked by a third party app (SalesLogix, a CRM app).  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EOnce it has attached to the process and I attempt to set a breakpoint in one of the projects, it doesnx27t set a breakpoint in that file.  It actually switches the current tab to another file in another project and sets a breakpoint in that document.  If the file isnx27t open, it even goes so far as to open it for me.  I canx27t explain this.  Ix27ve got no clue.  Anyone seen such odd behavior?  I wouldnx27t believe it if I wasnx27t seeing it myself.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EA little more info: if I set a breakpoint before attaching, it shows the x22red dotx22 and says no symbols loaded...no problem...I expect that.  When I attach and invoke my .net code from SalesLogix and switch back to VS, my breakpoint is completely gone (not even a warning that the source doesnx27t match the debug file).  When I attempt to manually load the debug file, then I get a message that the symbol file does not match the module.  The .pdb and the .dll are timestamped the same, so Ix27m stumped.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnyone have any ideas?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThx,x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EJeffx3C/px3E',1,4,'idevey11','2008-08-28 04:25:47'),(31480,'How stable is WPF?','x3Cpx3EHow stable is WPF not in terms of stability of a WPF program, but in terms of the x27stabilityx27 of the API itself.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ELet me explain:  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMicrosoft is notorious for changing its whole methodology around with new technology. Like with the move from silverlight 1 to silverlight 2. With WPF, I know that MS changed a bunch of stuff with the release of the .NET service pack. I donx27t know how much they changed things around. So the bottom line is, in your opinion are they going to revamp the system again with the next release or do you think that it is stable enough now that they wonx27t change the bulk of the system. I hate to have to unlearn stuff with every release.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI hope that the question wasnx27t too long winded.x3C/px3E',1,4,'dsizland14','2008-08-28 05:38:47'),(31500,'Do indexes work with x22INx22 clause','x3Cpx3EIf I have a query like:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3ESelect EmployeeId \nFrom Employee \nWhere EmployeeTypeId IN (1,2,3)\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Eand I have an index on the x3Ccodex3EEmployeeTypeIdx3C/codex3E field, does SQL server still use that index?x3C/px3E',1,5,'mheyward10','2008-08-28 06:00:09'),(31790,'How many ServiceContracts can a WCF service have?','x3Cpx3EHow many ServiceContracts can a WCF service have?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESpecifically, since a ServiceContract is an attribute to an interface, how many interfaces can I code into one WCF web service? Is it a one-to-one?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDoes it make sense to separate the contracts across multiple web services?x3C/px3E',1,11,'srm4902','2008-08-28 11:28:17'),(31800,'How to respond to an alternate URI in a RESTful web service','x3Cpx3EIx27m building a RESTful web service which has multiple URIs for one of its resources, because there is more than one unique identifier. Should the server respond to a GET request for an alternate URI by returning the resource, or should I send an HTTP 3xx redirect to the canonical URI? Is x3Cemx3EHTTP 303 (see also)x3C/emx3E the most appropriate redirect?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EClarification: the HTTP specification makes it clear that the choice of redirect depends on which URI future requests should use. In my application, the x27canonicalx27 URI is the most stable of the alternatives; an alternative URI will always direct to same canonical URI, or become invalid.x3C/px3E',1,6,'aa9279','2008-08-28 11:36:46'),(31840,'Java Logging vs Log4J','x3Cpx3EIs it still worth to add the log4j library to a Java 5 project just to log\nletx27s say some exceptions to a file with some nice rollover settings.\nOr will the standard util.logging facility do the job as well?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat do you think?x3C/px3E',1,3,'aillidges','2008-08-28 12:20:44'),(31870,'using a html entity in xslt (e.g. x26nbsp;)','x3Cpx3EWhat is the best way to include an html entity in XSLT?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ex26lt;xsl:template match=x22/a/nodex22x26gt;\n    x26lt;xsl:value-of select=x22.x22/x26gt;\n    x26lt;xsl:textx26gt;x26amp;nbsp;x26lt;/xsl:textx26gt;\nx26lt;/xsl:templatex26gt;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ethis one returns a x3Cstrongx3EXsltParseErrorx3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E',1,11,'ofaircloughi','2008-08-28 12:55:34'),(31930,'Sending e-mail from a Custom SQL Server Reporting Services Delivery Extension','x3Cpx3EIx27ve developed my own delivery extension for Reporting Services 2005, to integrate this with our SaaS marketing solution.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIt takes the subscription, and takes a snapshot of the report with a custom set of parameters. It then renders the report, sends an e-mail with a link and the report attached as XLS.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEverything works fine, until mail delivery...x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHerex27s my code for sending e-mail:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E public static Listx26lt;stringx26gt; SendMail(SubscriptionData data, Stream reportStream, string reportName, string smptServerHostname, int smtpServerPort)\n{\n  Listx26lt;stringx26gt; failedRecipients = new Listx26lt;stringx26gt;();\n\n  MailMessage emailMessage = new MailMessage(data.ReplyTo, data.To);\n  emailMessage.Priority = data.Priority;\n  emailMessage.Subject = data.Subject;\n  emailMessage.IsBodyHtml = false;\n  emailMessage.Body = data.Comment;\n\n  if (reportStream != null)\n  {\n    Attachment reportAttachment = new Attachment(reportStream, reportName);\n    emailMessage.Attachments.Add(reportAttachment);\n    reportStream.Dispose();\n  }\n\n  try\n  {\n    SmtpClient smtp = new SmtpClient(smptServerHostname, smtpServerPort);\n\n    // Send the MailMessage\n    smtp.Send(emailMessage);\n  }\n  catch (SmtpFailedRecipientsException ex)\n  {\n    // Delivery failed for the recipient. Add the e-mail address to the failedRecipients List\n    failedRecipients.Add(ex.FailedRecipient);\n  }\n  catch (SmtpFailedRecipientException ex)\n  {\n    // Delivery failed for the recipient. Add the e-mail address to the failedRecipients List\n    failedRecipients.Add(ex.FailedRecipient);\n  }\n  catch (SmtpException ex)\n  {\n    throw ex;\n  }\n  catch (Exception ex)\n  {\n    throw ex;\n  }\n\n  // Return the List of failed recipient e-mail addresses, so the client can maintain its list.\n  return failedRecipients;\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EValues for SmtpServerHostname is localhost, and port is 25.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI veryfied that I can actually send mail, by using Telnet. And it works.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EHerex27s the error message I get from SSRS:x3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EReportingServicesService!notification!4!08/28/2008-11:26:17:: Notification 6ab32b8d-296e-47a2-8d96-09e81222985c completed.  Success: False, Status: Exception Message: Failure sending mail. Stacktrace:    at MyDeliveryExtension.MailDelivery.SendMail(SubscriptionData data, Stream reportStream, String reportName, String smptServerHostname, Int32 smtpServerPort) in C:\\inetpub\\wwwroot\\CustomReporting\\MyDeliveryExtension\\MailDelivery.cs:line 48\n   at MyDeliveryExtension.MyDelivery.Deliver(Notification notification) in C:\\inetpub\\wwwroot\\CustomReporting\\MyDeliveryExtension\\MyDelivery.cs:line 153, DeliveryExtension: My Delivery, Report: Clicks Development, Attempt 1\nReportingServicesService!dbpolling!4!08/28/2008-11:26:17:: NotificationPolling finished processing item 6ab32b8d-296e-47a2-8d96-09e81222985cx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3ECould this have something to do with Trust/Code Access Security?x3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy delivery extension is granted full trust in rssrvpolicy.config:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E   x26lt;CodeGroup \n    class=x22UnionCodeGroupx22\n    version=x221x22\n    PermissionSetName=x22FullTrustx22\n    Name=x22MyDelivery_CodeGroupx22\n    Description=x22Code group for MyDelivery extensionx22x26gt;\n    x26lt;IMembershipCondition class=x22UrlMembershipConditionx22 version=x221x22 Url=x22C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft SQL Server\\MSSQL.2\\Reporting Services\\ReportServer\\bin\\MyDeliveryExtension.dllx22 /x26gt;\n   x26lt;/CodeGroupx26gt;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECould trust be an issue here?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnother theory: SQL Server and SSRS was installed in the security context of Local System. Am I right, or is this service account restricted access to any network resource? Even its own SMTP Server?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI tried changing all SQL Server Services logons to Administrator - but still without any success.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI also tried logging onto the SMTP server in my code, by proviiding: NetworkCredential(x22Administratorx22, x22passwordx22) and also NetworkCredential(x22Administratorx22, x22passwordx22, x22MyRepServerx22)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECan anyone help here, please?x3C/px3E',1,6,'clawrence3','2008-08-28 13:50:48'),(32000,'C# - SQLClient - Simplest INSERT','x3Cpx3EIx27m basically trying to figure out the simplest way to perform your basic insert operation in C#.NET using the SqlClient namespace. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m using x3Ccodex3ESqlConnectionx3C/codex3E for my db link, Ix27ve already had success executing some reads, and I want to know the simplest way to insert data. Ix27m finding what seem to be pretty verbose methods when I google.x3C/px3E',1,3,'achancelier6','2008-08-28 14:37:39'),(32010,'Is regex case insensitivity slower?','x3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://twitter.com/codinghorror/statuses/901272685x22x3ESourcex3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3ERegexOptions.IgnoreCase is more expensive than I would have thought (eg, should be barely measurable)x3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAssuming that this applies to PHP, Python, Perl, Ruby etc as well as C# (which is what I assume Jeff was using), how much of a slowdown is it and will I incur a similar penalty with x22/[a-zA-z]/x22 as I will with x22/[a-z]/ix22 ?x3C/px3E',1,2,'cgaweno','2008-08-28 14:55:17'),(32020,'Is soapUI the best web services testing tool/client/framework?','x3Cpx3EI have been working on a web services related project for about the last year.  Our team found x3Ca href=x22http://www.soapui.orgx22x3EsoapUIx3C/ax3E near the start of our project and we have been x3Cemx3Emostlyx3C/emx3E(*) satisfied with it (the free version, that is).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy question is: are there other tools/clients/frameworks that you have used/currently use for web services testing and would recommend?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3E(*) There are some weird GUI glitches that appear once in a while.  As is mentioned by some of the answers, we attributed this to a memory leak.x3C/px3E',1,2,'abaterb','2008-08-28 15:23:44'),(32100,'What is the simplest SQL Query to find the second largest value?','x3Cpx3EWhat is the simplest SQL query to find the second largest integer value in a specific column? x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThere are maybe duplicate values in the column.x3C/px3E',1,1,'aillidges','2008-08-28 16:39:53'),(32260,'Sending email in .NET through Gmail','x3Cpx3EInstead of relying on my host to send email, I was thinking of sending the messages though my Gmail account. The emails are personalized emails to the bands I play on my show. Is it possible to do?x3C/px3E',1,5,'civakhnop','2008-08-28 17:28:38'),(32280,'Passing null to a method','x3Cpx3EI am in the middle of reading the excellent x3Ca href=x22http://rads.stackoverflow.com/amzn/click/0132350882x22x3EClean Codex3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EOne discussion is regarding passing nulls into a method.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Epublic class MetricsCalculator {\n    public double xProjection(Point p1, Point p2) {\n        return (p2.x - p1.x) * 1.5;\n    }\n}\n...\ncalculator.xProjection(null, new Point(12,13));\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIt represents different ways of handling this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Epublic double xProjection(Point p1, Point p2) {\n    if (p1 == null || p2 == null) {\n        throw new IllegalArgumentException(x22Invalid argument for xProjectionx22);\n    }\n    return (p2.x - p1.x) * 1.5;\n}\n\npublic double xProjection(Point p1, Point p2) {\n    assert p1 != null : x22p1 should not be nullx22;\n    assert p2 != null : x22p2 should not be nullx22;\n    return (p2.x - p1.x) * 1.5;\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI prefer the x3Ca href=x22http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.4.2/docs/guide/lang/assert.htmlx22x3Eassertionsx3C/ax3E approach, but I donx27t like the fact that assertions are turned off by default.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe book finally states:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3EIn most programming languages there is no good way to deal with a null that is passed by a caller accidentally. Because this is the case, the rational approach is to forbid passing null by default.x3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIt doesnx27t really go into how you would enforce this restriction?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDo any of you have strong opinions either way.x3C/px3E',1,3,'tvallentint','2008-08-28 17:34:40'),(32360,'1:1 Foreign Key Constraints','x3Cpx3EHow do you specify that a foreign key constraint should be a 1:1 relationship in transact sql? Is declaring the column UNIQUE enough? Below is my existing code.!x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3ECREATE TABLE [dbo].MyTable(\n    [MyTablekey] INT IDENTITY(1,1) NOT FOR REPLICATION NOT NULL,\n    [OtherTableKey] INT NOT NULL UNIQUE\n        CONSTRAINT [FK_MyTable_OtherTable] FOREIGN KEY REFERENCES [dbo].[OtherTable]([OtherTableKey]),\n    ...\n    CONSTRAINT [PK_MyTable] PRIMARY KEY CLUSTERED \n    (\n        [MyTableKey] ASC\n    ) WITH (PAD_INDEX  = OFF, STATISTICS_NORECOMPUTE  = OFF, IGNORE_DUP_KEY = OFF, ALLOW_ROW_LOCKS  = ON, ALLOW_PAGE_LOCKS  = ON) ON [PRIMARY]\n) ON [PRIMARY]\nGO\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E',1,11,'hginglell13','2008-08-28 18:16:15'),(32460,'Get the DefaultView DataRowView from a DataRow','x3Cpx3EHerex27s the situation:  I need to bind a WPF x3Ccodex3EFixedPagex3C/codex3E against a x3Ccodex3EDataRowx3C/codex3E.  Bindings donx27t work against x3Ccodex3EDataRowsx3C/codex3E; they work against x3Ccodex3EDataRowViewsx3C/codex3E.  I need to do this in the most generic way possible, as I know nothing about and have no control over what is in the x3Ccodex3EDataRowx3C/codex3E.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat I need is to be able to get a x3Ccodex3EDataRowViewx3C/codex3E for a given x3Ccodex3EDataRowx3C/codex3E.  I canx27t use the x3Ccodex3EFind()x3C/codex3E method on the x3Ccodex3EDefaultViewx3C/codex3E because that takes a key, and there is no guarantee the table will have a primary key set.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDoes anybody have a suggestion as to the best way to go around this?  x3C/px3E',1,5,'awrefford16','2008-08-28 18:45:43'),(32540,'Alternative x22architecturalx22 approaches to javaScript client code?','x3Cpx3EHow is your javaScript code organized? Does it follow patterns like MVC, or something else? x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve been working on a side project for some time now, and the further I get, the more my webpage has turned into a full-featured application. Right now, Ix27m sticking with x3Ca href=x22http://jquery.comx22x3EjQueryx3C/ax3E, however, the logic on the page is growing to a point where some organization, or dare I say it, x22architecturex22 is needed. My first approach is x22MVC-ishx22:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3EThe x27modelx27 is a JSON tree that gets extended with helpersx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EThe view is the DOM plus classes that tweak itx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EThe controller is the object where I connect events handling and kick off view or model manipulationx3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m very interested, however, in how other people have built more substantial javaScript apps. Ix27m not interested in GWT, or other server-oriented approaches... just in the approach of x22javaScript + x26lt;generic web service-y thingy herex26gt;x22x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENote: earlier I said javaScript x22is not really OO, not really functionalx22. This, I think, distracted everyone. Letx27s put it this way, because javaScript is unique in many ways, and Ix27m coming from a strongly-typed background, I donx27t want to force paradigms I know but were developed in very different languages.x3C/px3E',1,5,'cscarbarrowm','2008-08-28 19:13:57'),(32550,'Does ReadUncommitted imply NoLock','x3Cpx3EWhen writing a SQL statement in SQL Server 2005, does the READUNCOMMITTED query hint imply NOLOCK or do I have to specify it manually too?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo is:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EWith (NoLock, ReadUnCommitted)\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ethe same as:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EWith (ReadUnCommitted)\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E',1,1,'sdally1','2008-08-28 19:17:00'),(32570,'How to make x27pretty urlsx27 work in php hosted in IIS?','x3Cpx3EIs there some way I can use urls like: x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://www.blog.com/team-spirit/x22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Ehttp://www.blog.com/team-spirit/x3C/ax3Ex3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Einstead ofx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://www.blog.com/?p=122x22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Ehttp://www.blog.com/?p=122x3C/ax3Ex3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ein a windows hosted PHP server?x3C/px3E',1,10,'wscreen1b','2008-08-28 19:23:53'),(32640,'Mocking Asp.net-mvc Controller Context','x3Cpx3ESo the controller context depends on some asp.net internals. What are some ways to cleanly mock these up for unit tests? Seems like its very easy to clog up tests with tons of setup when I only need, for example, Request.HttpMethod to return x22GETx22.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve seen some examples/helpers out on the nets, but some are dated. Figured this would be a good place to keep the latest and greatest.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m using latest version of rhino mocksx3C/px3E',1,6,'aauger2','2008-08-28 19:50:35'),(32750,'How can I take a byte array of a TIFF image and turn it into a System.Drawing.Image object?','x3Cpx3EI have a x3Ccodex3Ebyte[]x3C/codex3E array, the contents of which represent a TIFF file (as in, if I write out these bytes directly to a file using the x3Ccodex3EBinaryWriterx3C/codex3E object, it forms a perfectly valid TIFF file) and Ix27m trying to turn it into a System.Drawing.Image object so that I can use it for later manipulation (feeding into a multipage TIFF object)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe problem Ix27m having is that the commonly accepted code for this task:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E    public Image byteArrayToImage(byte[] byteArrayIn)\n    {\n        MemoryStream ms = new MemoryStream(byteArrayIn);\n        Image returnImage = Image.FromStream(ms, true);\n        return returnImage;\n    }\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Edoesnx27t work for me. The second line of the above method where it calls the x3Ccodex3EImage.FromStreamx3C/codex3E method dies at runtime, sayingx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EParameter Not Valid\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI believe that the method is choking on the fact that this is a TIFF file but I cannot figure out how to make the x3Ccodex3EFromStreamx3C/codex3E method accept this fact.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow do I turn a byte array of a TIFF image into an Image object?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAlso, like I said the end goal of this is to have a byte array representing a multipage TIFF file, which contains the TIFF files for which I have byte array objects of right now. If therex27s a much better way to go about doing this, Ix27m all for it.x3C/px3E',1,2,'ajan8','2008-08-28 20:38:10'),(32780,'SQL Server 2003 internet connection','x3Cpx3ERecently we got a new server at the office purely for testing purposes. It is set up so that we can access it from any computer. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHowever today our ip got blocked from one of our other sites saying that our ip has been suspected of having a virus that sends spam emails. we learned this from the cbl x3Ca href=x22http://cbl.abuseat.org/x22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Ehttp://cbl.abuseat.org/x3C/ax3E x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo of course we turned the server off to stop this. The problem is the server must be on to continue developing our application and to access the database that is installed on it. Our normal admin is on vacation and is unreachable, and the rest of us are idiots(me included) in this area. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWe believe that the best solution is to remove it from connecting to the internet but still access it on the lan. If that is a valid solution how would this be done or is there a better way? say blocking specified ports or whatever.x3C/px3E',1,3,'wscreen1b','2008-08-28 20:48:46'),(32790,'Alternatives to System.exit(1)','x3Cpx3EFor various reasons calling x3Ccodex3ESystem.exitx3C/codex3E is frowned upon when writing x3Cstrongx3EJava Applicationsx3C/strongx3E, so how can I notify the calling process that not everything is going according to plan?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EEdit:x3C/strongx3E The 1 is a x3Ccodex3Estandinx3C/codex3E for any non-zero exit code.x3C/px3E',1,7,'erowcliffe1d','2008-08-28 20:52:44'),(32930,'What is a good dvd burning component for Windows or .Net?','x3Cpx3EIx27d like to add dvd burning functionality to my .Net app (running on Windows Server 2003), are there any good components available?  Ix27ve used the NeroCOM sdk that used to come with Nero but they no longer support the sdk in the latest versions of Nero.  I learned that Microsoft has created an IMAPI2 upgrade for Windows XP/2003 and there is an x3Ca href=x22http://www.codeproject.com/KB/miscctrl/imapi2.aspxx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Eexample projectx3C/ax3E at CodeProject but not having used it myself I canx27t say how easy/reliable it is to use.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m not really worried about burning audio/video to DVD as this is for file backup purposes only.x3C/px3E',1,4,'aalandg','2008-08-28 21:59:11'),(33080,'Setting the height of a DIV dynamically','x3Cpx3EIn a web application, I have a page that contains a DIV that has an auto-width depending on the width of the browser window.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI need an auto-height for the object.  The DIV starts about 300px from the top screen, and itx27s height should make it stretch to the bottom of the browser screen.  I have a max height for the container DIV, so there would have to be minimum-height for the div.  I believe I can just restrict that in CSS, and use Javascript to handle the resizing of the DIV.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy javascript isnx27t nearly as good as it should be.  Is there an easy script I could write that would do this for me?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEdit: \nThe DIV houses a control that does itx27s own overflow handling (implements its own scroll bar).x3C/px3E',1,2,'civakhnop','2008-08-28 22:52:53'),(33150,'How to pass method name to custom server control in asp.net?','x3Cpx3EI am working on a Customer Server Control that extends another control.  There is no problem with attaching to other controls on the form.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ein vb.net:  Parent.FindControl(TargetControlName)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI would like to pass a method to the control in the ASPX markup. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Efor example: x26lt;c:MyCustomerControl runat=server InitializeStuffCallback=x22InitializeStuffx22x26gt;x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo, I tried using reflection to access the given method name from the Parent.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESomething like (in VB)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EDim pageType As Type = Page.GetType\nDim CallbackMethodInfo As MethodInfo = pageType.GetMethod( x22MethodNamex22 )\n\nx27Also tried \nsender.Parent.GetType.GetMethod(x22MethodNamex22)\nsender.Parent.Parent.GetType.GetMethod(x22MethodNamex22)\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe method isnx27t found, because it just isnx27t apart of the Page.  Where should I be looking?  Ix27m fairly sure this is possible because Ix27ve seen other controls do similar.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Chr /x3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI forgot to mention, my work-around is to give the control events and attaching to them in the Code-behind.x3C/px3E',1,4,'eburnyaten','2008-08-28 23:11:34'),(33250,'Caching Active Directory Data','x3Cpx3EIn one of my applications, I am querying active directory to get a list of all users below a given user (using the x22Direct Reportsx22 thing). So basically, given the name of the person, it is looked up in AD, then the Direct Reports are read. But then for every direct report, the tool needs to check the direct reports of the direct reports. Or, more abstract: The Tool will use a person as the root of the tree and then walk down the complete tree to get the names of all the leaves (can be several hundred)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENow, my concern is obviously performance, as this needs to be done quite a few times. My idea is to manually cache that (essentially just put all the names in a long string and store that somewhere and update it once a day).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBut I just wonder if there is a more elegant way to first get the information and then cache it, possibly using something in the System.DirectoryServices Namespace?x3C/px3E',1,10,'kgrenkovu','2008-08-28 23:58:10'),(33390,'Best use pattern for a DataContext','x3Cpx3EWhatx27s the best lifetime model for a DataContext? Should I just create a new one whenever I need it (aka, function level), should I keep one available in each class that would use it (class level), or should I create a static class with a static DataContext (app-domain level)? Are there any considered best practices on this?x3C/px3E',1,5,'sdally1','2008-08-29 01:02:15'),(33510,'What is the best approach to both modularity and platform independence?','x3Cpx3EI hope this question does not come off as broad as it may seem at first.  I am designing a software application in my x3Ccodex3Ex26lt;sarcasmx26gt;x3C/codex3Ex3Cemx3Evoluminousx3C/emx3Ex3Ccodex3Ex26lt;/sarcasmx26gt;x3C/codex3E spare time.  I would like it to be both cross-platform and modular.  At this point, because I am still in the planning phase, I can pick practically any language and toolset.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis makes things harder, not easier, because there are seemingly so many ways of accomplishing both of the goals (modularity, platform agnosticism). x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy basic premise is that security, data storage, interaction with the operating system, and configuration should all be handled by a x22containerx22 application - but most of the other functionality will be supplied through plug-in modules.  If I had to describe it at a high level (without completely giving away my idea), it would be a single application that can do many different jobs, all dedicated to the same goal (there are lots of disparate things to do, but all the data has to interact and be highly available).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis is not a new idea, and not particularly exotic.  Yet I find myself wrestling with not so much how to do it (I can think of lots of ways), but which method is best.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EFor example, I know that Eclipse practically embodies what I am describing, but I find Java applications in general (and Eclipse is no exception) to be too large and slow for what I need. Ditto desktop apps written Python and Ruby (which are excellent languages!)  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI donx27t mind recompiling the code base for different platforms as native exectables.  Yet, C and C++ have their own set of issues.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAs a C# developer, I have a preference for managed code.  But I am not at all sold on Mono, yet (I could be convinced).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDoes anyone have any ideas/experiences/ specific favorite frameworks to share?x3C/px3E',1,4,'sspindlerw','2008-08-29 02:03:58'),(33550,'Best open-source Mathematica equivalent','x3Cpx3EWhat is the best open-source equivalent for Mathematica?  My requirements are:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Colx3E\nx3Clix3E(most important) Must be a real computer algebra system (CAS).  Notably, I donx27t want Matlab clones -- I want something that can, at least, symbolically differentiate and integrate.x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EMust be programmable.  A functional-programming view of the world, like Mathematicax27s, would be awesome.  The basic datatype of Mx27ica is the list, which is very convenient!x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3E(least important) Similar syntax would be nice.x3C/lix3E\nx3C/olx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe ability to deal with objects such as groups or graphs would be a great bonus, but my primary emphasis is on the main things Mathematica and Maple do: algebra and calculus, both symbolic and numeric.  Also, plotting is not high on my list of requirements, as Ix27m mostly a terminal and not GUI user.x3C/px3E',1,1,'idevey11','2008-08-29 02:24:57'),(33590,'Drawing a custom label on a pie chart in Yahoox27s Flash Library ASTRA','x3Cpx3EHas anyone looked at x3Ca href=x22http://developer.yahoo.com/flash/x22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EYahoox27s ASTRAx3C/ax3E? Itx27s fairly nifty, but I had some issues creating a custom label for a pie chart. They have an example for a line chart, which overrides an axisx27s seriesx27s label renderer.  My solution was to override the x3Ccodex3EmyPieChart.dataTipFunctionx3C/codex3E. For data that looks like:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EmyPieChart.dataProvider =\n  [ { category: x22Groceriesx22, cost: 50 },\n    { category: x22Transportationx22, cost: 175} ]\nmyPieChart.dataField = x22costx22;\nmyPieChart.categoryField = x22categoryx22;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI wrote a function like this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eimport com.yahoo.astra.fl.charts.series.*\nmyPieChart.dataTipFunction = \n  function (obj:Object, index:int, series:ISeries):String {\n    return obj.category + x22\\n$x22 + obj.cost;\n  };\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ETherex27s ceil(2.718281828459045) problems with this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Colx3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3EIx27m directly calling the category and cost properties of the data provider. The names are actually configurable when setting up the chart, Ix27d like to maintain that flexibility.x3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3EThe default data tip would show the category, the cost (without a dollar sign), and the percentage it makes up in the pie chart. So here, Ix27ve lost the percentage. I just have no idea which property of what would hold that. It might be part of the series.x3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3EI probably only need to override the x3Ccodex3EdataItemRendererx3C/codex3E for the cost part of the series, but I donx27t know how to access it.  The documentation is a little ... lacking there.x3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3C/olx3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENormally I would just look at the default implementation of the x3Ccodex3EdataTipFunctionx3C/codex3E but itx27s all inside a compiled shm thatx27s part of the components distributed from yahoo.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECan anyone help me complete this overridden function with percentage information and the flexibility mentioned in point 1?x3C/px3E',1,10,'kgrenkovu','2008-08-29 02:54:37'),(33630,'Whatx27s the maximum amount of RAM I can use in a Windows box?','x3Cpx3EObviously, thatx27s 64-bit windows.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAlso, whatx27s the maximum amount of memory a single 64-bit process can use?\nI was kind of counting on using it all... \n(Yes, I know what Ix27m doing, please donx27t tell me that if I need that much RAM i must be doing something wrong)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAlso, is this the same for a .Net 2.0 process? Or is there a lower limit for .Net?x3C/px3E',1,2,'cleatham18','2008-08-29 03:25:02'),(33720,'Change templates in Xcode','x3Cpx3EHow would I change the initial templates created by Xcode when creating a new Cocoa Class.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI am referring to the comments and class name created when using Xcodex27s new class wizard.x3C/px3E',1,9,'rmaccurlyer','2008-08-29 04:44:14'),(33790,'How can I use `scp` to deploy a websitex27s `.htaccess` file?','x3Cpx3EI am currently using the following command to upload my site content:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Escp -r web/* user@site.com:site.com/\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis works great except that the .htaccess file is not sent. Presumably, this is because itx27s hidden.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have tried adding a second line to send the file explicitely:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Escp -r web/.htaccess user@site.com:site.com/.htaccess\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis works great except now I have to enter my password twice.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny thoughts on how to make this deploy with only 1 or 0 entries of my password?x3C/px3E',1,5,'mbeckinsale1a','2008-08-29 05:44:54'),(33860,'Is it possible to call Javascriptx27s onsubmit event programatically on a form?','x3Cpx3EIn Ruby on Rails, Ix27m attempting to update the x3Ccodex3EinnerHTMLx3C/codex3E of a div tag using the x3Ccodex3Eform_remote_tagx3C/codex3E helper.  This update happens whenever an associated select tag receives an onchange event.  The problem is, x3Ccodex3Ex26lt;select onchange=x22this.form.submit();x22x26gt;x3C/codex3E; doesnx27t work.  Nor does x3Ccodex3Edocument.forms[0].submit()x3C/codex3E.  The only way to get the onsubmit code generated in the form_remote_tag to execute is to create a hidden submit button, and invoke the click method on the button from the select tag.  Herex27s a working ERb partial example.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ex26lt;% form_remote_tag :url =x26gt; product_path, :update =x26gt; x27contentx27, :method =x26gt; x27getx27 do -%x26gt;\n  x26lt;% content_tag :div, :id =x26gt; x27contentx27 do -%x26gt;\n    x26lt;%= select_tag :update, options_for_select([[x22foox22, 1], [x22barx22, 2]]), :onchange =x26gt; x22this.form.commit.clickx22 %x26gt;\n    x26lt;%= submit_tag x27submit_buttonx27, :style =x26gt; x22display: nonex22 %x26gt;\n  x26lt;% end %x26gt;\nx26lt;% end %x26gt;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat I want to do is something like this, but it doesnx27t work.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ex26lt;% form_remote_tag :url =x26gt; product_path, :update =x26gt; x27contentx27, :method =x26gt; x27getx27 do -%x26gt;\n  x26lt;% content_tag :div, :id =x26gt; x27contentx27 do -%x26gt;\n    # the following line does not work\n    x26lt;%= select_tag :update, options_for_select([[x22foox22, 1], [x22barx22, 2]]), :onchange =x26gt; x22this.form.onsubmit()x22 %x26gt;\n  x26lt;% end %x26gt;\nx26lt;% end %x26gt;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo, is there any way to remove the invisible submit button for this use case?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThere seems to be some confusion.  So, let me explain.  The basic problem is that x3Ccodex3Esubmit()x3C/codex3E doesnx27t call the x3Ccodex3Eonsubmit()x3C/codex3E code rendered into the form.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe actual HTML form that Rails renders from this ERb looks like this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ex26lt;form action=x22/products/1x22 method=x22postx22 onsubmit=x22new Ajax.Updater(x27contentx27, x27/products/1x27, {asynchronous:true, evalScripts:true, method:x27getx27, parameters:Form.serialize(this)}); return false;x22x26gt;\n  x26lt;div style=x22margin:0;padding:0x22x26gt;\n    x26lt;input name=x22authenticity_tokenx22 type=x22hiddenx22 value=x224eacf78eb87e9262a0b631a8a6e417e9a5957cabx22 /x26gt;\n  x26lt;/divx26gt;\n  x26lt;div id=x22contentx22x26gt;\n    x26lt;select id=x22updatex22 name=x22updatex22 onchange=x22this.form.commit.clickx22x26gt;\n      x26lt;option value=x221x22x26gt;foox26lt;/optionx26gt;\n      x26lt;option value=x222x22x26gt;barx26lt;/optionx26gt;\n    x26lt;/selectx26gt;\n    x26lt;input name=x22commitx22 style=x22display: nonex22 type=x22submitx22 value=x22submit_buttonx22 /x26gt;\n  x26lt;/divx26gt;\nx26lt;/formx26gt;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI want to axe the invisible submit button, but using a straight form.submit appears to not work.  So, I need some way to call the formx27s onsubmit event code.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EUpdate: Orion Edwards solution would work if there wasnx27t a x3Ccodex3Ereturn(false);x3C/codex3E generated by Rails.  Ix27m not sure which is worse though, sending a phantom click to an invisible submit button or calling eval on the x3Ccodex3EgetAttribute(x27onsubmitx27)x3C/codex3E call after removing the return call with a javascript string replacement!   x3C/px3E',1,3,'prihak','2008-08-29 06:33:21'),(33960,'How do you get the ethernet address using Java?','x3Cpx3EI would like to retrieve the ethernet address of the network interface that is used to access a particular website.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow can this be done in Java?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3ESolutionx3C/strongx3E Note that the accepted solution of x3Ccodex3EgetHardwareAddressx3C/codex3E is only available in Java 6. There does not seem to be a solution for Java 5 aside from executing i(f|p)confing.x3C/px3E',1,3,'sfitzhenryv','2008-08-29 08:31:24'),(33990,'Canx27t create a subversion repository with Eclipse 3.4.0, svn 1.5.1','x3Cpx3EIx27m working on mac OS x 10.4. I have a subversion repository stored on an external drive connected via USB. I created a new python project in Eclipse (using the PyDev plugin). When I use right click Team-x3EShare Project to set up a new prject with subversion, I get the following error:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EError while creating module: org.tigris.subversion.javahl.ClientException: Couldnx27t open a repository\nsvn:  Unable to open ra_local session to URL\nsvn: Unable to open repository x27file:///Volumes/svn-repos/Palindrome/Palindromex27x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe subversion repository has the following permisions:\ndrwxrwxrwx     9 cameronl  cameronl   306 Aug 23 10:08 svn-reposx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe external drive is formatted as Mac OS extended.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m completely stumped. Anybody have any suggestions?x3C/px3E',1,2,'achancelier6','2008-08-29 09:12:07'),(34020,'Are Python threads buggy?','x3Cpx3EA reliable coder friend told me that Pythonx27s current multi-threading implementation is seriously buggy - enough to avoid using altogether.  What can said about this rumor?x3C/px3E',1,2,'ajan8','2008-08-29 09:43:16'),(34120,'HTML Scraping in Php','x3Cpx3EIx27ve been doing some html scraping in PHP using regular expressions.  This works, but the result is finicky and fragile.  Has anyone used any packages that provide a more robust solution?  A config driven solution would be ideal, but Ix27m not picky.x3C/px3E',1,4,'cleatham18','2008-08-29 11:32:15'),(34270,'COMException x22Library not registered.x22 while using System.DirectoryServices','x3Cpx3EI have only just started received the following error in my windows forms application under dot net 2 framework on windows 2000 when using System.DirectoryServices.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E    {System.Runtime.InteropServices.COMException}\nSystem.Runtime.InteropServices.COMException: {x22Library not registered.x22}\n_className: Nothing\n_COMPlusExceptionCode: -532459699\n_data: Nothing\n_dynamicMethods: Nothing\n_exceptionMethod: Nothing\n_exceptionMethodString: Nothing\n_helpURL: Nothing\n_HResult: -2147319779\n_innerException: Nothing\n_message: x22Library not registered.x22\n_remoteStackIndex: 0\n_remoteStackTraceString: Nothing\n_source: Nothing\n_stackTrace: {System.Array}\n_stackTraceString: Nothing\n_xcode: -532459699\n_xptrs: 0\nSource: x22System.DirectoryServicesx22\nStackTrace: x22   at System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry.Bind(Boolean throwIfFail)\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Eat System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry.Bind()\n   at System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry.get_AdsObject()\n   at System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.FindAll(Boolean findMoreThanOne)\n   at System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.FindAll()x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have re-installed the framework and re-registered activeds.dll however this has not resolved the issue. I am guessing I need to find another dll and re-register it however it is not clear which dll this would be.x3C/px3E',1,3,'aillidges','2008-08-29 13:41:56'),(34300,'Has .NET made raw COM and DCOM programming redundant?','x3Cpx3EHas the introduction of the .net framework made raw programming in COM and DCOM redundant ? x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3E(Except for using some COM+ services, e.g. for transaction management through the System.EnterpriseServices namespace)x3C/px3E',1,3,'mschafflere','2008-08-29 14:00:33'),(34390,'How to make user controls know about css classes in ASP.NET','x3Cpx3ESince there are no header sections for user controls in asp.net, user controls have no way of knowing about stylesheet files. So css classes in the user controls are not recognized by visual studio and produces warnings. How can I make a user control know that it will relate to a css class, so if it is warning me about a non-existing css class, it means that the class really do not exist?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEdit: Or should I go for a different design like exposing css classes as properties like x22HeaderStyle-CssClassx22 of GridView?x3C/px3E',1,8,'dsizland14','2008-08-29 15:37:54'),(34490,'How do I create a SHA1 hash in ruby?','x3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SHA-1x22x3ESHA Hash functionsx3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E',1,6,'mlowried','2008-08-29 19:49:08'),(34510,'What is a race condition?','x3Cpx3EWhen writing multi-threaded applications, one of the most common problems experienced are race conditions.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy questions to the community are:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat is a race condition? How do you detect them? How do you handle them? Finally, how do you prevent them from occurring?x3C/px3E',1,10,'dsizland14','2008-08-29 19:55:10'),(34570,'What is the best quick-read Python book out there?','x3Cpx3EI am taking a class that requires Python. We will review the language in class next week, and I am a quick study on new languages, but I was wondering if there are any really great Python books I can grab while I am struggling through the basics of setting up my IDE, server environment and all those other x22gotchasx22 that come with a new programming language. Suggestions?x3C/px3E',1,9,'aalandg','2008-08-29 20:10:41'),(34600,'Can you pair program remotely?','x3Cpx3EWe have a team of about 7 engineers, whom I supervise. We do not have a formal office where we all work. Instead, a handful are located outside of our city, while the rest of us are scattered around the Bay Area.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EQuite frequently, I find myself attempting to teach concepts like TDD or refactoring to some of our more junior (or not) developers. The best technique I know is pair programming, where you both sit at the same computer and work on a problem together. Since we are not in the same place most of the time, the only option is to use some kind of screen sharing and Skype to have one of us x22drivex22 while the other consults, and then switch.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy question is has anyone tried this x22virtualx22 pair programming, and did you find it at all useful?x3C/px3E',1,10,'hginglell13','2008-08-29 20:16:57'),(34790,'duplicating jQuery datepicker','x3Cpx3EThe x3Ccodex3Edatepickerx3C/codex3E function only works on the first input box that is created.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m trying to duplicate a datepicker by cloning the x3Ccodex3Edivx3C/codex3E that is containing it.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ex26lt;a href=x22#x22 id=x22dupMex22x26gt;clickx26lt;/ax26gt;\nx26lt;div id=x22templatex22x26gt;\ninput-text x26lt;input type=x22textx22 value=x22text1x22 id=x22txtx22 /x26gt;\ndate time picker x26lt;input type=x22textx22 id=x22examplex22 value=x22(add date)x22 /x26gt;\nx26lt;/divx26gt;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ETo initialize the datepicker, according to the x3Ca href=x22http://docs.jquery.com/UI/Datepickerx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EjQuery UI documentationx3C/ax3E I only have to do x3Ccodex3E$(x27#examplex27).datepicker();x3C/codex3E and it does work, but only on the first datepicker that is created.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe code to duplicate the x3Ccodex3Edivx3C/codex3E is the following:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E$(x22a#dupMex22).click(function(event){\n    event.preventDefault();\n    i++;\n    var a = $(x22#templatex22).clone(true).insertBefore(x22#templatex22).hide().fadeIn(1000);\n    a.find(x22input#txtx22).attr(x27valuex27, i);\n    a.find(x22input#examplex22).datepicker();\n});\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe strangest thing is that on the x3Ccodex3Edocument.readyx3C/codex3E I have:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E$(x27#template #examplex27).datepicker();\n$(x22#template #txtx22).click(function() { alert($(this).val()); });\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Eand if I click on the x3Ccodex3E#txtx3C/codex3E it always works.x3C/px3E',1,3,'rtomeo0','2008-08-29 21:19:25'),(34920,'How do I lock a file in Perl?','x3Cpx3EWhat is the best way to create a lock on a file in Perl?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs it best to flock on the file or to create a lock file to place a lock on and check for a lock on the lock file?x3C/px3E',1,6,'jsorel9','2008-08-29 22:13:21'),(35050,'Comparison of Javascript libraries','x3Cpx3EAfter the suggestion to use a library for x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/34486/what-more-is-needed-for-ajax-than-this-functionx22x3Emy ajax needsx3C/ax3E I am going to use one, the problem is that there are so many and Ix27ve no idea how to even begin telling them apart.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThus, can anybody x3Cbr /x3E\nA) Give a rundown of the differences or x3Cbr /x3E\nB) Point me (and others like me) somewhere that has such a list. \nx3Cbr /x3Ex3Cbr /x3EFailing that plan C is to go with whichever gets mentioned the most here.x3C/px3E',1,4,'mschafflere','2008-08-29 23:03:01'),(35070,'programmatically merge .reg file into win32 registry','x3Cpx3EWhatx27s the best way to programmatically merge a .reg file into the registry? This is for unit testing; the .reg file is a test artifact which will be added then removed at the start and end of testing.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EOr, if therex27s a better way to unit test against the registry...x3C/px3E',1,7,'dmatuszinski15','2008-08-29 23:09:47'),(35120,'Image processing in Silverlight 2','x3Cpx3EIs it possible to do image processing in silverlight 2.0?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat I want to do is take an image, crop it, and then send the new cropped image up to the server.  I know I can fake it by clipping the image, but that only effects the