it does not support uploading files. The only way to asynchronously upload files that I know of is using the hidden x3Ccodex3Eiframex3C/codex3E method.x3C/px3E',1,9,'cleatham18','2008-08-30 00:31:27'),(35320,'How do you get the last record generated in a recursive CTE?','x3Cpx3EIn the code below I am using a recursive CTE(Common Table Expression) in SQL Server 2005 to try and find the top level parent of a basic hierarchical structure. The rule of this hierarchy is that every CustID has a ParentID and if the CustID has no parent then the ParentID = CustID and it is the highest level.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EDECLARE @LookupID int\n\n--Our test value\nSET @LookupID = 1\n\nWITH cteLevelOne (ParentID, CustID) AS\n(\n    	SELECT   a.ParentID, a.CustID\n    	FROM     tblCustomer AS a\n    	WHERE    a.CustID = @LookupID\n    UNION ALL\n    	SELECT   a.ParentID, a.CustID\n    	FROM     tblCustomer AS a\n    	INNER JOIN cteLevelOne AS c ON a.CustID = c.ParentID\n    	WHERE c.CustID x26lt;x26gt; a.CustomerID\n)\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo if tblCustomer looks like this:  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EParentID    CustID\n5            5\n1            8\n5            4\n4            1\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe result I get from the code above is:  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EParentID    CustID\n4            1\n5            4\n5            5\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat I want is just the last row of that result:  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EParentID    CustID\n5            5\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow do I just return the last record generated in the CTE (which would be highest level CustID)?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAlso note that there are multiple unrelated CustID hierarchies in this table so I canx27t just do a SELECT * FROM tblCustomer WHERE ParentID = CustID. I canx27t order by ParentID or CustID because the ID number is not related to where it is in the hierarchy.x3C/px3E',1,11,'mschafflere','2008-08-30 01:19:24'),(35380,'Print Odd-Even numbers using signals','x3Cpx3EI need to to print natural nos. 1,2,...n such that the parent process prints all odd numbers and the child process prints all even numbers, and all of this needs to be done using POSIX signals. How would I go about accomplishing this?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe output should be:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EParent : 1x3Cbrx3E\nChild  : 2x3Cbrx3E\nParent : 3x3Cbrx3E\n...x3C/px3E',1,5,'mschafflere','2008-08-30 01:52:57'),(35420,'mysql software: any suggestions to oversee my mysql replication server?','x3Cpx3EIx27ve had a tough time setting up my replication server. Is there any program (OS X, Win, Linux or php no problem) that lets me monitor and resolve replication issues? (btw, for those -uhm- following, ive been on this issue x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/8166/mysql-replication-if-i-dont-specify-any-databases-will-logbin-log-everythingx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Eherex3C/ax3E, x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/3798/full-complete-mysql-db-replication-ideas-what-do-people-dox22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Eherex3C/ax3E, x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/8365/mysql-administrator-backups-compatibility-mode-what-exactly-is-this-doingx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Eherex3C/ax3E and x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/30660/mysql-binary-log-replication-can-it-be-set-to-ignore-errorsx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Eherex3C/ax3E. Either ix27m going about this the wrong way or i must be immensely thick)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy production database is several megs in size and growing. Every time the database replication stops and the databases inevitably begin to slide out of sync i cringe. My last resync from dump took almost 4 hours roundtrip!x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAs always, even after sync, I run into this kind of show-stopping errorx22:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EError x27Duplicate entry x27252440x27 for key 1x27 on query.\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI would love it if there was some way to closely monitor whats going on and perhaps let the software deal with it. Ix27m even all ears for service companies which may help me monitor my data better. Or an alternate way to mirror altogether.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EEditx3C/strongx3E: going through my previous questions i found x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/30660/mysql-binary-log-replication-can-it-be-set-to-ignore-errors#30889x22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Ethisx3C/ax3E which helps tremendously. Ix27m still all ears on the monitoring solution.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Echeers,x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3E/mpx3C/px3E',1,8,'abaterb','2008-08-30 02:30:03'),(35470,'Are there static analysis tools for Python?','x3Cpx3EI am starting to use Python (specifically because of Django) and I would like to remove the burden for exhaustive testing by performing some static analysis.  What tools/parameters/etc. exist to detect issues at compile time that would otherwise show up during runtime? (type errors are probably the most obvious case of this, but undefined variables are another big one that could be avoided with an in-depth analysis of the AST.)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EObviously testing is important, and I donx27t imply that tests can be obviated entirely; however, there are many runtime errors in python that are not possible in other languages that perform stricter run-time checking -- Ix27m hoping that there are tools to bring at least some of these capabilities to python as well.x3C/px3E',1,2,'abaterb','2008-08-30 03:44:29'),(35480,'How can I clear Class::DBIx27s internal cache?','x3Cpx3EIx27m currently working on a large implementation of Class::DBI for an existing database structure, and am running into a problem with clearing the cache from Class::DBI.  This is a mod_perl implementation, so an instance of a class can be quite old between times that it is accessed.\nFrom the man pages I found two options:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EMusic::DBI-x26gt;clear_object_index();\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnd:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EMusic::Artist-x26gt;purge_object_index_every(2000);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENow, when I add clear_object_index() to the DESTROY method, it seems to run, but doesnx27t actually empty the cache.  I am able to manually change the database, re-run the request, and it is still the old version.\npurge_object_index_every says that it clears the index every n requests.  Setting this to x221x22 or x220x22, seems to clear the index... sometimes.  Ix27d expect one of those two to work, but for some reason it doesnx27t do it every time.  More like 1 in 5 times.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny suggestions for clearing this out?x3C/px3E',1,5,'aa9279','2008-08-30 03:56:27'),(35490,'Spread vs MPI vs zeromq?','x3Cpx3EIn one of the answers to x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/31572/broadcast-like-udp-with-the-reliability-of-tcp#31629x22x3EBroadcast like UDP with the Reliability of TCPx3C/ax3E, a user mentions the x3Ca href=x22http://spread.orgx22x3ESpreadx3C/ax3E messaging API.  Ix27ve also run across one called x3Ca href=x22http://zeromq.orgx22x3EØMQx3C/ax3E.  I also have some familiarity with x3Ca href=x22http://www-unix.mcs.anl.gov/mpi/x22x3EMPIx3C/ax3E.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo, my main question is: why would I choose one over the other?  More specifically, why would I choose to use Spread or ØMQ when there are mature implementations of MPI to be had?x3C/px3E',1,5,'hbuxcy1c','2008-08-30 04:07:41'),(35530,'What Are High-Pass and Low-Pass Filters?','x3Cpx3EGraphics and audio editing and processing software often contain functions called x22High-Pass Filterx22 and x22Low-Pass Filterx22.  Exactly what do these do, and what are the algorithms for implementing them?x3C/px3E',1,1,'cgaweno','2008-08-30 04:55:26'),(35560,'Lazy Loading with a WCF Service Domain Model?','x3Cpx3EIx27m looking to push my domain model into a WCF Service API and wanted to get some thoughts on lazy loading techniques with this type of setup.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny suggestions when taking this approach?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ewhen I implemented this technique and step into my app, just before the server returns my list it hits the get of each property that is supposed to be lazy loaded ... Thus eager loading. Could you explain this issue or suggest a resolution?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEdit:  It x3Ca href=x22http://benders-blog.blogspot.com/2007/01/lazy-loading-in-soa-world.htmlx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Eappearsx3C/ax3E you can use the XMLIgnore attribute so it doesn’t get looked at during serialization .. still reading up on this thoughx3C/px3E',1,4,'dsizland14','2008-08-30 05:46:19'),(35670,'How do I begin using SVN?','x3Cpx3EI am ready to start using SVN, but I have NO (as in the money required for free beer) experience with source control.  I have installed subversion on my server (that was easy, x27apt-get install subversionx27) but now I donx27t know what to do, how to configure it, or how to use it.x3Cbr /x3Ex3Cbr /x3EWhat suggestions do you have, and where can I find good resources to learn to start using it?x3Cbr /x3Ex3Cbr /x3E\nUpdate:x3Cbr /x3E\nO.K. So the feedback has been great and I have read through a bit of it but I want to clarify my question by saying that I am looking for more information on how to actually go about setting my up my repositories, clients, server, etc.  I know that I could do a quick Google search and find dozens (or more) resources but Ix27m hoping that someone whom has experience with subversion and a client(I have installed tortoise) could suggest a good reference that will be reliable, and have quality content.x3C/px3E',1,1,'idevey11','2008-08-30 08:01:55'),(35700,'Writing cross-platform apps in C','x3Cpx3EWhat things should be kept most in mind when writing cross-platform applications in C? Targeted platforms: 32-bit Intel based PC, Mac, and Linux. Ix27m especially looking for the type of versatility that Jungle Disk has in their USB desktop edition ( x3Ca href=x22http://www.jungledisk.com/desktop/download.aspxx22x3Ehttp://www.jungledisk.com/desktop/download.aspxx3C/ax3E )x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat are tips and x22gotchasx22 for this type of development?x3C/px3E',1,7,'achancelier6','2008-08-30 09:30:24'),(35720,'Getting started with SideShow Devices','x3Cpx3EIs there a recommendation for a hardware platform for developing/testing SideShow devices, or is the Emulator adequate?x3C/px3E',1,2,'dmatuszinski15','2008-08-30 09:57:13'),(35870,'Comparison of Lat, Long Coordinates','x3Cpx3EI have a list of more than 15 thousand latitude and longitude coordinates.  Given any X,Y coordinates, what is the fastest way to find the closest coordinates on the list?x3C/px3E',1,3,'eburnyaten','2008-08-30 14:34:05'),(35940,'Elegant Snippets of F#','x3Cpx3EIx27m currently learning F# quite intensively. I really love it as a language, it just sort of x27feelsx27 right and seems to allow you to produce some succint elegant code.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m interested in finding some really nice x27wow factorx27 snippets of F# code which demonstate the elegence of the language, especially compared to C#. For example I really like:-x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3E\n#light\nlet ListProduct l = List.fold_left (*) 1 l\nx3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhich inputs a list of ints and multiplies each element in the list, i.e. obtains the product of the list (e.g. a list of 1,2,3 would be calculated as 1*2*3=6). The closest C# equivilent, using LINQ and functional concepts is as follows:-x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eusing System;\nusing System.Collections.Generic;\nusing System.Linq;\n\n...\n\npublic static class ListHelper {\n  public static int ListProduct(Listx26lt;intx26gt; l) {\n    return l.Aggregate(1, (i, j) =x26gt; i * j);\n  }\n}    \nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBefore LINQ that would have been:-x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eusing System;\nusing System.Collections.Generic;\n\n...\n\npublic static class ListHelper {\n  public static int ListProduct(Listx26lt;intx26gt; l) {\n    int ret = 1;\n    foreach (int i in l) ret *= i;\n    return ret;\n  }\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m certainly not trying to criticise C# here, I think itx27s a wonderful language, itx27s just nice to see how F# compares and to see how it can do some things more elegantly - does anyone have anything really nice?x3C/px3E',1,3,'fbrizellc','2008-08-30 16:53:58'),(35950,'I donx27t understand std::tr1::unordered_map','x3Cpx3EI need an associative container that makes me index a certain object through a string, but that also keeps the order of insertion, so I can look for a specific object by its name or just iterate on it and retrieve objects in the same order I inserted them.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI think this x3Ca href=x22http://www.ddj.com/cpp/184406207x22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3Ehybrid of linked list and hash mapx3C/ax3E should do the job, but before I tried to use x3Ccodex3Estd::tr1::unordered_mapx3C/codex3E thinking that it was working in that way I described, but it wasnx27t. So could someone explain me the meaning and behavior of x3Ccodex3Eunordered_mapx3C/codex3E?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3E@wesc: Ix27m sure std::map is implemented by STL, while Ix27m sure std::hash_map is NOT in the STL (I think older version of Visual Studio put it in a namespace called stdext).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3E@cristopher: so, if I get it right, the difference is in the implementation (and thus performances), not in the way it behaves externally.x3C/px3E',1,2,'aa9279','2008-08-30 17:20:42'),(36030,'Yaws uses old config file','x3Cpx3EIx27m developing a web app on Yaws 1.65 (installed through apt) running on Debian etch on a VPS with UML.  Whenever I do /etc/init.d/yaws restart or a stop/start, it initializes according to an old version of the config file (/etc/yaws/yaws.conf).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI know this because I changed the docroot from the default to another directory (call it A), then a few weeks later changed it to directory B, and the config file has stayed with B for the last several months.  But then, after a restart, it switches back to A.  If it switched back to the package default, that would be understandable, but it switches to an old customized version instead.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe funny thing is that if I leave it stopped for several minutes, when I start it again, everything switches back to normal (using directory B).  But while itx27s stopped, if I run ps, I donx27t see any yaws-related processes (yaws, heart, etc).  This problem has survived several reboots, so itx27s got to be an old cached copy of the config somewhere, but I have yet to find anything like that.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny idea what could be going on?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EUpdate:\n@Gorgapor - I stopped yaws, renamed the config file and tried to start it again.  It failed to start.  However, I was able to restart a couple of times and this time it didnx27t switch back to the old version.x3C/px3E',1,7,'dmatuszinski15','2008-08-30 19:15:01'),(36260,'Dealing with circular dependencies in OCaml','x3Cpx3EIx27m writing an interpreter for an experimental language. Three of the main constructs of the language are definitions, statements, and expressions. Definitions can contain statements and expressions, statements can contain definitions and expressions, and one kind of expression can contain statements. I represent all of these using union types so I can easily use pattern matching on them. Ideally, I would like to put the code for these in different files, but OMake complains about circular dependency issues. As far as I know, circular type definitions across modules are not allowed.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe only way I know of to solve this is to define all three types at once:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Etype defn = ...\nand stmt = ...\nand expr = ...\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIt seems like this requires all the code for types to be in the same file. Is there any way around this? How do you deal with circular definitions in your code?x3C/px3E',1,4,'sdally1','2008-08-30 23:06:44'),(36350,'How to pass a single object[] to a params object[]','x3Cpx3EI have a method which takes params object[] such as:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Evoid Foo(params object[] items)\n{\n    Console.WriteLine(items[0]);\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhen I pass two object arrays to this method, it works fine:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EFoo(new object[]{ (object)x221x22, (object)x222x22 }, new object[]{ (object)x223x22, (object)x224x22 } );\n// Output: System.Object[]\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBut when I pass a single object[], it does not take my object[] as the first param, instead it takes its all elements like I wanted to pass them one by one:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EFoo(new object[]{ (object)x221x22, (object)x222x22 });\n// Output: 1, expected: System.Object[]\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow do I pass a single object[] as a first argument to a params array?x3C/px3E',1,2,'clawrence3','2008-08-31 01:22:06'),(36430,'What are the important Ruby commands?','x3Cpx3EIx27m not sure of all of them, but what are the commands to do things like update Ruby, download a new gem, or update an existing gem? What other important things are there?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESince it might matter, Ix27m running Windows.x3C/px3E',1,1,'prihak','2008-08-31 02:36:52'),(36600,'Viewing DirectX application remotely','x3Cpx3EWex27re working on an application that displays information through a Direct3D visualisation. A late client request is the ability to view this application via some Remote Desktop solution.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHas anyone done anything similar? What options are available / unavailable? Ix27m thinking RDC, VNC, Citrix...x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny advice?x3C/px3E',1,5,'aalandg','2008-08-31 07:05:52'),(36760,'SQL Query, Count with 0 count','x3Cpx3EI have three tables: page, attachment, page-attachmentx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have data like this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Epage\nID    NAME\n1     first page\n2     second page\n3     third page\n4     fourth page\n\nattachment\nID    NAME\n1     foo.word\n2     test.xsl\n3     mm.ppt\n\npage-attachment\nID    PAGE-ID   ATTACHMENT-ID\n1     2         1\n2     2         2\n3     3         3\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI would like to get the number of attachments per page x3Cstrongx3Ealso when that number is 0x3C/strongx3E. I have tried with: x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eselect page.name, count(page-attachment.id) as attachmentsnumber \nfrom page \n    inner join page-attachment on page.id=page-id \ngroup by page.id\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI am getting this output: x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3ENAME        ATTACHMENTSNUMBER\nsecond page  2\nthird page   1\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI would like to get this output:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3ENAME        ATTACHMENTSNUMBER\nfirst page   0\nsecond page  2\nthird page   1\nfourth page  0\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow do I get the 0 part?x3C/px3E',1,11,'aauger2','2008-08-31 14:39:58'),(36820,'Version Control for word documents','x3Cpx3EHow would people recommend doing version control for word documents? Is the in build control up to the job or is it better to rely on dedicated version control systems, and if so, which ones?x3C/px3E',1,7,'sfitzhenryv','2008-08-31 16:23:55'),(36890,'Changing a CORBA interface without recompiling','x3Cpx3EIx27d like to add a method to my existing serverx27s CORBA interface. Will that require recompiling all clients?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m using TAO.x3C/px3E',1,4,'chenburyh','2008-08-31 18:44:18'),(37030,'How to best implement software updates on windows?','x3Cpx3EI want to implement an x22automatic updatex22 system for  a windows application. \nRight now Ix27m semi-manually creating an x3Ca href=x22http://connectedflow.com/appcasting/x22x3Ex22appcastx22x3C/ax3E which my program checks, and notifies the user that a new version is available. (Ix27m using\n x3Ca href=x22http://nsis.sourceforge.net/Main_Pagex22x3ENSISx3C/ax3E for my installers).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there software that I can use that will handle the x22automaticx22 part of the updates, perhaps similar to  x3Ca href=x22http://sparkle.andymatuschak.org/x22x3ESparklex3C/ax3E on the mac? Any issues/pitfalls that I should be aware of?x3C/px3E',1,9,'tvallentint','2008-08-31 22:57:29'),(37070,'What is the meaning of x22non temporalx22 memory accesses in x86','x3Cpx3EThis is a somewhat low-level question.  In x86 assembly there are two SSE instructions: x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3Ex3Ccodex3EMOVDQA x3Cix3Ex3Cemx3Exmmi, m128x3C/emx3Ex3C/ix3Ex3C/codex3Ex3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Eand  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3Ex3Ccodex3EMOVNTDQA x3Cix3Ex3Cemx3Exmmi, m128x3C/emx3Ex3C/ix3Ex3C/codex3Ex3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe IA-32 Software Developerx27s Manual says that the x3Cemx3ENTx3C/emx3E in MOVNTDQA stands for x3Cemx3ENon-Temporalx3C/emx3E, and that otherwise itx27s the same as MOVDQA.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy question is, what does x3Cemx3ENon-Temporalx3C/emx3E mean?  x3C/px3E',1,7,'fbrizellc','2008-09-01 00:18:34'),(37310,'Checking the results of a Factory in a unit test','x3Cpx3EI have developed some classes with similar behavior, they all implement the same interface.  I implemented a factory that creates the appropriate object and returns the interface.  I am writing a unit test for the factory.  All you get back is an interface to the object.\nWhat is the best way to test that the factory has worked correctly?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI would like to know the answer in Java, but if there is a solution that crosses languages I would like to know it.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENumber 2. in the answer, would be done like the other answer?  If so I will mark the other answer accepted as well and reword my question to adress both a factory where an interface is returned and you have no clue what type of concrete class implemented the interface, and the case where you do know what concrete class was used.x3C/px3E',1,1,'hschade12','2008-09-01 04:40:03'),(37590,'How to convert .ICO to .PNG?','x3Cp