tive javascript api to do this, but I assumed someone would have already written a wrapper to easily integrate this into an ASP.NET application.x3C/px3E',1,7,'kgrenkovu','2008-09-01 19:49:49'),(38090,'How to prevent Write Ahead Logging on just one table in PostgreSQL?','x3Cpx3EI am considering log-shipping of x3Ca href=x22http://www.postgresql.org/docs/8.2/static/runtime-config-wal.htmlx22x3EWrite Ahead Logs (WAL)x3C/ax3E in PostgreSQL to create a warm-standby database. However I have one table in the database that receives a huge amount of INSERT/DELETEs each day, but which I donx27t care about protecting the data in it. To reduce the amount of WALs produced I was wondering, x3Cstrongx3Eis there a way to prevent any activity on one table from being recorded in the WALs?x3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E',1,11,'rtomeo0','2008-09-01 20:03:55'),(38160,'Parallelize Bash Script with maximum number of processes','x3Cpx3ELets say I have a loop in bash:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Efor foo in `some-command`\ndo\n   do-something $foo\ndone\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ccodex3Edo-somethingx3C/codex3E is cpu bound and I have a nice shiny 4 core processor. Ix27d like to be able to run up to 4 x3Ccodex3Edo-somethingx3C/codex3Ex27s at once.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe naive approach seems to be:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Efor foo in `some-command`\ndo\n   do-something $foo x26amp;\ndone\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis will run x3Cemx3Eallx3C/emx3E x3Ccodex3Edo-somethingx3C/codex3Es at once, but there are a couple downsides, mainly that do-something may also have some significant I/O which performing x3Cemx3Eallx3C/emx3E at once might slow down a bit. The other problem is that this code block returns immediately, so no way to do other work when all the x3Ccodex3Edo-somethingx3C/codex3Es are finished.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow would you write this loop so there are always X x3Ccodex3Edo-somethingx3C/codex3Es running at once?x3C/px3E',1,2,'gdodding5','2008-09-01 20:47:53'),(38190,'How do 