e integer in primary key column','x3Cpx3EIx27m just getting dirty in WinForms, and Ix27ve discovered, through a lovely tutorial, the magic of dragging a database table onto the design view of my main form. So, all is lovely, Ix27ve got my DataGridView with all of the columns represented beautifully.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBUT...x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhen I run my application against this brand new, empty .sdf (empty save for the two tables Ix27ve created, which are themselves empty), I get a -1 in the column corresponding to my primary key/identity column whenever I try to create that first record.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny idea why this might be happening? If it helps, the column is an x3Ccodex3Eintx3C/codex3E.x3C/px3E',1,11,'idevey11','2008-09-02 02:01:25'),(38670,'ASP.NET controls cannot be referenced in code-behind in Visual Studio 2008','x3Cpx3EOk, so, my visual studio is broken. I say this NOT prematurely, as it was my first response to see where I had messed up in my code. When I add controls to the page I canx27t reference all of them in the code behind. Some of them I can, it seems that the first few I put on a page work, then it just stops. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI first thought it may be the type of control as initially I was trying to reference a repeater inside an update panel. I know I am correctly referencing the code behind in my aspx page. But just in case it was a  screw up on my part I started to recreate the page from scratch and this time got a few more controls down before VS stopped recognizing my controls.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAfter creating my page twice and getting stuck I thought maybe it was still the type of controls. I created a new page and just threw some labels on it. No dice, build fails when referencing the control from the code behind. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn a possibly unrelated note when I switch to the dreaded x22designx22 mode of the aspx pages VS 2008 errors out and restarts. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have already put a trouble ticket in to Microsoft. I uninstalled all add-ins, I reinstalled visual studio. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnyone that wants to see my code just ask, but I am using the straight WYSIWYG visual studio x22new aspx pagex22 nothing fancy.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI doubt anyone has run into this, but have you? x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHas anyone had success trouble shooting these things with Microsoft? Any way to expedite this ticket without paying??? I have been talking to a rep from Microsoft for days with no luck yet and I am dead in the water. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThank you. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Chr /x3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EJon Limjap:x3C/strongx3E I edited the title to both make it clear and descriptive x3Cemx3Eandx3C/emx3E make sure that nobody sees it as offensive. x22Foo-barredx22 doesnx27t exactly constitute a proper question title, although your question is clearly a valid one.x3C/px3E',1,5,'hbuxcy1c','2008-09-02 05:10:54'),(38680,'How to provide next page of updated content?','x3Cpx3EFeel free to edit the title if you know how to formulate the question better. (Tagging is a problem as well.) The problem may be too difficult in this general form, so let us consider a concrete example.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EYou get a screenful of stackoverflow questions by requesting x3Ccodex3E/questions ?sort=newestx3C/codex3E page. Next page link leads to x3Ccodex3E/questions?page=2 x26amp;sort=newestx3C/codex3E. I suppose that at server side, the request is translated into an SQL query with LIMIT clause. Problem with this approach is, that if new question were added while user browses first page, his second page will start with some questions he already saw. (If he has 10 question per page, and 10 new questions happened to be added, he’ll get exactly the same content second time!)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there an elegant way to solve this common problem? I realize that it is not that big a problem, at least not for stackoverflow, but still.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe best idea I have (apart from storing request history per client) is to use x3Ccodex3E/questions?answer_id=NNNx3C/codex3E format. Server returns a page that starts with the requested answer, and puts the id of the first answer on the next page into next page link. There must be a way to write SQL for that, right? x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs it how it usually done? Or there is a better way?x3C/px3E',1,1,'msmallpeacex','2008-09-02 05:25:18'),(38820,'Which class design is better?','x3Cpx3EWhich class design is better and why?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Epublic class User\n{\n    public String UserName;\n    public String Password;\n    public String FirstName;\n    public String LastName;\n}\n\npublic class Employee : User\n{\n    public String EmployeeId;\n    public String EmployeeCode;\n    public String DepartmentId;\n}\n\npublic class Member : User\n{\n    public String MemberId;\n    public String JoinDate;\n    public String ExpiryDate;\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EORx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Epublic class User\n{\n    public String UserId;\n    public String UserName;\n    public String Password;\n    public String FirstName;\n    public String LastName;\n}\n\npublic class Employee\n{\n    public User UserInfo;\n    public String EmployeeId;\n    public String EmployeeCode;\n    public String DepartmentId;\n}\n\npublic class Member\n{\n    public User UserInfo;\n    public String MemberId;\n    public String JoinDate;\n    public String ExpiryDate;\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E',1,6,'itrowla','2008-09-02 08:34:20'),(38870,'One or Two Primary Keys in Many-to-Many Table?','x3Cpx3EI have the following tables in my database that have a many-to-many relationship, which is expressed by a connecting table that has foreign keys to the primary keys of each of the main tables:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3EWidget: WidgetID (PK), Title, Price  x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EUser: UserID (PK), FirstName, LastNamex3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAssume that each User-Widget combination is unique. I can see two options for how to structure the connecting table that defines the data relationship:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Colx3E\nx3Clix3EUserWidgets1: UserWidgetID (PK), WidgetID (FK), UserID (FK)  x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EUserWidgets2: WidgetID (PK, FK), UserID (PK, FK)x3C/lix3E\nx3C/olx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EOption 1 has a single column for the Primary Key. However, this seems unnecessary since the only data being stored in the table is the relationship between the two primary tables, and this relationship itself can form a unique key. Thus leading to option 2, which has a two-column primary key, but loses the one-column unique identifier that option 1 has. I could also optionally add a two-column unique index (WidgetID, UserID) to the first table.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there any real difference between the two performance-wise, or any reason to prefer one approach over the other for structuring the UserWidgets many-to-many table?x3C/px3E',1,8,'wscreen1b','2008-09-02 09:21:36'),(38890,'Enforce constraint checking only when inserting rows in MSSQL?','x3Cpx3EIs there a way to enforce constraint checking in MSSQL only when inserting new rows?  I.e. allow the constraints to be violated when removing/updating rows?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EUpdate: I mean FK constraint.x3C/px3E',1,9,'prihak','2008-09-02 09:34:35'),(38920,'php mail() not working windows 2003, IIS SMTP','x3Cpx3EIx27m getting this problem:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EPHP Warning: mail() [function.mail]: SMTP server response: 550 5.7.1 Unable to relay for chris.mahan@gmail.com in c:\\inetpub\\wwwroot\\mailtest.php on line 12 \nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Efrom this script:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ex26lt;?php\n$to = x22chris.mahan@gmail.comx22;\n$subject = x22testx22;\n$body = x22this is a testx22;\n\nif (mail($to, $subject, $body)){\n    echo x22mail sentx22;\n}\nelse {\n    echo x22problemx22;\n}\n?x26gt;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Esection from php.ini on the server:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E[mail function]\n; For Win32 only.\nSMTP = server.domain.com; for Win32 only\nsmtp_port = 25\n\n; For Win32 only.\nsendmail_from = support@domain.com\n; For Unix only.  You may supply arguments as well (default: x22sendmail -t -ix22).\n;sendmail_path =\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3E(note that x22serverx22 and x22domainx22 refer accurately to the actual server and domain name)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn IIS, SMTP is running. Under x3Ccodex3Ex22Accessx22x3C/codex3E tab, x3Ccodex3Ex22Relayx22x3C/codex3E button, the Select which computers may relay through this virtual server is set to x3Ccodex3Echeckbox x22only the list belowx22x3C/codex3E and on the list is x3Ccodex3Ex22127.0.0.1(xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx)x22 (xx27s representing actual server IP address).x3C/codex3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EServer is running x3Ccodex3EWindows Server 2003 Service Pack 2x3C/codex3E, fully patched as of 5 PM Sept 1st 2008. I assume it is running x3Ccodex3EIIS7x3C/codex3E (how to check?).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny ideas?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn reponse to x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/users/2257/espox22x3EEspox3C/ax3E: This machine is hosted at a datacenter. We do not want to use a gmail account (were doing it, want to move away from that). Windows server 2003 comes with its own SMTP server.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EUpdate: Per Yaakov Ellisx27 advice, I dropped all relay restrictions and added the server  IP to the allowed list (using the reverse DNS button provided) and the thing started working.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThanks to both Espo and Yaakov for helping me out.x3C/px3E',1,7,'gdodding5','2008-09-02 10:15:57'),(38940,'Generate field in MySQL SELECT','x3Cpx3EIf Ix27ve got a table containing Field1 and Field2 can I generate a new field in the select statement? For example, a normal query would be:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3ESELECT Field1, Field2 FROM Table\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnd I want to also create Field3 and have that returned in the resultset... something along the lines of this would be ideal:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3ESELECT Field1, Field2, Field3 = x27Valuex27 FROM Table\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs this possible at all?x3C/px3E',1,6,'cleatham18','2008-09-02 10:50:58'),(38960,'How to find out if a file exists in C# / .NET?','x3Cpx3EI would like to test a string containing a path to a file for existence of that file (something like the x3Ccodex3E-ex3C/codex3E test in Perl or the x3Ccodex3Eos.path.exists()x3C/codex3E in Python) in C#.x3C/px3E',1,10,'hschade12','2008-09-02 11:18:48'),(39070,'Programmable, secure FTP replacement','x3Cpx3EWe need to move off traditional FTP for security purposes (it transmits itx27s passwords unencrypted). I am hearing SSH touted as the obvious alternative. However I have been driving FTP from an ASP.NET program interface to automate my web-site development, which is now quite a highly web-enabled process. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECan anyone recommend a secure way to transfer files around which has a program interface that I can drive from ASP.NET?x3C/px3E',1,4,'rmaccurlyer','2008-09-02 13:06:04'),(39240,'x22Similar Postsx22 like functionality using MS SQL Server?','x3Cpx3EI have lots of article store in MS SQL server 2005 database in a table called Articles-x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ex22Articles (ArticleID, ArticleTitle, ArticleContent)x22\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENow I want some SP or SQL query which could return me similar Article against any userx27s input (very much like x22Similar Postsx22 in blogs OR x22Related Questionsx22 in stackoverflow). The matching should work on both ArticleTitle and ArticleContent. The query should be intelligent enough to sort the result on the basis on their relevancy.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs it possible to do this in MS SQL Server 2005?x3C/px3E',1,5,'clawrence3','2008-09-02 15:12:35'),(39770,'What do you call the tags in Subversion and CVS that add automatic content?','x3Cpx3EThings like x3Ccodex3E$log$x3C/codex3E and x3Ccodex3E$version$x3C/codex3E which add data upon check-in to the file. Ix27m interested in seeing the other ones and what information they can provide, but I canx27t get much info unless I know what they are called.x3C/px3E',1,9,'clawrence3','2008-09-02 19:17:16'),(39780,'How do I check job status from SSIS control flow?','x3Cpx3EHerex27s my scenario - I have an SSIS job that depends on another prior SSIS job to run. I need to be able to check the first jobx27s status before I kick off the second one. Itx27s not feasible to add the 2nd job into the workflow of the first one, as it is already way too complex. I want to be able to check the first jobx27s status (Failed, Successful, Currently Executing) from the second onex27s, and use this as a condition to decide whether the second one should run, or wait for a retry. I know this can be done by querying the MSDB database on the SQL Server running the job. Ix27m wondering of there is an easier way, such as possibly using the WMI Data Reader Task? Anyone had this experience?x3C/px3E',1,9,'tyurkiewicz19','2008-09-02 19:19:50'),(39910,'How to use the SharePoint MultipleLookupField control?','x3Cpx3EI want to use the  MultipleLookupField control in a web page that will run in the context of SharePoint. I was wondering if anyone would help me with an example, which shows step by step how to use the control two display two SPField Collections.x3C/px3E',1,7,'fbrizellc','2008-09-02 20:14:06'),(39960,'javascript locals()?','x3Cpx3EIn python one can get a dictionary of all local and global variables in the current scope with the built-in functions locals() and globals().  Is there some equivalent way of doing this in javascript?  For instance, I would like to do something like the following:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Evar foo = function(){ alert(x27foox27); };\nvar bar = function(){ alert(x27barx27); };\n\nvar s = x27foox27;\nlocals()[s](); // alerts x27foox27\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs this at all possible, or should I just be using a local object for the lookup?x3C/px3E',1,1,'jsorel9','2008-09-02 20:29:30'),(40090,'Is overloading the only way to have default function arguments in C#?','x3Cpx3EIs it true that the only way to handle default function arguments is through function overloading?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EFor example, in PHP I can do this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Efunction foo($x, $y=0)\n{\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWould the best way to handle it in C# be this?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Evoid foo(int x)\n{\n  foo(x, 0);\n}\n\nvoid foo(int x, int y)\n{\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3Ex3Cemx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://bytes.com/forum/thread224970.htmlx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EExample lifted from herex3C/ax3Ex3C/emx3Ex3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEditx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3Ex3Cemx3EMade the C# example into actual C# (Thanks Blair Conrad)x3C/emx3Ex3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E',1,5,'achancelier6','2008-09-02 21:25:56'),(40230,'GUIDs as Primary Keys - Offline OLTP','x3Cpx3EWe are working on designing an application that is typically OLTP (think: purchasing system). However, this one in particular has the need that some users will be offline, so they need to be able to download the DB to their machine, work on it, and then sync back once theyx27re on the LAN.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI would like to note that I know this has been done before, I just donx27t have experience with this particular model.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EOne idea I thought about was using GUIDs as table keys. So for example, a Purchase Order would not have a number (auto-numeric) but a GUID instead, so that every offline client can generate those, and I donx27t have clashes when I connect back to the DB.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs this a bad idea for some reason?\nWill access to these tables through the GUID key be slow?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHave you had experience with these type of systems? How have you solved this problem?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThanks!x3Cbr /x3E\nDanielx3C/px3E',1,1,'tyurkiewicz19','2008-09-02 22:35:36'),(40480,'Is Java x22pass-by-referencex22 or x22pass-by-valuex22?','x3Cpx3EI always thought Java was x3Cstrongx3Epass-by-referencex3C/strongx3E; however Ix27ve seen a couple of blog posts (for example, x3Ca href=x22http://javadude.com/articles/passbyvalue.htmx22x3Ethis blogx3C/ax3E) that claim itx27s not. I donx27t think I understand the distinction theyx27re making. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat is the explanation?x3C/px3E',1,7,'aillidges','2008-09-03 00:14:29'),(40590,'jQuery and Prototype Selector Madness','x3Cpx3EBoth the jQuery and Prototpye JavaScript libraries refuse to allow me to use a variable to select an list item element by index number although they accept a hard coded number. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EFor example, in Prototype this works:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E$$(x27lix27)[5].addClassName(x27activex27);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBut this will not work no matter how I try to cast the variable as a number or integer:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E$$(x27lix27)[currentPage].addClassName(x27activex27);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn jQuery I get similar weirdness. This will work:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EjQuery(x27lix27).eq(5).addClass(x22activex22);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBut this will not work again even though the value of currentPage is 5 and its type is number:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EjQuery(x27lix27).eq(currentPage).addClass(x22activex22);\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m trying to create a JavaScript pagination system and I need to set the class on the active page button. The list item elements are created dynamically depending upon the number of pages I need.x3C/px3E',1,7,'clawrence3','2008-09-03 00:41:21'),(40680,'How do I get the full url of the page I am on in C#','x3Cpx3EI need to be able to get at the full URL of the page I am on from a user control.  Is it just a matter of concatenating a bunch of Request variables together?  If so which ones? Or is there a more simpiler way?x3C/px3E',1,7,'itrowla','2008-09-03 01:09:44'),(40730,'How do you give a C# Auto-Property a default value?','x3Cpx3EHow do you give a C# Auto-Property a default value?  I either use the constructor, or revert to the old syntax. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3E Using the Constructor:x3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eclass Person \n{\n    public Person()\n    {\n        Name = x22Default Namex22;\n    }\n    public string Name { get; set; }\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EUsing normal property syntaxx3C/strongx3E  (with a default value)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eprivate string name = x22Default Namex22;\npublic string Name \n{\n    get \n    {\n        return name;\n    }\n    set\n    {\n        name = value;\n    }\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there a better way?x3C/px3E',1,4,'rtomeo0','2008-09-03 01:29:41'),(40840,'Cannot create an environment variable in the registry','x3Cpx3EI have a custom installer action that updates the PATH environment, and creates an additional environment variable. Appending a directory to the existing path variable is working fine, but for some reason my attempts to create a new environment variable have been unsuccessful. The code I am using is:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E        using (RegistryKey reg = Registry.LocalMachine.OpenSubKey(@x22SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\Environmentx22, true))\n        {\n            reg.SetValue(x22MYVARx22, x22SomeValx22, RegistryValueKind.ExpandString);\n        }\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEdit: The OS is 32-bit XP, and as far as I can tell it is failing silently.x3C/px3E',1,3,'nivakhnov17','2008-09-03 02:34:03'),(41010,'Smarty integration into the Code Igniter framework','x3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EA Little Background Informationx3C/strongx3E:x3Cbrx3E\nIx27ve been looking at a few PHP framework recently, and it came down to two. The Zend Framework or CodeIgniter. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI prefer CodeIgniter, because of its simple design. Itx27s very bare bone, and it is just kept simple. The thing I donx27t like though is the weak template system. The template system is important for me, because I will be working with another designer. Being able to give him a good template system is a big plus.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EZend was the second choice, because of the better template system that is built in. Zend is a different beast though compared to CodeIgniter. It emphasis x22loose coupling between modulesx22, but is a bigger framework. I donx27t like to feel like I have many things running under the hood that I never use. That is unnecessary overhead in my opinion, so I thought about putting a template system into CodeIgniter: Smarty.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EQuestion(s)x3C/strongx3E: How easy/hard is the process to integrate Smarty into CodeIgniter? From my initial scan of the CodeIgniter documentation, I can see that the layout of the framework is easy enough to understand, and I anticipate no problems. I want to know if anyone has used it before, and therefore are aware of any x22gotchasx22 you my have experienced that is going to make this harder than it should be or impossible to pull off. I also want to know if this is a good thing to do at all. Is the template system in CodeIgniter enough for normal use? Are there any other template modules that are good for CodeIgniter aside from Smarty? I better off with Zend Framework? Is any wheel being invented here? Thank you for your help! x3C/px3E',1,2,'msmallpeacex','2008-09-03 05:18:45'),(41050,'Where do you store your database connectionstring?','x3Cpx3EI usually store my connectionstring in web.config or in the application settings of my Visual Studio project. The application Ix27m currently working on makes a lot of trips to the database which means it will look up the connectionstring every time. Should I be putting the connectionstring in the cache or should I be looking at storing the whole SqlConnection object in the cache to eliminate the need to open and close them all the time?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EUpdatex3C/strongx3E: Seems like the consensus is to store the connection string in a configuration file and leave the caching in the trusting hand of ADO.NETx3C/px3E',1,1,'mheyward10','2008-09-03 06:12:34'),(41220,'Is there a best .NET algorithm for credit card encryption?','x3Cpx3EThe .NET x3Ccodex3ESystem.Security.Cryptographyx3C/codex3E namespace has a rather bewildering collection of algorithms that I could use for encryption of credit card details. Which is the best?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIt clearly needs to be secure for a relatively short string. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEDIT: Ix27m in the UK, where I understand wex27re OK storing encrypted credit card details so long as the three-digit CVV number is never stored. And thanks all for the great responses.x3C/px3E',1,7,'wscreen1b','2008-09-03 09:46:20'),(41290,'File Access Strategy in a Multi-Threaded Environment (Web App)','x3Cpx3EI have a file which is an XML representation of some data that is taken from a Web service and cached locally within a Web Application. The idea being is that this data is x3Cemx3Everyx3C/emx3E static, but just x3Cemx3Emightx3C/emx3E change. So I have set it up to cache to a file, and stuck a monitor against it to check if it has been deleted. Once deleted, the file will be refreshed from its source and rebuilt.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI am now running in to problems though, because obviously in a multi-threaded environment it falls over as it is trying to access the data when it is still reading/writing the file.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis is confusing me, because I added a object to lock against, and this is always locked during read/write. It was my understanding that attempted access from other threads would be told to x22waitx22 until the lock was released?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EJust to let you know, I am real new to multi-threaded development, so I am totally willing to accept this is a screw up on my part :)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cstrongx3EAm I missing something?x3C/strongx3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cstrongx3EWhat is the best file access strategy in a multi-threaded environment?x3C/strongx3E\nx3Chr /x3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Ch3x3EEditx3C/h3x3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESorry - I should have said this is using x3Cstrongx3EASP.NET 2.0x3C/strongx3E :)x3C/px3E',1,3,'aauger2','2008-09-03 11:44:40'),(41300,'Emacs in Windows','x3Cpx3EHow do you run Emacs in Windows?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat is the best flavor of Emacs to use in Windows, and where can I download it? And where is the .emacs file located?x3C/px3E',1,5,'cgaweno','2008-09-03 12:04:11'),(41320,'Working on a Visual Studio Project with multiple users?','x3Cpx3EI just wonder what the best approach is to have multiple users work on a Project in Visual Studio 2005 Professional.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWe got a Solution with multiple Class Libraries, but when everyone opens the solution, we keep getting the x22X was modified, Reload/Discard?x22 prompt all the time. Just opening one project is an obvious alternative, but I find it harder to use as you canx27t just see some of the other classes in other projects that way.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAre there any Guidelines for Team Development with VS2005 Pro?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEdit: Thanks. The current environment is a bit limited in the sense there is only 1 PC with RDP Connection, but that will change in the future. Marking the first answer as Accepted, but they are all good :)x3C/px3E',1,6,'hbuxcy1c','2008-09-03 12:35:49'),(41330,'How to detect the presence of a default recording device in the system?','x3Cpx3EHow do I detect if the system has a default recording device installed?\nI bet this can be done through some calls to the Win32 API, anyone has any experience with this?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m talking about doing this through code, not by opening the control panel and taking a look under sound options.x3C/px3E',1,7,'astarmoreq','2008-09-03 12:46:48'),(41400,'How to wrap a function with variable length arguments?','x3Cpx3EI am looking to do this in C/C++.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI came across x3Ca href=x22http://www.swig.org/Doc1.3/Varargs.htmlx22x3Ex3Cstrongx3EVariable Length Argumentsx3C/strongx3Ex3C/ax3E but this suggests a solution with Python x26amp; C using x3Ca href=x22http://sourceware.org/libffi/x22x3Elibffix3C/ax3E.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENow, if I want to wrap x3Ccodex3Eprintfx3C/codex3E function with x3Ccodex3Emyprintfx3C/codex3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat I do is like below:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Evoid myprintf(char* fmt, ...)\n{\n    va_list args;\n    va_start(args,fmt);\n    printf(fmt,args);\n    va_end(args);\n}\n\nint _tmain(int argc, _TCHAR* argv[])\n{\n    int a = 9;\n    int b = 10;\n    char v = x27Cx27;\n    myprintf(x22This is a number: %d and \\nthis is a character: %c and \\n another number: %d\\nx22,a, v, b);\n    return 0;\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBut the results are not as expected!x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EThis is a number: 1244780 and\nthis is a character: h and\nanother number: 29953463\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny point where did I miss??x3C/px3E',1,8,'prihak','2008-09-03 14:12:27'),(41460,'What are the differences between GPL v2 and GPL v3 licenses?','x3Cpx3EIn simple terms, what are the reasons for, and what are the differences between the GPL v2 and GPL v3 open source licenses? Explanations and references to legal terms and further descriptions would be appreciated.x3C/px3E',1,6,'hschade12','2008-09-03 15:05:11'),(41580,'Should I Keep Registering A Failure?','x3Cpx3EIx27m working on an automated regression test suite for an app which I maintain.  While developing the automated regression test, I ran across some behavior thatx27s almost certainly a bug.  So, for now, Ix27ve modified the automated regression test to not register a failure--itx27s deliberately allowing this bad behavior to go by, I mean.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo, I am interested in the opinions of others on this site.  Obviously, Ix27ll add a bug to our defect tracking to make sure this error behavior gets fixed.  But are there any compelling reasons (either way) to either change the regression test to constantly indicate failure or leave the regression test broken and not have a failure until we can get to fixing the defective behavior?  I think of this as a 6 of one and a half-dozen of the other type of question but I ask here because I thought others may see it differently.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3E@Paul Tomblin,x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EJust to be clear--Ix27ve never considered removing the test; I was simply considering modifying the pass/fail condition to allow for the failure without it being thrown up in my face every time I run the test. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m a little concerned about repeated failures from known causes eventually getting treated like warnings in C++.  I know developers who see warnings in their C++ code and simply ignore them because they think theyx27re just useless noise.  Ix27m afraid leaving a known failure in the regression suite might cause people to start ignoring other, possibly more important, failures. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBTW, lest I be misunderstood, I consider warnings in C++ to be an important aid in crafting strong code but judging from other C++ developers Ix27ve met I think Ix27m in the minority.x3C/px3E',1,6,'rmaccurlyer','2008-09-03 16:47:10'),(41590,'How do you properly use namespaces in C++?','x3Cpx3EI come from a Java background, where packages are used, not namespaces. Ix27m used to putting classes that work together to form a complete object into packages, and then reusing them later from that package. But now Ix27m working in C++.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow do you use namespaces in C++? Do you create a single namespace for the entire application, or do you create namespaces for the major components? If so, how do you create objects from classes in other namespaces?x3C/px3E',1,2,'civakhnop','2008-09-03 16:54:06'),(41630,'is it possible to concat arguments to a command line using backquotes ?','x3Cpx3EI would like to execute an OS command from my ruby script but I want to add an argument from a ruby variable.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI know thatx27s possible by using keyword x3Cemx3Esystemx3C/emx3E like that :x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E#!/usr/bin/env ruby\ndirectory = x27/home/paulgreg/x27\nsystem x27ls x27 + directory\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ebut is that possible by using the x22backquotes or backticks syntaxx22 ?\n(I mean by using that syntax : x3Ccodex3Elsx3C/codex3E)x3C/px3E',1,5,'awrefford16','2008-09-03 17:13:06'),(41640,'Mute Specific Application in Vista','x3Cpx3EI am in need of a way to mute a specific application in Vista.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EExample: Mute just Firefox, but not all of the other application.  Much similar to muting a specific program from within the volume mixer in vista. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIf there is a program that will do this, i would appreciate that.  Otherwise if there is a way to do this, I will write a small app(Preferrably something .net).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEDIT: I want to automate this procedure, possibly key-map it.x3C/px3E',1,4,'msmallpeacex','2008-09-03 17:18:29'),(41970,'Lightweight fuzzy search library','x3Cpx3ECan you suggest some light weight fuzzy text search library?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat I want to do is to allow users to find correct data for search terms with typos.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI could use full-text search engines like Lucene, but I think itx27s an overkill.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EEdit:x3C/strongx3Ex3Cbrx3E\nTo make question more clear here is a main scenario for that library:x3Cbrx3E\nI have a large list of strings.  I want to be able to search in this list (something like MSVSx27 intellisense) but it should be possible to filter this list by string which is not present in it but close enough to some string which is in the list.x3Cbrx3E\nExample:  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3ERedx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EGreenx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EBluex3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhen I type x27Grenx27 or x27Geenx27 in a text box, I want to see x27Greenx27 in the result set.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMain language for indexed data will be English.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI think that Lucene is to heavy for that task.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EUpdatex3C/strongx3E:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI found one product matching my requirements. Itx27s x3Ca href=x22http://shuffletext.com/Highlight/x22x3EShuffleTextx3C/ax3E.x3Cbrx3E\nDo you know any alternatives?x3C/px3E',1,1,'aauger2','2008-09-03 19:49:20'),(42070,'Why does the Bourne shell printf iterate over a %s argument?','x3Cpx3EWhatx27s going on here?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Eprintf.sh:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E#! /bin/sh\nNAME=x22George W. Bushx22\nprintf x22Hello, %s\\nx22 $NAME\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECommand line session:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E$ ./printf.sh\nHello, George\nHello, W.\nHello, Bush\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EUPDATE: x3Ccodex3Eprintf x22Hello, %s\\nx22 x22$NAMEx22x3C/codex3E works. For why Ix27m not using x3Ccodex3Eechox3C/codex3E, considerx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Eecho.sh:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E#! /bin/sh\nFILE=x22C:\\tmpx22\necho x22Filename: $FILEx22\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECommand-line:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E$ ./echo.sh\nFilename: C:    mp\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe x3Ca href=x22http://www.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/utilities/echo.htmlx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EPOSIX spec for x3Ccodex3Eechox3C/codex3Ex3C/ax3E says, x22New applications are encouraged to use x3Ccodex3Eprintfx3C/codex3E instead of x3Ccodex3Eechox3C/codex3Ex22 (for this and other reasons). x3C/px3E',1,5,'tyurkiewicz19','2008-09-03 20:30:50'),(42150,'How can I unit test a Windows Service?','x3Cpx3E.NET Framework: 2.0\nPreferred Language: C#x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI am new to TDD (Test Driven Development).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EFirst of all, is it even possible to unit test Windows Service?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWindows service class is derived from ServiceBase, which has overridable methods, x3C/px3E\n\nx3Colx3E\nx3Clix3EOnStart x3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3EOnStopx3C/lix3E\nx3C/olx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow can I trigger those methods to be called as if unit test is an actual service that calls those methods in proper order?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAt this point, am I even doing a Unit testing? or an Integration test?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI have looked at WCF service question but it didnx27t make any sense to me since I have never dealt with WCF service.x3C/px3E',1,1,'nivakhnov17','2008-09-03 21:28:30'),(42200,'Managing LINQ to SQL .dbml model complexity','x3Cpx3EThis question is addressed to a degree in this question on x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/33664/best-practices-for-managing-linq-to-sql-dbml-filesx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3ELINQ to SQL .dbml best practicesx3C/ax3E, but I am not sure how to add to a question.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EOne of our applications uses LINQ to SQL and we have currently have one .dbml file for the entire database which is becoming difficult to manage.  We are looking at refactoring it a bit into separate files that are more module/functionality specific, but one problem is that many of the high level classes would have to be duplicated in several .dbml files as the associations canx27t be used across .dbml files (as far as I know), with the additional partial class code as well.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHas anyone grappled with this problem and what recommendations would you make?x3C/px3E',1,5,'cribbens4','2008-09-03 21:46:50'),(42460,'Custom titlebars/chrome in a WinForms app','x3Cpx3EIx27m almost certain I know the answer to this question, but Ix27m hoping therex27s something Ix27ve overlooked.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECertain applications seem to have the Vista Aero look and feel to their caption bars and buttons even when running on Windows XP. (Google Chrome and  Windows Live Photo Gallery come to mind as examples.)  I know that one way to accomplish this from WinForms would be to create a borderless form and draw the caption bar/buttons yourself, then overriding x3Ccodex3EWndProcx3C/codex3E to make sure moving, resizing, and button clicks do what theyx27re supposed to do (Ix27m not clear on the specifics but could probably pull it off given a day to read documentation.)  Ix27m curious if therex27s a different, easier way that Ix27m overlooking.  Perhaps some API calls or window styles Ix27ve overlooked?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI believe Google has answered it for me by using the roll-your-own-window approach with Chrome.  I will leave the question open for another day in case someone has new information, but I believe I have answered the question myself.x3C/px3E',1,9,'tplumsteadj','2008-09-04 00:04:47'),(42490,'TFS - Branching for experimental development: Solution fails to load','x3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EDisclaimer: Ix27m stuck on TFS and I hate it.x3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy source control structure looks like this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3E/devx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3E/releasesx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3E/branchesx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3E/experimental-upgradex3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI branched from dev to experimental-upgrade and didnx27t touch it.  I then did some more work in dev and merged to experimental-upgrade.  Somehow TFS complained that I had changes in both source and target and I had to resolve them.  I chose to x22Copy item from source branchx22 for all 5 items.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI check out the experimental-upgrade to a local folder and try to open the main solution file in there.  TFS prompts me: x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3Ex22Projects have recently been added to this solution.  Would you like to get them from source control?x3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIf I say yes it does some stuff but ultimately comes back failing to load a handful of the projects.  If I say no I get the same result.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EComparing my sln in both branches tells me that they are equal.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ECan anyone let me know what Ix27m doing wrong?  This should be a straightforward branch/merge operation...x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ETIA.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EUPDATE:x3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI noticed that if I click x22yesx22 on the above dialog, the projects are downloaded to the $/ root of source control... (i.e. out of the dev x26amp; branches folders)x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIf I open up the solution in the branch and remove the dead projects and try to re-add them (by right-clicking sln, add existing project, choose project located in the branch folder, it gives me the error...x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cblockquotex3E\n  x3Cpx3ECannot load the project c:\\sandbox\\my_solution\\proj1\\proj1.csproj, the file has been removed or deleted.  The project path I was trying to add is this:  c:\\sandbox\\my_solution\\branches\\experimental-upgrade\\proj1\\proj1.csprojx3C/px3E\nx3C/blockquotex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat in the world is pointing these projects x3Cemx3Eoutsidex3C/emx3E of their local root?  The solution file is identical to the one in the dev branch, and those projects load just fine.  I also looked at the vspscc and vssscc files but didnx27t find anything.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIdeas?x3C/px3E',1,2,'tvallentint','2008-09-04 00:21:14'),(42550,'Extract Address Information from a Web Page','x3Cpx3EI need to take a web page and extract the address information from the page. Some are easier than others. Ix27m looking for a firefox plugin, windows app, or VB.NET code that will help me get this done.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIdeally I would like to have a web page on our admin (ASP.NET/VB.NET) where you enter a URL and it scraps the page and returns a Dataset that I can put in a Grid.x3C/px3E',1,4,'cscarbarrowm','2008-09-04 00:49:26'),(42610,'Metalanaguage to describe the Model from MVC to generate identical client and server side code','x3Cpx3EI am looking for a powerful meta-language to describa behaviour for an application i intend to use in offline mode (google-gears + javascript) and server side sqlite + (php/ruby/java etc) and looking for a good format to describe the modelx27s behaviour which can be easily converted to the target languages.\nAm I completely off track, and there is a much better way?x3C/px3E',1,11,'mbeckinsale1a','2008-09-04 01:12:43'),(42620,'SQL Server Views, blessing or curse?','x3Cpx3EI once worked with an architect who banned the use of SQL views. His main reason was that views made it too easy for a thoughtless coder to needlessly involve joined tables which, if that coder tried harder, could be avoided altogether.  Implicitly he was encouraging code reuse via copy-and-paste instead of encapsulation in views.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe database had nearly 600 tables and was highly normalised, so most of the useful SQL was necessarily verbose.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESeveral years later I can see at least one bad outcome from the ban - we have many hundreds of dense, lengthy stored procs that verge on unmaintainable.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIn hindsight I would say it was a bad decision, but what are your experiences with SQL views?  Have you found them bad for performance? Any other thoughts on when they are or are not appropriate?x3C/px3E',1,4,'aauger2','2008-09-04 01:17:17'),(42690,'Which Dynamic .NET language makes more sense to learn, Iron Ruby or Iron Python?','x3Cpx3EIx27d like to take some time to learn more about dynamic languages built on top of the DLR and Ix27m not sure which language would be better to learn.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHaving limited time, I really only have time to look learn one of them.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny opinions on which of the two (Iron Ruby or Iron Python) would be more useful in the long run?x3C/px3E',1,7,'aa9279','2008-09-04 01:52:50'),(42710,'Efficient synthesis of a 4-to-1 function in Verilog','x3Cpx3EI need to implement a 4-to-1 function in Veriog.  The input is 4 bits, a number from 0-15.  The output is a single bit, 0 or 1.  Each input gives a different output and the mapping from inputs to outputs is known, but the inputs and outputs themselves are not.  I want vcs to successfully optimizing the code and also have it be as short/neat as possible.  My solution so far:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Ewire [3:0] a;\nwire b;\nwire [15:0] c;\n\nassign c = 16x27b0100110010111010; //for example but could be any constant\nassign b = c[a];\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHaving to declare c is ugly and I donx27t know if vcs will recognize the K-map there.  Will this work as well as a case statement or an assignment in conjunctive normal form?x3C/px3E',1,9,'sdally1','2008-09-04 02:02:50'),(42740,'What is WCF in simple terms?','x3Cpx3EWhat is WCF in simple terms?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EItx27s hard to distill the meaning from x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows_Communication_Foundationx22x3Ethe Wikipedia pagex3C/ax3E.x3C/px3E',1,1,'cleatham18','2008-09-04 02:20:15'),(42770,'Writing/Using C++ Libraries','x3Cpx3EI am looking for basic examples/tutorials on:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Colx3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3EHow to write/compile libraries in C++ (x3Ccodex3E.sox3C/codex3E files for Linux, x3Ccodex3E.dllx3C/codex3E files for Windows).x3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3EHow to import and use those libraries in other code.x3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3C/olx3E',1,3,'eburnyaten','2008-09-04 02:46:45'),(42830,'Setting Focus with ASP.NET AJAX Control Toolkit','x3Cpx3EIx27m using the x3Ca href=x22http://www.asp.net/AJAX/AjaxControlToolkit/Samples/AutoComplete/AutoComplete.aspxx22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EAutoCompletex3C/ax3E control from the ASP.NET AJAX Control Toolkit and Ix27m experiencing an issue where the AutoComplete does not populate when I set the focus to the assigned textbox.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27ve tried setting the focus in the Page_Load, Page_PreRender, and Page_Init events and the focus is set properly but the AutoComplete does not work.  If I donx27t set the focus, everything works fine but Ix27d like to set it so the users donx27t have that extra click.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there a special place I need to set the focus or something else I need to do to make this work?  Thanks.x3C/px3E',1,8,'hbuxcy1c','2008-09-04 03:29:43'),(42950,'Get Last Day of the Month in Python','x3Cpx3EIs there a way using Pythonx27s standard library to easily determine (i.e. one function call) the last day of a given month?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIf the standard library doesnx27t support that, does the dateutil package support this?x3C/px3E',1,10,'aillidges','2008-09-04 04:54:44'),(42980,'How to use p4merge as the merge/diff tool for Mercurial?','x3Cpx3EDoes anyone know how to setup x3Ca href=x22http://www.selenic.com/mercurial/wiki/index.cgi/Mercurialx22x3EMercurialx3C/ax3E to use x3Ca href=x22http://www.perforce.com/perforce/products/merge.htmlx22x3Ep4mergex3C/ax3E as the merge/diff tool on OS X 10.5?x3C/px3E',1,8,'eburnyaten','2008-09-04 05:14:33'),(42990,'Regex to match against something that is not a specific substring','x3Cpx3EI am looking for a regex that will match a string that starts with one substring and does not end with a certain substring.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EExample:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E// Updated to be correct, thanks @Apocalisp\n^foo.*(?x26lt;!bar)$\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EShould match anything that starts with x22foox22 and doesnx27t end with x22barx22.  I know about the [^...] syntax, but I canx27t find anything that will do that for a string instead of single characters.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI am specifically trying to do this for Javax27s regex, but Ix27ve run into this before so answers for other regex engines would be great too.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThanks to @Kibbee for verifying that this works in C# as well.  x3C/px3E',1,4,'hschade12','2008-09-04 05:22:58'),(43180,'What are some resources for getting started in operating system development?','x3Cpx3EOne thing Ix27ve always wanted to do is develop my very own operating system (not necessarily fancy like Linux or Windows, but better than a simple boot loader which Ix27ve already done).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIx27m having a hard time finding resources/guides that take you past writing a simple x22Hello Worldx22 OS.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI know lots of people will probably recommend I look at Linux or BSD; but the code base for systems like that is (presumably) so big that I wouldnx27t know where to start.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAny suggestions?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EUpdate: To make it easier for people who land on this post through Google here are some OS development resources:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22https://web.archive.org/web/20120506110242/http://osix.net/modules/article/?id=359x22x3EWriting Your Own Operating Systemx3C/ax3E (Thanks Adam)x3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://www.linuxfromscratch.org/x22x3ELinux From Scratchx3C/ax3E (Thanks John)x3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SharpOS_(operating_system)x22x3ESharpOS (C# Operating System)x3C/ax3E (Thanks lomaxx)x3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://www.minix3.org/x22x3EMinix3x3C/ax3E and x3Ca href=x22http://minix1.woodhull.com/mxdownld.htmlx22x3EMinix2x3C/ax3E (Thanks Mike)x3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://wiki.osdev.org/Main_Pagex22x3EOS Dev Wikix3C/ax3E and x3Ca href=x22http://forum.osdev.org/x22x3EForumsx3C/ax3E (Thanks Steve)x3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://www.osdever.net/x22x3EBonaFidex3C/ax3E (Thanks Steve)x3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://osdever.net/bkerndev/Docs/intro.htmx22x3EBranx3C/ax3E (Thanks Steve)x3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://www.jamesmolloy.co.uk/tutorial_html/index.htmlx22x3ERoll your own toy UNIX-clone OSx3C/ax3E (Thanks Steve)x3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://www.brokenthorn.com/Resources/OSDevIndex.htmlx22x3EBroken Thorn OS Development Seriesx3C/ax3Ex3C/px3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EOther resources:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI found a nice resource named x3Ca href=x22http://mikeos.berlios.de/x22x3EMikeOSx3C/ax3E, x22MikeOS is a learning tool to demonstrate how simple OSes work. It uses 16-bit real mode for BIOS access, so that it doesnx27t need complex driversx22x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EUpdated 11/14/08x3C/emx3E x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI found some resources at x3Ca href=x22http://www.freebyte.com/operatingsystems/#osprojectsx22x3EFreebytex27s Guide to...Free and non-free Operating Systemsx3C/ax3E that links to kits such as OSKit and ExOS library.  These seem super useful in getting started in OS development.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EUpdated 2/23/09x3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/users/42019/ric-tokyox22x3ERic Tokyox3C/ax3E recommended x3Ca href=x22http://code.google.com/p/nanoos/x22x3Enanoosx3C/ax3E in this x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/580308/making-an-os-in-c/580362#580362x22x3Equestionx3C/ax3E.  Nanoos is an OS written in C++.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EUpdated 3/9/09x3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDinah provided some useful Stack Overflow discussion of aspiring OS developers: x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/340674/roadblocks-in-creating-a-custom-operating-systemx22x3ERoadblocks in creating a custom operating systemx3C/ax3E discusses what pitfalls you might encounter while developing an OS\nand x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/130065/os-developmentx22x3EOS Developmentx3C/ax3E is a more general discussion.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EUpdated 7/9/09x3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ELB provided a link to the x3Ca href=x22http://www.scs.stanford.edu/07au-cs140/pintos/pintos.htmlx22x3EPintos Projectx3C/ax3E, an education OS designed for students learning OS development.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EUpdated 7/27/09 (Still going strong!)x3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI stumbled upon an x3Ca href=x22http://academicearth.org/courses/operating-systems-and-system-programmingx22x3Eonline OS coursex3C/ax3E from Berkley featuring 23 lectures.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://tomos.sourceforge.net/x22x3ETomOSx3C/ax3E is a fork of x3Ca href=x22http://mikeos.berlios.de/x22x3EMikeOSx3C/ax3E that includes a little memory manager and mouse support. As MikeOS, it is designed to be an educational project.  It is written in NASM assembler.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EUpdated 8/4/09x3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI found the x3Ca href=x22http://www.cs.berkeley.edu/~kubitron/courses/cs162-F08/x22x3Eslides and other materialsx3C/ax3E to go along with the online Berkeley lectures listed above. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EUpdated 8/23/09x3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAll x3Ca href=x22http://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/osdevx22x3Equestions tagged osdevx3C/ax3E on stackoverflowx3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://www.eecs.harvard.edu/syrah/os161/x22x3EOS/161x3C/ax3E is an academic OS written in c that runs on a simulated hardware.  This OS is similar in Nachos.  Thanks Novelocrat!x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Etangurena recommends x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MicroC/OS-IIx22x3Ehttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MicroC/OS-IIx3C/ax3E, an OS designed for embedded systems.  There is a x3Ca href=x22http://rads.stackoverflow.com/amzn/click/1578201039x22x3Ecompanion bookx3C/ax3E as well.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://rads.stackoverflow.com/amzn/click/0672327201x22x3ELinux Kernel Developmentx3C/ax3E by Robert Love is suggested by Anders.  It is a x22widely acclaimed insiderx27s look at the Linux kernel.x22x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EUpdated 9/18/2009x3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThanks Tim S. Van Haren for telling us about x3Ca href=x22http://www.gocosmos.org/index.en.aspxx22x3ECosmosx3C/ax3E, an OS written entirely in c#.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Etgiphil tells us about x3Ca href=x22http://www.codeplex.com/mosax22x3EManaged Operating System Alliance (MOSA) Frameworkx3C/ax3E, x22a set of tools, specifications and source code to foster development of managed operating systems based on the Common Intermediate Language.x22x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EUpdate 9/24/2009x3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESteve found a couple resources for development on windows using Visual Studio, check out x3Ca href=x22http://www.brokenthorn.com/Resources/OSDevMSVC.htmlx22x3EBrokenThornx27s guide setup with VS 2005x3C/ax3E or x3Ca href=x22http://wiki.osdev.org/Visual%5FStudiox22x3EOSDevx27s VS Sectionx3C/ax3E.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EUpdate 1/20/2012x3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EA set of tutorials aims to take you through programming a simple UNIX-clone operating system for the x86 architecture.\nx3Ca href=x22http://www.jamesmolloy.co.uk/tutorial_html/x22x3EJamesMx27s kernel development tutorialsx3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EUpdated 9/5/2012x3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ekerneltrap.org is no longer available.  The linux kernel v0.01 is available from x3Ca href=x22http://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/Historic/linux-0.01.tar.gzx22x3Ekernel.orgx3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EUpdated 12/21/2012x3C/emx3E\nA basic OS development x3Ca href=x22http://nw08.american.edu/~mblack/teaching.html#OSPROJECTx22x3Etutorialx3C/ax3E designed to be a semesterx27s project. It guides you through to build an OS with basic components. Very good start for beginners. Related x3Ca href=x22http://nw08.american.edu/~mblack/papers/sigcse09.pdfx22x3Epaperx3C/ax3E.  Thanks Srujan!x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EUpdated 11/15/2013x3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://www.cs.bham.ac.uk/~exr/lectures/opsys/10_11/lectures/os-dev.pdfx22x3EWriting a Simple Operating System From Scratchx3C/ax3E.  Thanks James Moore!x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EUpdated 12/8/2013x3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22https://github.com/SamyPesse/How-to-Make-a-Computer-Operating-Systemx22x3EHow to make a computer operating systemx3C/ax3E  Thanks ddtoni!x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EUpdated 3/18/2014x3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22https://github.com/klange/toaruosx22x3EToAruOS an OS built mostly from scratch, including GUIx3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cemx3EUpdated Sept 12 2016x3C/emx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Ca href=x22http://www.independent-software.com/writing-your-own-toy-operating-system/x22x3EWriting your own Toy Operating Systemx3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E',1,1,'scurraghy','2008-09-04 08:28:09'),(43290,'How to generate urls in django','x3Cpx3EIn Djangox27s template language, you can use x3Ccodex3E{% url [viewname] [args] %}x3C/codex3E to generate a URL to a specific view with parameters. How can you programatically do the same in Python code?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhat I need is to create a list of menu items where each item has name, URL, and an active flag  (whether itx27s the current page or not). This is because it will be a lot cleaner to do this in Python than the template language.x3C/px3E',1,4,'mschafflere','2008-09-04 11:36:39'),(43320,'NHibernate ISession Flush: Where and when to use it, and why?','x3Cpx3EOne of the things that get me thoroughly confused is the use of x3Ccodex3Esession.Flushx3C/codex3E,in conjunction with x3Ccodex3Esession.Commitx3C/codex3E, and x3Ccodex3Esession.Closex3C/codex3E.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESometimes x3Ccodex3Esession.Closex3C/codex3E works, e.g., it commits all the changes that I need. I know I need to use commit when I have a transaction, or a unit of work with several creates/updates/deletes, so that I can choose to rollback if an error occurs.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBut sometimes I really get stymied by the logic behind x3Ccodex3Esession.Flushx3C/codex3E. I have seen examples where you have a x3Ccodex3Esession.SaveOrUpdate()x3C/codex3E followed by a flush, but when I remove Flush it works fine anyway. Sometimes I run into errors on the Flush statement saying that the session timed out, and removing it made sure that I didnx27t run into that error.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDoes anyone have a good guideline as to where or when to use a Flush? Ix27ve checked out the NHibernate documentation for this, but I still canx27t find a straightforward answer.x3C/px3E',1,3,'mbeckinsale1a','2008-09-04 12:04:04'),(43400,'Is there a standard HTML layout with multiple CSS styles available?','x3Cpx3EWhen it comes to web-design, I am horrible at producing anything remotely good looking. Thankfully there are a lot of free x3Ca href=x22http://www.mantisatemplates.com/web-templates.phpx22x3Esourcesx3C/ax3E for x3Ca href=x22http://www.freecsstemplates.org/x22x3Edesignx3C/ax3E x3Ca href=x22http://www.oswd.org/x22x3Etemplatesx3C/ax3E. However, a problem with these designs is that they just cover a single page, and not many use cases. If you take a look at x3Ca href=x22http://www.csszengarden.com/x22x3ECSS Zen Gardensx3C/ax3E, they have 1 single HTML file, and can radically style it differently by just changing the CSS file.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENow I am wondering if there is a standard HTML layout (tags and ids), that covers alot of use cases, and can be generically themed with different CSS files like Zen Garden. What I am imagining is a set of rules off how you write your html, and what boxes, lists, menus and styles you are supposed to use. A set of standard test pages covering the various uses can be created, and a new CSS file while have to support all the different pages in a nice view.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there any projects that covers anything similar to what I am describing?x3C/px3E',1,1,'abaterb','2008-09-04 13:25:09'),(43490,'When is Control.DestroyHandle called?','x3Cpx3EWhen is this called? More specifically, I have a control Ix27m creating - how can I release handles when the window is closed. In normal win32 Ix27d do it during x3Ccodex3Ewm_closex3C/codex3E - is x3Ccodex3EDestroyHandlex3C/codex3E the .net equivalent?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Chrx3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI donx27t want to destroy the window handle myself - my control is listening for events on another object and when my control is destroyed, I want to stop listening to those events. Eg:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Evoid Dispose(bool disposing) {\n    otherObject.Event -= myEventHandler;\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E',1,7,'mheyward10','2008-09-04 15:03:04'),(43500,'Is there a built-in method to compare collections in C#?','x3Cpx3EI would like to compare the contents of a couple of collections in my Equals method.  I have a Dictionary and an IList.  Is there a built-in method to do this?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEdited:\nI want to compare two Dictionaries and two ILists, so I think what equality means is clear - if the two dictionaries contain the same keys mapped to the same values, then theyx27re equal.x3C/px3E',1,7,'aillidges','2008-09-04 15:17:57'),(43580,'How to find the mime type of a file in python?','x3Cpx3ELetx27s say you want to save a bunch of files somewhere, for instance in BLOBs. Letx27s say you want to dish these files out via a web page and have the client automatically open the correct application/viewer.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAssumption: The browser figures out which application/viewer to use by the mime-type (content-type?) header in the HTTP response.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBased on that assumption, in addition to the bytes of the file, you also want to save the MIME type.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EHow would you find the MIME type of a file? Ix27m currently on a Mac, but this should also work on Windows. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDoes the browser add this information when posting the file to the web page?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIs there a neat python library for finding this information? A WebService or (even better) a downloadable database?x3C/px3E',1,1,'nivakhnov17','2008-09-04 16:07:27'),(43870,'How to concatenate strings of a string field in a PostgreSQL x27group byx27 query?','x3Cpx3EI am looking for a way to concatenate the strings of a field within a group by query. So for example, I have a table:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EID   COMPANY_ID   EMPLOYEE\n1    1            Anna\n2    1            Bill\n3    2            Carol\n4    2            Dave\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Eand I wanted to group by company_id to get something like:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3ECOMPANY_ID   EMPLOYEE\n1            Anna, Bill\n2            Carol, Dave\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThere is a built-in function in mySQL to do this x3Ca href=x22http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/group-by-functions.html#function_group-concatx22x3Egroup_concatx3C/ax3Ex3C/px3E',1,3,'mbeckinsale1a','2008-09-04 18:27:16'),(43890,'Crop MP3 to first 30 seconds','x3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EOriginal Questionx3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI want to be able to generate a new (fully valid) MP3 file from an existing MP3 file to be used as a preview -- try-before-you-buy style. The new file should only contain the first x3Cemx3Enx3C/emx3E seconds of the track.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ENow, I know I could just x22chop the streamx22 at x3Cemx3Enx3C/emx3E seconds (calculating from the bitrate and header size) when delivering the file, but this is a bit dirty and a real PITA on a VBR track. Ix27d like to be able to generate a proper MP3 file.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAnyone any ideas?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ex3Cstrongx3EAnswersx3C/strongx3Ex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EBoth mp3split and ffmpeg are both good solutions. I chose ffmpeg as it is commonly installed on linux servers and is also x3Ca href=x22http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=205275x26amp;package_id=248632x22x3Eeasily available for windowsx3C/ax3E.  Herex27s some more good command line parameters for generating previews with ffmpegx3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cstrongx3Ex3Ccodex3E-t x26lt;secondsx26gt;x3C/codex3Ex3C/strongx3E chop after specified number of secondsx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cstrongx3Ex3Ccodex3E-yx3C/codex3Ex3C/strongx3E force file overwritex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cstrongx3Ex3Ccodex3E-ab x26lt;bitratex26gt;x3C/codex3Ex3C/strongx3E set bitrate e.g. x3Cemx3E-ab 96kx3C/emx3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cstrongx3Ex3Ccodex3E-ar x26lt;rate Hzx26gt;x3C/codex3Ex3C/strongx3E set sampling rate e.g. x3Cemx3E-ar 22050x3C/emx3E for 22.05kHzx3C/lix3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cstrongx3Ex3Ccodex3E-map_meta_data x26lt;outfilex26gt;:x26lt;infilex26gt;x3C/codex3Ex3C/strongx3E copy track metadata from infile to outfilex3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E\n\nx3Cpx3Einstead of setting -ab and -ar, you can copy the original track settings, as Tim Farley suggests, with:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Culx3E\nx3Clix3Ex3Cstrongx3Ex3Ccodex3E-acodec copyx3C/codex3Ex3C/strongx3Ex3C/lix3E\nx3C/ulx3E',1,7,'aalandg','2008-09-04 18:35:14'),(43920,'What software to use for a multistage development environment?','x3Cpx3EFor me a multistage environment contains environments for development, testing, quality assurance, maybe a client review stage and finally production. It should allow easy collaboration between developers, project status tracking and easy deployment of the application to any stage for a specific version. x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EYou can propose specific tools for specific application types but I think the question is general enough. Is there any software package ready to use out of the box?x3C/px3E',1,3,'sspindlerw','2008-09-04 18:48:21'),(43940,'Custom Aggregate Functions in MS SQL Server?','x3Cpx3EHow can I create a custom aggregate function in MS SQL Server? An example would help a lot.x3C/px3E',1,1,'hschade12','2008-09-04 19:01:44'),(43960,'COTS Workshop Registration System','x3Cpx3EDoes anyone have any experience with any COTS systems for managing workshops and the associated registrations, courses, communications, etc.?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWe have a home-built Perl system that is about 8 years old and is currently embedded as an iframe in a SharePoint portal site (externally facing). Needless to say, it isnx27t integrated into our site well, looks like crap, needs an overhaul, lacks features, etc. It would be nice to find either a product we can install or a service that provides those features.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThanks!x3C/px3E',1,3,'rtomeo0','2008-09-04 19:07:30'),(43970,'Configuring sendmail behind a firewall','x3Cpx3EIx27m setting up a server which is on a network behind a firewall and I want programs on this computer to be able to use sendmail to send emails to any email address.  We have an SMTP server running on this network (letx27s call it mailrelay.example.com) which is how wex27re supposed to get outgoing emails through the firewall.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo how do I configure sendmail to send all mail through mailrelay.example.com?  Googling hasnx27t given me the answer yet, and has only revealed that sendmail configuration is extremely complex and annoying.x3C/px3E',1,8,'scurraghy','2008-09-04 19:10:13'),(44080,'Does Microsoft ASP.NET Ajax Cause DOM Object Leaks?','x3Cpx3EWex27ve been using x22Dripx22 to try and identify why pages with UpdatePanels in them tend to use a lot of client-side memory.  With a page with a regular postback, we are seeing 0 leaks detected by Drip.  However, when we add an update panel to the mix, every single DOM object that is inside of the update panel appears to leak (according to Drip).x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI am not certain is Drip is reliable enough to report these kinds of things - the reported leaks do seem to indicate Drip is modifying the page slightly.  x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EDoes anyone have any experience with this?  Should I panic and stop using Microsoft Ajax?  Ix27m not above doubting Microsoft, but it seems fishy to me that it could be x3Cemx3Ethisx3C/emx3E bad.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAlso, if you know of a tool that is better than Drip, that would be helpful as well.x3C/px3E',1,3,'msmallpeacex','2008-09-04 20:05:57'),(44100,'Best way to use a property to reference a Key-Value pair in a dictionary','x3Cpx3EThis is a fairly trivial matter, but Ix27m curious to hear peoplex27s opinions on it.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EIf I have a Dictionary which Ix27m access through properties, which of these formats would you prefer for the property?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E/// x26lt;summaryx26gt;\n/// This classx27s FirstProperty property\n/// x26lt;/summaryx26gt;\n[DefaultValue(x22myValuex22)]\npublic string FirstProperty {\n    get {\n        return Dictionary[x22myKeyx22];\n    }\n    set {\n        Dictionary[x22myKeyx22] = value;\n    }\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThis is probably the typical way of doing it. Itx27s fairly efficient, easy to understand, etc. The only disadvantage is with a longer or more complex key it would be possible to misspell it or change only one instance or something, leading me to this:x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3E/// x26lt;summaryx26gt;\n/// This classx27s SecondProperty property\n/// x26lt;/summaryx26gt;\n[DefaultValue(x22myValuex22)]\nprivate const string DICT_MYKEY = x22myKeyx22\npublic string SecondProperty {\n    get {\n        return Dictionary[DICT_MYKEY];\n    }\n    set {\n        Dictionary[DICT_MYKEY] = value;\n    }\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EWhich is marginally more complicated, but seems to offer additional safety, and is closer to what I would think of as the x22Code Completex22 solution. The downside is that when you also have a ///  block and a [DefaultValue()] block above the property already, it starts getting a bit crowded up there.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3ESo which do you like better, and why? Does anybody have any better ideas?x3C/px3E',1,2,'itrowla','2008-09-04 20:15:13'),(44190,'Looking for a simple JavaScript example that updates DOM','x3Cpx3EI am looking for a simple JavaScript example that updates DOM.x3Cbrx3E\nAny suggestions?x3C/px3E',1,3,'dmatuszinski15','2008-09-04 21:06:32'),(44220,'Difference between foreach and for loops over an IEnumerable class in C#','x3Cpx3EI have been told that there is a performance difference between the following code blocks.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Eforeach (Entity e in entityList)\n{\n ....\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Eand x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3Efor (int i=0; ix26lt;entityList.Count; i++)\n{\n   Entity e = (Entity)entityList[i];\n   ...\n}\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3Ewherex3C/px3E\n\nx3Cprex3Ex3Ccodex3EListx26lt;Entityx26gt; entityList;\nx3C/codex3Ex3C/prex3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI am no CLR expect but from what I can tell they should boil down to basically the same code.  Does anybody have concrete (heck, Ix27d take packed dirt) evidence one way or the other?x3C/px3E',1,3,'awrefford16','2008-09-04 21:20:16'),(44260,'Can .NET check other running programs command line parameters?','x3Cpx3EWex27ve got an interesting case where we are trying to determine how different instances of our app were launched. Is there any way for .NET to be able to query another running instance and get the command line parameters passed to that instance? Ix27ve not been able to find any way to do it in .NET so far, so I thought Ix27d check here to see if anyone had done anything like this before.x3C/px3E',1,1,'abaterb','2008-09-04 21:34:27'),(44270,'Order an Array like another Array in C#','x3Cpx3EIx27m looking for the best algorithm to take array A {0,1,2,3} and make order it like array B {3,1,0,2}.  Any ideas?x3C/px3E',1,10,'hginglell13','2008-09-04 21:37:04'),(44350,'What are the best keyboard macros for programming in windows?','x3Cpx3EI like putting shortcuts of the form x22g - google.lnkx22 in my start menu so google is two keystrokes away. Win, g.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EMy eight or so most frequent applications go there.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EI also make links to my solution files I am always opening x22x - Popular Project.lnkx22x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EAre there any better ways to automate opening frequently used applications?x3C/px3E',1,5,'eburnyaten','2008-09-04 22:04:01'),(44470,'How do I get the ClickOnce Publish version to match the AssemblyInfo.cs File version?','x3Cpx3EEvery time I publish the application in x3Ca href=x22http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ClickOncex22 rel=x22nofollowx22x3EClickOncex3C/ax3E I get get it to update the revision number by one. Is there a way to get this change automatically to change the version number in AssemblyInfo.cs file (all our error reporting looks at the Assembly Version)?x3C/px3E',1,11,'cgaweno','2008-09-04 22:54:01'),(44630,'version control practice','x3Cpx3EIn my current job the supervisorx27s practice is to only check in production ready code.  Most recently the project I was on involved work by 3 different developers with some file overlap.  This meant manually integrating changes despite the fact that some changes took a day and then it was done.  I wanted to see if this was a common practice and get suggestions on how to change this practice with the knowledge that many times my opinion means little in the grand scheme of things.x3C/px3E',1,4,'fbrizellc','2008-09-04 23:51:26'),(44660,'Regex in VB6?','x3Cpx3EI need to write a program that can sift through specially-formatted text files (essentially CSV files with a fixed set of column types that have different delimiters for some columns ... comma in most places, colons in others) to search for formatting errors.  I figure regular expressions will be the way to go.x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThe question:  Is there a good regex library for VB6?x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EThank you!x3C/px3E\n\nx3Cpx3EEdit:  Holy crap, 3 responses in under an hour.  Thanks a ton, folks!  Ix27ve heard such good things about Regex Buddy from Jeffx27s postings / podcasting, that I will have to take a look.x3C/px3E',1,4,'wscreen1b','2008-09-05 00:07:28'),(44760,'Eclipse x22Share Projectx22 by hand?','x3Cpx3EWhat actually happens to the file system when you do a Subclipse Share Project on an Eclipse project that was externally checked out from Subversion?  All the .svn folders are already in place.  I get an error when I try to Share Project the right way, and Ix27d rather not delete and re-checkout the projects from the SVN  Repository browser.x3C/px3E',1,5,'gdodding5','2008-09-05 00:54:41'),(44761,'How to use vscode?','How?',0,7,'srm4902','2022-05-07 13:24:03'),(44762,'Something pHP','PHP',0,5,'srm4902','2022-05-07 14:05:20');
